01:43:15.800 --> 01:43:17.800
[Guest]: So, why is he doing this extra?

01:43:17.800 --> 01:43:19.800
[Guest]: Then, I understood one thing.

01:43:19.800 --> 01:43:21.800
[Guest]: Why does Yogi Adityanath have his own IT cell?

01:43:21.800 --> 01:43:22.800
[Guest]: Separately.

01:43:22.800 --> 01:43:24.800
[Guest]: There is a separate IT cell for UP.

01:43:24.800 --> 01:43:26.800
[Guest]: There is for separate states also.

01:43:26.800 --> 01:43:28.800
[Guest]: But the Yogi one is slightly more prominent.

01:43:28.800 --> 01:43:29.800
[Guest]: Why?

01:43:29.800 --> 01:43:30.800
[Guest]: Why?

01:43:30.800 --> 01:43:31.800
[Guest]: I don't know.

01:43:31.800 --> 01:43:33.800
[Guest]: I really don't know.

01:43:33.800 --> 01:43:35.800
[Guest]: Like, I have only been able to observe these things.

01:43:35.800 --> 01:43:37.800
[Guest]: But I have no reasons for these things.

01:43:37.800 --> 01:43:40.800
[Guest]: But the thing is that,

01:43:40.800 --> 01:43:42.800
[Guest]: the large point I am trying to make is,

01:43:42.800 --> 01:43:44.800
[Guest]: you start not looking at it as a monolith.

01:43:44.800 --> 01:43:48.800
[Guest]: You understand that everyone has different opinions there also.

01:43:48.800 --> 01:43:50.800
[Guest]: Someone is saying something,

01:43:50.800 --> 01:43:51.800
[Guest]: someone is saying something,

01:43:51.800 --> 01:43:52.800
[Guest]: someone is fighting with someone,

01:43:52.800 --> 01:43:53.800
[Guest]: someone is fighting with someone.

01:43:53.800 --> 01:43:57.800
[Guest]: There is no ecosystem like a right-wing.

01:43:57.800 --> 01:43:58.800
[Guest]: There is a gradation in them also.

01:43:58.800 --> 01:44:00.800
[Guest]: People are fighting and doing this and that.

01:44:00.800 --> 01:44:02.800
[Guest]: And a lot of times, there are a lot of things

01:44:02.800 --> 01:44:04.800
[Guest]: where they don't talk about it.

01:44:04.800 --> 01:44:05.800
[Guest]: Where they are fighting.

01:44:05.800 --> 01:44:09.800
[Guest]: And those fissures are not adequately exploited.

01:44:09.800 --> 01:44:11.800
[Amit Varma]: So, I have a follow-up question.

01:44:11.800 --> 01:44:13.800
[Amit Varma]: But before that, I just want to say that,

01:44:13.800 --> 01:44:16.800
[Amit Varma]: what you mentioned about the reason they are targeting you

01:44:16.800 --> 01:44:19.800
[Amit Varma]: is because you are the kind of Muslim they are afraid of.

01:44:19.800 --> 01:44:21.800
[Amit Varma]: Educated, articulate,

01:44:21.800 --> 01:44:24.800
[Amit Varma]: who is not going to respond to their rebel rousing

01:44:24.800 --> 01:44:26.800
[Amit Varma]: with more rebel rousing.

01:44:26.800 --> 01:44:27.800
[Amit Varma]: I think that's a great point.

01:44:27.800 --> 01:44:29.800
[Amit Varma]: I mean, I think of someone like Munawar Faruqi.

01:44:29.800 --> 01:44:31.800
[Amit Varma]: And it's natural that they would see him as a threat

01:44:31.800 --> 01:44:35.800
[Amit Varma]: because not only is Munawar a fantastic comedian,

01:44:35.800 --> 01:44:37.800
[Amit Varma]: but how can you see him and not love him?

01:44:37.800 --> 01:44:38.800
[Amit Varma]: Right?

01:44:38.800 --> 01:44:40.800
[Amit Varma]: So, obviously, they'll want to cut down on him,

01:44:40.800 --> 01:44:42.800
[Amit Varma]: on you, on Umar Khalid, for example,

01:44:42.800 --> 01:44:43.800
[Amit Varma]: poor guy in jail for so long.

01:44:43.800 --> 01:44:47.800
[Amit Varma]: So, that's sort of a great point worth thinking about.

01:44:47.800 --> 01:44:48.800
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, in that context,

01:44:48.800 --> 01:44:51.800
[Amit Varma]: in fact, yesterday, I did a long episode

01:44:51.800 --> 01:44:52.800
[Amit Varma]: with Mukulika Banerjee,

01:44:52.800 --> 01:44:54.800
[Amit Varma]: might release after your episode.

01:44:54.800 --> 01:44:55.800
[Amit Varma]: We spoke about all her books.

01:44:55.800 --> 01:44:56.800
[Amit Varma]: Very long episode.

01:44:56.800 --> 01:44:57.800
[Amit Varma]: And in that, you know,

01:44:57.800 --> 01:44:59.800
[Amit Varma]: she spoke about a book that she had edited.

01:44:59.800 --> 01:45:01.800
[Amit Varma]: And the book is called Muslim Portraits.

01:45:01.800 --> 01:45:02.800
[Unknown]: Yeah.

01:45:02.800 --> 01:45:04.800
[Amit Varma]: Where she got portraits of different, you know,

01:45:04.800 --> 01:45:06.800
[Amit Varma]: Muslims written by different writers.

01:45:06.800 --> 01:45:07.800
[Amit Varma]: And her point was this.

01:45:07.800 --> 01:45:10.800
[Amit Varma]: And it is a point that I think, you know,

01:45:10.800 --> 01:45:12.800
[Amit Varma]: in a different way, you've tried versions of that.

01:45:12.800 --> 01:45:14.800
[Amit Varma]: And her point was that right now,

01:45:14.800 --> 01:45:15.800
[Amit Varma]: there is a stereotype.

01:45:15.800 --> 01:45:17.800
[Amit Varma]: Ki Musalman aisa hai.

01:45:17.800 --> 01:45:20.800
[Amit Varma]: And the point is that is, you know,

01:45:20.800 --> 01:45:23.800
[Amit Varma]: I often use the sort of the framework

01:45:23.800 --> 01:45:24.800
[Amit Varma]: of abstract and concrete.

01:45:24.800 --> 01:45:26.800
[Amit Varma]: But I think a lot of the negativity in us

01:45:26.800 --> 01:45:29.800
[Amit Varma]: comes from abstract concepts like nationalism,

01:45:29.800 --> 01:45:31.800
[Amit Varma]: purity, civilization, all of that crap.

01:45:31.800 --> 01:45:32.800
[Amit Varma]: But in the concrete,

01:45:32.800 --> 01:45:34.800
[Amit Varma]: when we encounter something,

01:45:34.800 --> 01:45:36.800
[Amit Varma]: we may not, you know, react quite the same way.

01:45:36.800 --> 01:45:38.800
[Amit Varma]: And what she was trying to do in a sense

01:45:38.800 --> 01:45:41.800
[Amit Varma]: is go beyond that abstract stereotype of a Muslim

01:45:41.800 --> 01:45:43.800
[Amit Varma]: and give you nine specific Muslim lives

01:45:43.800 --> 01:45:45.800
[Unknown]: of people who are just like you,

01:45:45.800 --> 01:45:47.800
[Amit Varma]: who have the same, who share your humanity,

01:45:47.800 --> 01:45:50.800
[Amit Varma]: who might, you know, be sad about the same things

01:45:50.800 --> 01:45:52.800
[Amit Varma]: like the same music, eat the same food, all of that.

01:45:52.800 --> 01:45:54.800
[Unknown]: And therefore kind of humanize them.

01:45:54.800 --> 01:45:56.800
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, in a sense,

01:45:56.800 --> 01:45:57.800
[Amit Varma]: in a different kind of aspect,

01:45:57.800 --> 01:45:59.800
[Amit Varma]: you did that with your great poem,

01:45:59.800 --> 01:46:00.800
[Amit Varma]: Hindustani Musalman also,

01:46:00.800 --> 01:46:01.800
[Amit Varma]: where you're showing that, hey,

01:46:01.800 --> 01:46:02.800
[Amit Varma]: you know, we contain multitudes.

01:46:02.800 --> 01:46:04.800
[Amit Varma]: It's not just one thing.

01:46:04.800 --> 01:46:06.800
[Amit Varma]: My follow-up question is this,

01:46:06.800 --> 01:46:08.800
[Amit Varma]: when you say that they're not a monolith.

01:46:08.800 --> 01:46:10.800
[Amit Varma]: And I did an episode early last year

01:46:10.800 --> 01:46:12.800
[Amit Varma]: with Raghu Sanjay Lal Jaitley.

01:46:12.800 --> 01:46:13.800
[Amit Varma]: That's a pseudonym.

01:46:13.800 --> 01:46:14.800
[Amit Varma]: He doesn't write under his real name.

01:46:14.800 --> 01:46:16.800
[Amit Varma]: He writes this great newsletter.

01:46:16.800 --> 01:46:19.800
[Amit Varma]: And we were discussing the political theorist,

01:46:19.800 --> 01:46:21.800
[Amit Varma]: Carl Schmitt's formulation

01:46:21.800 --> 01:46:23.800
[Amit Varma]: that in politics, you need an other, right?

01:46:23.800 --> 01:46:24.800
[Unknown]: An enemy.

01:46:24.800 --> 01:46:25.800
[Amit Varma]: It's always about that.

01:46:25.800 --> 01:46:27.800
[Amit Varma]: Like you will not go out there

01:46:27.800 --> 01:46:28.800
[Amit Varma]: with a positive emotion

01:46:28.800 --> 01:46:30.800
[Amit Varma]: and rouse the people to vote for you.

01:46:30.800 --> 01:46:32.800
[Amit Varma]: You will go out there with a negative emotion.

01:46:32.800 --> 01:46:33.800
[Amit Varma]: You need an other.

01:46:33.800 --> 01:46:34.800
[Amit Varma]: So at one hand,

01:46:34.800 --> 01:46:36.800
[Amit Varma]: obviously the other for the BJP is a Muslim.

01:46:36.800 --> 01:46:38.800
[Amit Varma]: But if you look in the political space,

01:46:38.800 --> 01:46:40.800
[Amit Varma]: they have eviscerated the other

01:46:40.800 --> 01:46:43.800
[Amit Varma]: in the sense that there is no opposition to speak of.

01:46:43.800 --> 01:46:45.800
[Amit Varma]: And we'll come to that later also.

01:46:45.800 --> 01:46:47.800
[Amit Varma]: But there is no opposition to speak of.

01:46:47.800 --> 01:46:49.800
[Amit Varma]: And therefore, you know,

01:46:49.800 --> 01:46:51.800
[Amit Varma]: both Raghu and I felt

01:46:51.800 --> 01:46:54.800
[Amit Varma]: when we discussed this whole Trads vs. Raitas thing

01:46:54.800 --> 01:46:57.800
[Amit Varma]: that now the opposition will come from within.

01:46:57.800 --> 01:46:59.800
[Amit Varma]: Because they'll start eating themselves up from within.

01:46:59.800 --> 01:47:01.800
[Amit Varma]: The Trads vs. Raitas has started.

01:47:01.800 --> 01:47:03.800
[Amit Varma]: You know, you will have the well-heeled

01:47:03.800 --> 01:47:05.800
[Amit Varma]: Swapan Das Gupta kind of bigot

01:47:05.800 --> 01:47:06.800
[Amit Varma]: who will wear nice clothes

01:47:06.800 --> 01:47:08.800
[Amit Varma]: and go to a party and all that.

01:47:08.800 --> 01:47:09.800
[Amit Varma]: But tomorrow,

01:47:09.800 --> 01:47:11.800
[Amit Varma]: the Trads are going to turn around

01:47:11.800 --> 01:47:13.800
[Amit Varma]: and say, why is your wife wearing sleeveless?

01:47:13.800 --> 01:47:14.800
[Amit Varma]: Yes.

01:47:14.800 --> 01:47:16.800
[Amit Varma]: You know, why are you eating mutton for lunch?

01:47:16.800 --> 01:47:18.800
[Amit Varma]: Why are you etc. etc.

01:47:18.800 --> 01:47:19.800
[Amit Varma]: And it will splinter.

01:47:19.800 --> 01:47:20.800
[Amit Varma]: And in a sense, that was our hope.

01:47:20.800 --> 01:47:22.800
[Amit Varma]: That eventually the center cannot hold.

01:47:22.800 --> 01:47:23.800
[Amit Varma]: It will keep splintering

01:47:23.800 --> 01:47:25.800
[Amit Varma]: till it kind of falls apart.

01:47:25.800 --> 01:47:27.800
[Amit Varma]: And you're saying you've seen the same phenomenon

01:47:27.800 --> 01:47:28.800
[Amit Varma]: that it is kind of splintering.

01:47:28.800 --> 01:47:31.800
[Amit Varma]: So, any thoughts to add to that?

01:47:31.800 --> 01:47:32.800
[Guest]: Absolutely.

01:47:32.800 --> 01:47:34.800
[Guest]: Perhaps this is not the most appropriate example

01:47:34.800 --> 01:47:35.800
[Guest]: to what you're saying.

01:47:35.800 --> 01:47:39.800
[Guest]: But this bulldozer phenomena,

01:47:39.800 --> 01:47:44.800
[Guest]: I look at it as a competition between BJP ministers.

01:47:44.800 --> 01:47:46.800
[Guest]: I also look at it as a competition

01:47:46.800 --> 01:47:48.800
[Guest]: between BJP ministers

01:47:48.800 --> 01:47:50.800
[Guest]: apart from the clear-cut threatening

01:47:50.800 --> 01:47:52.800
[Guest]: and demolishing of Muslim houses.

01:47:52.800 --> 01:47:55.800
[Guest]: It was done by Yogi Adityanath.

01:47:55.800 --> 01:47:57.800
[Guest]: Then it was done by Shivraj Singh Chauhan.

01:47:57.800 --> 01:47:59.800
[Guest]: And if you look at the recent Delhi demolitions,

01:47:59.800 --> 01:48:00.800
[Guest]: in the propaganda,

01:48:00.800 --> 01:48:02.800
[Guest]: in the cartoons and everything

01:48:02.800 --> 01:48:03.800
[Guest]: that they're sharing,

01:48:03.800 --> 01:48:04.800
[Guest]: the propaganda they're sharing,

01:48:04.800 --> 01:48:06.800
[Guest]: apparently it has been done by Amit Shah.

01:48:06.800 --> 01:48:07.800
[Guest]: Is what they're crediting.

01:48:07.800 --> 01:48:09.800
[Guest]: Is what the right wing is crediting.

01:48:09.800 --> 01:48:11.800
[Guest]: They are crediting it to Amit Shah.

01:48:11.800 --> 01:48:18.800
[Guest]: So, it is in a way them trying to say that,

01:48:18.800 --> 01:48:21.800
[Guest]: Hey, listen, I demolished 20 houses.

01:48:21.800 --> 01:48:23.800
[Guest]: Now the other guy says,

01:48:23.800 --> 01:48:25.800
[Guest]: Hey, listen, I demolished 50 houses.

01:48:25.800 --> 01:48:28.800
[Guest]: And send them compensation notices also.

01:48:28.800 --> 01:48:30.800
[Guest]: And then the third guy comes and says,

01:48:30.800 --> 01:48:32.800
[Guest]: Hey, I demolished 100 houses.

01:48:32.800 --> 01:48:33.800
[Guest]: And guess what?

01:48:33.800 --> 01:48:34.800
[Guest]: I did it in Delhi.

01:48:34.800 --> 01:48:37.800
[Guest]: This is how I look at it.

01:48:37.800 --> 01:48:45.800
[Guest]: So, now the scary part for me is,

01:48:45.800 --> 01:48:49.800
[Guest]: what if one day they decide to

01:48:49.800 --> 01:48:54.800
[Guest]: heap a pile of bodies.

01:48:54.800 --> 01:48:57.800
[Guest]: They say, I demolished 20 houses.

01:48:57.800 --> 01:48:59.800
[Guest]: Someone will say,

01:48:59.800 --> 01:49:01.800
[Guest]: He said, I demolished 50 houses.

01:49:01.800 --> 01:49:03.800
[Guest]: Then the third will say,

01:49:03.800 --> 01:49:05.800
[Guest]: I demolished 500 houses in 3 days.

01:49:05.800 --> 01:49:08.800
[Guest]: What if they make their strong,

01:49:08.800 --> 01:49:11.800
[Guest]: big swinging dick assertion

01:49:11.800 --> 01:49:14.800
[Guest]: by a pile of dead bodies

01:49:14.800 --> 01:49:18.800
[Guest]: instead of a pile of a demolished house.

01:49:18.800 --> 01:49:20.800
[Guest]: Now, will it go there?

01:49:20.800 --> 01:49:21.800
[Guest]: Will it escalate there?

01:49:21.800 --> 01:49:22.800
[Guest]: Now, that is how I look at it.

01:49:22.800 --> 01:49:23.800
[Guest]: Scary.

01:49:23.800 --> 01:49:25.800
[Guest]: And, will they eat it up?

01:49:25.800 --> 01:49:26.800
[Guest]: That is definitely happening.

01:49:26.800 --> 01:49:28.800
[Guest]: I mean, if you see,

01:49:28.800 --> 01:49:31.800
[Guest]: there is a huge number of people in right wing

01:49:31.800 --> 01:49:37.800
[Guest]: who have turned to Yogi as their next PM.

01:49:37.800 --> 01:49:40.800
[Guest]: And it is strange because during CNRC,

01:49:40.800 --> 01:49:41.800
[Guest]: if you remember,

01:49:41.800 --> 01:49:43.800
[Guest]: it was Amit Shah who was constantly

01:49:43.800 --> 01:49:45.800
[Guest]: coming in the propaganda news

01:49:45.800 --> 01:49:46.800
[Guest]: that it is Amit Shah and Modi,

01:49:46.800 --> 01:49:47.800
[Guest]: Amit Shah and Modi,

01:49:47.800 --> 01:49:48.800
[Guest]: but then he fell sick.

01:49:48.800 --> 01:49:49.800
[Guest]: And then Amit Shah has disappeared

01:49:49.800 --> 01:49:50.800
[Guest]: from propaganda since then,

01:49:50.800 --> 01:49:52.800
[Guest]: as the next PM,

01:49:52.800 --> 01:49:53.800
[Guest]: which is strange.

01:49:53.800 --> 01:49:54.800
[Guest]: Why?

01:49:54.800 --> 01:49:56.800
[Guest]: Now, I don't have the answers to these.

01:49:56.800 --> 01:49:58.800
[Guest]: I just observe and I sit at home

01:49:58.800 --> 01:49:59.800
[Guest]: and I'm like, yeah,

01:49:59.800 --> 01:50:01.800
[Guest]: this is happening.

01:50:01.800 --> 01:50:04.800
[Guest]: And I don't know what to do with these thoughts.

01:50:04.800 --> 01:50:08.800
[Guest]: But yes, there is definitely an interesting conflict.

01:50:08.800 --> 01:50:10.800
[Guest]: And I do feel that

01:50:10.800 --> 01:50:12.800
[Guest]: when there is so much power,

01:50:12.800 --> 01:50:13.800
[Guest]: so much money,

01:50:13.800 --> 01:50:14.800
[Guest]: and there is no conflict inside,

01:50:14.800 --> 01:50:16.800
[Guest]: this is not possible.

01:50:16.800 --> 01:50:18.800
[Guest]: You are sitting at the top.

01:50:18.800 --> 01:50:22.800
[Guest]: I mean, your cultural model,

01:50:22.800 --> 01:50:24.800
[Guest]: its entire manifestation,

01:50:24.800 --> 01:50:26.800
[Guest]: through the political front,

01:50:26.800 --> 01:50:30.800
[Guest]: you have taken over the government institutions.

01:50:30.800 --> 01:50:33.800
[Guest]: And you have not forced the government institutions.

01:50:33.800 --> 01:50:36.800
[Guest]: People have done it a little bit out of fear,

01:50:36.800 --> 01:50:37.800
[Guest]: but they also agree a little bit.

01:50:37.800 --> 01:50:39.800
[Guest]: There is also a little bit of their benefit.

01:50:39.800 --> 01:50:43.800
[Guest]: It is not like they have beaten everyone up.

01:50:43.800 --> 01:50:48.800
[Guest]: So, now what can make them fall?

01:50:48.800 --> 01:50:50.800
[Guest]: I think they fought with each other.

01:50:50.800 --> 01:50:52.800
[Guest]: It is not possible that they fought with each other.

01:50:52.800 --> 01:50:55.800
[Guest]: So, this is one thing I feel.

01:50:55.800 --> 01:50:57.800
[Guest]: And what I am telling you,

01:50:57.800 --> 01:50:58.800
[Guest]: I just hope that

01:50:58.800 --> 01:51:00.800
[Guest]: this bulldozing that is going on,

01:51:00.800 --> 01:51:02.800
[Guest]: it never escalates to violence.

01:51:02.800 --> 01:51:03.800
[Guest]: It is there.

01:51:03.800 --> 01:51:05.800
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, very worrying thoughts.

01:51:05.800 --> 01:51:07.800
[Amit Varma]: And you know, you were talking about competition.

01:51:07.800 --> 01:51:10.800
[Amit Varma]: And one thing I felt while watching the Dharam Sansad videos,

01:51:10.800 --> 01:51:12.800
[Amit Varma]: for example, from Haridwar,

01:51:12.800 --> 01:51:14.800
[Amit Varma]: is that if it was one guy making a speech,

01:51:14.800 --> 01:51:16.800
[Amit Varma]: it would not have been so extreme.

01:51:16.800 --> 01:51:18.800
[Amit Varma]: But because it's a whole bunch of them

01:51:18.800 --> 01:51:19.800
[Amit Varma]: on the same munch,

01:51:19.800 --> 01:51:21.800
[Amit Varma]: talking to the same rabid crowd,

01:51:21.800 --> 01:51:23.800
[Amit Varma]: out of competition,

01:51:23.800 --> 01:51:25.800
[Amit Varma]: each trying to be more extreme than the other guy.

01:51:25.800 --> 01:51:28.800
[Amit Varma]: And I think what social media does,

01:51:28.800 --> 01:51:32.800
[Amit Varma]: and this is in many different aspects of politics,

01:51:32.800 --> 01:51:34.800
[Amit Varma]: not just Hindutva, not just India,

01:51:34.800 --> 01:51:37.800
[Amit Varma]: is that it gives an incentive towards extremism.

01:51:37.800 --> 01:51:39.800
[Amit Varma]: Because once you join a tribe,

01:51:39.800 --> 01:51:41.800
[Amit Varma]: ideological tribe, religious tribe, whatever it is,

01:51:41.800 --> 01:51:42.800
[Amit Varma]: once you join a tribe,

01:51:42.800 --> 01:51:45.800
[Amit Varma]: the only way to raise status within your tribe

01:51:45.800 --> 01:51:48.800
[Amit Varma]: is by posturing more than the next guy.

01:51:48.800 --> 01:51:51.800
[Amit Varma]: And you inevitably then swing to the extremes

01:51:51.800 --> 01:51:54.800
[Amit Varma]: where you will attack people on the other side

01:51:54.800 --> 01:51:55.800
[Amit Varma]: and just attack them,

01:51:55.800 --> 01:51:56.800
[Amit Varma]: not engage with them in any way

01:51:56.800 --> 01:51:57.800
[Amit Varma]: because engagement is,

01:51:57.800 --> 01:51:58.800
[Amit Varma]: you're not supposed to be respectful.

01:51:58.800 --> 01:52:00.800
[Amit Varma]: Or you will attack people on your own side

01:52:00.800 --> 01:52:02.800
[Amit Varma]: for not being pure enough.

01:52:02.800 --> 01:52:04.800
[Amit Varma]: And you know, you eventually eat each other up.

01:52:04.800 --> 01:52:06.800
[Amit Varma]: And that's what I felt was,

01:52:06.800 --> 01:52:09.800
