[Guest]: And if there's something I don't want, gain that I get, I don't want it anyway.

03:17:26.960 --> 03:17:31.960
[Guest]: But that made me realize, no, it is good to connect to people

03:17:31.960 --> 03:17:33.960
[Guest]: because what we are doing is constructive.

03:17:33.960 --> 03:17:36.960
[Guest]: What we are doing is not, we are not trying to propagate hate.

03:17:36.960 --> 03:17:37.960
[Guest]: We are not trying to do this.

03:17:37.960 --> 03:17:40.960
[Guest]: What we are trying to do is we are trying to defend ourselves in a reasonable way,

03:17:40.960 --> 03:17:44.960
[Guest]: in a certain way, which is,

03:17:44.960 --> 03:17:47.960
[Guest]: perhaps some people want to listen to it.

03:17:47.960 --> 03:17:50.960
[Guest]: I won't assume that many people want to listen to it.

03:17:50.960 --> 03:17:55.960
[Guest]: But maybe some people want to listen to it.

03:17:55.960 --> 03:17:56.960
[Guest]: So we should think.

03:17:56.960 --> 03:17:59.960
[Guest]: And we do spend a lot of time on it.

03:17:59.960 --> 03:18:03.960
[Guest]: I mean, I can't tell you how much time I spend on this.

03:18:03.960 --> 03:18:07.960
[Guest]: That every day, we talk about it for 2-3 hours.

03:18:07.960 --> 03:18:11.960
[Guest]: So not everyone can do this because

03:18:11.960 --> 03:18:14.960
[Guest]: not everyone has a knife on their neck.

03:18:14.960 --> 03:18:17.960
[Amit Varma]: That's a lovely way to put it.

03:18:17.960 --> 03:18:22.960
[Guest]: So our discourse doesn't end at 2 at night

03:18:22.960 --> 03:18:25.960
[Guest]: because we know that these people will start again the next day.

03:18:25.960 --> 03:18:31.960
[Guest]: So I can't stop fighting fascism by closing Twitter at 12 at night.

03:18:31.960 --> 03:18:33.960
[Guest]: That's not an option for me.

03:18:33.960 --> 03:18:39.960
[Guest]: So that drives us and pushes us forward.

03:18:39.960 --> 03:18:42.960
[Guest]: Another thing that gives me confidence,

03:18:42.960 --> 03:18:44.960
[Guest]: which I like,

03:18:44.960 --> 03:18:50.960
[Guest]: and which I am sure the poor RSS people find very bad,

03:18:50.960 --> 03:18:54.960
[Guest]: is that my understanding is that

03:18:54.960 --> 03:19:00.960
[Guest]: the Muslim society is very independent in many ways.

03:19:00.960 --> 03:19:03.960
[Guest]: They have their religion,

03:19:03.960 --> 03:19:06.960
[Guest]: they have their God,

03:19:06.960 --> 03:19:08.960
[Guest]: they have their book,

03:19:08.960 --> 03:19:10.960
[Guest]: they have their prophet.

03:19:10.960 --> 03:19:13.960
[Guest]: So they are not dependent.

03:19:13.960 --> 03:19:21.960
[Guest]: They have to give a spiritual fulfillment from a religious angle.

03:19:21.960 --> 03:19:23.960
[Guest]: And they are doing that.

03:19:23.960 --> 03:19:25.960
[Guest]: In their own way.

03:19:25.960 --> 03:19:29.960
[Guest]: Now, there is criticism in the Abrahamic religion.

03:19:29.960 --> 03:19:30.960
[Guest]: That's a different thing.

03:19:30.960 --> 03:19:31.960
[Guest]: It's a theological discussion.

03:19:31.960 --> 03:19:33.960
[Guest]: I am not giving a theological discussion.

03:19:33.960 --> 03:19:36.960
[Guest]: I am talking from the context of a religion that provides a very basic utility.

03:19:36.960 --> 03:19:41.960
[Guest]: A different religion that provides in a diverse country like India.

03:19:41.960 --> 03:19:43.960
[Guest]: I am talking from that context.

03:19:43.960 --> 03:19:45.960
[Guest]: That they are giving their God.

03:19:45.960 --> 03:19:47.960
[Guest]: They are giving their whole God.

03:19:47.960 --> 03:19:49.960
[Guest]: They are not giving half God.

03:19:49.960 --> 03:19:52.960
[Guest]: That you will get God till the temple's door.

03:19:52.960 --> 03:19:53.960
[Guest]: That's not the case.

03:19:53.960 --> 03:19:54.960
[Guest]: They are giving their whole God.

03:19:54.960 --> 03:19:56.960
[Guest]: They are giving their whole book.

03:19:56.960 --> 03:19:57.960
[Guest]: They are giving their whole God.

03:19:57.960 --> 03:19:58.960
[Guest]: They are giving their whole prophet.

03:19:58.960 --> 03:20:01.960
[Guest]: So they are giving a spiritual fulfillment.

03:20:01.960 --> 03:20:04.960
[Guest]: After that,

03:20:04.960 --> 03:20:08.960
[Guest]: the cultural aspect is also there.

03:20:08.960 --> 03:20:10.960
[Guest]: The food is there.

03:20:10.960 --> 03:20:15.960
[Guest]: Of course, there are influences in the food.

03:20:15.960 --> 03:20:17.960
[Guest]: But the food is present in its own way.

03:20:17.960 --> 03:20:21.960
[Guest]: That if you demonize biryani, then shawarma will come.

03:20:21.960 --> 03:20:24.960
[Guest]: You will go to replace it culturally.

03:20:24.960 --> 03:20:26.960
[Guest]: So, there are a lot of cultural things.

03:20:26.960 --> 03:20:28.960
[Guest]: There are korma, kebabs, etc.

03:20:28.960 --> 03:20:30.960
[Guest]: So, the food is present.

03:20:30.960 --> 03:20:32.960
[Guest]: The architecture is present.

03:20:32.960 --> 03:20:36.960
[Guest]: The clothes are present in their own way.

03:20:36.960 --> 03:20:41.960
[Guest]: Now, you can criticize modesty, fashion, hijab, etc.

03:20:41.960 --> 03:20:44.960
[Guest]: But in general, there are a lot of differences in the dressing sense.

03:20:44.960 --> 03:20:46.960
[Guest]: The boys will be able to tell better.

03:20:46.960 --> 03:20:49.960
[Guest]: And the boys will also be able to tell better than the traditional dressers.

03:20:49.960 --> 03:20:52.960
[Guest]: For example, I wear a kurta, pajama, saya, hat,

03:20:52.960 --> 03:20:53.960
[Guest]: I wear itra, I do tasbih.

03:20:53.960 --> 03:20:54.960
[Guest]: What are these things?

03:20:54.960 --> 03:20:57.960
[Amit Varma]: So many cultural and religious things have become different.

03:20:57.960 --> 03:21:01.960
[Amit Varma]: In fact, the kurta worn by Modi ji is also from Islamic countries.

03:21:01.960 --> 03:21:04.960
[Amit Varma]: Stitch clothing came to India because of the Europeans.

03:21:04.960 --> 03:21:06.960
[Guest]: How much will they remove that right?

03:21:06.960 --> 03:21:10.960
[Guest]: Now, the spiritual fulfillment is independent.

03:21:10.960 --> 03:21:12.960
[Guest]: Then the cultural is also independent.

03:21:12.960 --> 03:21:14.960
[Guest]: The architecture is there.

03:21:14.960 --> 03:21:16.960
[Guest]: There are kawalis playing in the music.

03:21:16.960 --> 03:21:18.960
[Guest]: There is Urdu poetry in poetry.

03:21:18.960 --> 03:21:20.960
[Guest]: The third is linguistic.

03:21:20.960 --> 03:21:22.960
[Guest]: We have our own language.

03:21:22.960 --> 03:21:24.960
[Guest]: There is Urdu and Arabic.

03:21:24.960 --> 03:21:26.960
[Guest]: Although Urdu is an Indian language.

03:21:26.960 --> 03:21:28.960
[Guest]: It is the language made here.

03:21:28.960 --> 03:21:33.960
[Guest]: But it has been ostracized by calling it the language of Muslims.

03:21:33.960 --> 03:21:36.960
[Guest]: So if I assume that it is our language,

03:21:36.960 --> 03:21:38.960
[Guest]: then we also have our own language.

03:21:38.960 --> 03:21:41.960
[Guest]: There is Arabic and we also understand the local language.

03:21:41.960 --> 03:21:47.960
[Guest]: So it becomes very difficult to break this.

03:21:47.960 --> 03:21:52.960
[Guest]: Because you are not giving us anything in the name of spiritual fulfillment.

03:21:52.960 --> 03:21:54.960
[Guest]: We already have it.

03:21:54.960 --> 03:21:57.960
[Guest]: We are happy with our culture.

03:21:57.960 --> 03:22:00.960
[Guest]: Actually, we take what we like in your culture.

03:22:00.960 --> 03:22:03.960
[Guest]: We are not like, this is for Hindus, that is for Muslims.

03:22:03.960 --> 03:22:05.960
[Guest]: We will not do this, we will not do that.

03:22:05.960 --> 03:22:07.960
[Guest]: There may be some religious customs.

03:22:07.960 --> 03:22:09.960
[Guest]: Of course, there are exceptions.

03:22:09.960 --> 03:22:11.960
[Guest]: But it is not that we are rejecting it.

03:22:11.960 --> 03:22:13.960
[Guest]: Okay?

03:22:13.960 --> 03:22:16.960
[Guest]: And now, like I am eating kebabs.

03:22:16.960 --> 03:22:18.960
[Guest]: I have no objection to beef.

03:22:18.960 --> 03:22:21.960
[Guest]: But I also like Indore's poha a lot.

03:22:21.960 --> 03:22:24.960
[Guest]: So I have accepted both things.

03:22:24.960 --> 03:22:27.960
[Guest]: You are rejecting biryani and beef.

03:22:27.960 --> 03:22:29.960
[Guest]: You have an issue with independence.

03:22:29.960 --> 03:22:31.960
[Guest]: I am independent and I am also delving into poetry.

03:22:31.960 --> 03:22:33.960
[Guest]: I am bringing my expertise in poetry.

03:22:33.960 --> 03:22:35.960
[Guest]: So that is my issue.

03:22:35.960 --> 03:22:37.960
[Guest]: Then, linguistically, I have no objection.

03:22:37.960 --> 03:22:42.960
[Guest]: Because if Hindi is moving like a vehicle of Hindutva,

03:22:42.960 --> 03:22:46.960
[Guest]: then I do not even need your language.

03:22:46.960 --> 03:22:49.960
[Guest]: I am independent on my language.

03:22:49.960 --> 03:22:53.960
[Guest]: So I think this thing gives me confidence.

03:22:53.960 --> 03:22:59.960
[Guest]: Also, there are a lot of communitarian things in the culture.

03:22:59.960 --> 03:23:02.960
[Guest]: For example, reading namaz daily in the mosque.

03:23:02.960 --> 03:23:04.960
[Guest]: Or reading namaz daily on Friday.

03:23:04.960 --> 03:23:07.960
[Guest]: Now, the one who has read, knows that

03:23:07.960 --> 03:23:09.960
[Guest]: Namaz is not the only thing that is read.

03:23:09.960 --> 03:23:11.960
[Guest]: Salam is also recited.

03:23:11.960 --> 03:23:13.960
[Guest]: You are doing ablution together.

03:23:13.960 --> 03:23:14.960
[Guest]: You talk to each other.

03:23:14.960 --> 03:23:15.960
[Guest]: You meet someone.

03:23:15.960 --> 03:23:19.960
[Guest]: After that, you go out to eat or drink with someone.

03:23:19.960 --> 03:23:24.960
[Guest]: So this is a different kind of communitarian culture.

03:23:24.960 --> 03:23:28.960
[Guest]: If there is a crisis, why do we go out first?

03:23:28.960 --> 03:23:31.960
[Guest]: Because this is also a religious principle.

03:23:31.960 --> 03:23:33.960
[Guest]: Help others so that no one goes hungry.

03:23:33.960 --> 03:23:39.960
[Guest]: So it is very difficult to break these things.

03:23:39.960 --> 03:23:44.960
[Guest]: I don't know how RSS is working on this.

03:23:44.960 --> 03:23:46.960
[Guest]: I know a couple of things.

03:23:46.960 --> 03:23:49.960
[Guest]: But this thing gives me peace and solace.

03:23:49.960 --> 03:23:52.960
[Guest]: That this is the strength of the Muslim community by and large.

03:23:52.960 --> 03:23:56.960
[Guest]: And the omnipresence of RSS

03:23:56.960 --> 03:24:03.960
[Guest]: is their religious, cultural, and linguistic omnipresence.

03:24:03.960 --> 03:24:07.960
[Guest]: And it is also economic and political in which they kill us.

03:24:07.960 --> 03:24:17.960
[Guest]: But these three must be very saddened.

03:24:17.960 --> 03:24:19.960
[Guest]: I don't know how much you agree with this or how much you find it.

03:24:19.960 --> 03:24:22.960
[Amit Varma]: No, I find it extremely interesting.

03:24:22.960 --> 03:24:26.960
[Amit Varma]: In a sense, I envy you a little bit.

03:24:26.960 --> 03:24:30.960
[Amit Varma]: I might be born a Hindu, but I consider myself an atheist as such.

03:24:30.960 --> 03:24:33.960
[Amit Varma]: My community is really a community of choice,

03:24:33.960 --> 03:24:36.960
[Amit Varma]: which is the next thing I will speak about with you.

03:24:36.960 --> 03:24:38.960
[Amit Varma]: And it is very limited.

03:24:38.960 --> 03:24:41.960
[Amit Varma]: And in that sense, that communitarian thing, I don't know.

03:24:41.960 --> 03:24:43.960
[Amit Varma]: It is something that is absent.

03:24:43.960 --> 03:24:46.960
[Amit Varma]: I understand that it is something that religions give you.

03:24:46.960 --> 03:24:48.960
[Amit Varma]: All the different organized religions.

03:24:48.960 --> 03:24:51.960
[Amit Varma]: But it is how it is.

03:24:51.960 --> 03:24:54.960
[Amit Varma]: It is an interesting way of putting it.

03:24:54.960 --> 03:24:56.960
[Amit Varma]: Except that it is not an argument I would make

03:24:56.960 --> 03:24:58.960
[Amit Varma]: because it almost seems adversarial.

03:24:58.960 --> 03:25:02.960
[Unknown]: Whereas so far a lot of the arguments that you have made are not adversarial.

03:25:02.960 --> 03:25:06.960
[Amit Varma]: They are simply like, don't do criminal things.

03:25:06.960 --> 03:25:08.960
[Amit Varma]: Leave us alone.

03:25:08.960 --> 03:25:10.960
[Amit Varma]: Don't kill us. Don't beat us. All of that.

03:25:10.960 --> 03:25:12.960
[Amit Varma]: And I love those.

03:25:12.960 --> 03:25:14.960
[Amit Varma]: But if you get into...

03:25:14.960 --> 03:25:16.960
[Guest]: But I get what you are coming for.

03:25:16.960 --> 03:25:18.960
[Guest]: These are great points.

03:25:18.960 --> 03:25:20.960
[Guest]: It is not adversarial, perhaps.

03:25:20.960 --> 03:25:22.960
[Guest]: I don't know what made it sound like that.

03:25:22.960 --> 03:25:24.960
[Guest]: But it is not adversarial in the sense that

03:25:24.960 --> 03:25:26.960
[Guest]: if at all it is adversarial,

03:25:26.960 --> 03:25:32.960
[Guest]: then it is adversarial towards the percolation and poisoning by the RSS.

03:25:32.960 --> 03:25:38.960
[Guest]: Which I think I am allowed to be adversarial about.

03:25:38.960 --> 03:25:44.960
[Amit Varma]: Absolutely. So it is not adversarial in a sense of a statement on its own

03:25:44.960 --> 03:25:46.960
[Unknown]: where you are saying these are the things that I value.

03:25:46.960 --> 03:25:48.960
[Unknown]: Of course not. It is a beautiful thing, in fact.

03:25:48.960 --> 03:25:53.960
[Amit Varma]: But the way you stated it in context as an argument against the RSS

03:25:53.960 --> 03:25:55.960
[Amit Varma]: that we will do this.

03:25:55.960 --> 03:25:59.960
[Amit Varma]: And this tribe versus tribe argument doesn't appeal to me.

03:25:59.960 --> 03:26:01.960
[Amit Varma]: I just...

03:26:01.960 --> 03:26:03.960
[Guest]: And I don't mean that in a negative sense.

03:26:03.960 --> 03:26:05.960
[Guest]: I don't mean tribe in that sense.

03:26:05.960 --> 03:26:07.960
[Guest]: It is not a tribe versus tribe.

03:26:07.960 --> 03:26:09.960
[Guest]: I think what I am trying to say is that

03:26:09.960 --> 03:26:11.960
[Guest]: because had it been a tribe versus tribe,

03:26:11.960 --> 03:26:13.960
[Guest]: I think I would have probably ended up saying

03:26:13.960 --> 03:26:15.960
[Guest]: that this is how we will fight them or this is how we will resist them.

03:26:15.960 --> 03:26:17.960
[Guest]: I think that what I am trying to say is that

03:26:17.960 --> 03:26:20.960
[Guest]: there are certain omnipresent features,

03:26:20.960 --> 03:26:22.960
[Guest]: like economic and political,

03:26:22.960 --> 03:26:25.960
[Guest]: that are interfering with Muslims

03:26:25.960 --> 03:26:27.960
[Guest]: and Muslim-ness.

03:26:27.960 --> 03:26:29.960
[Guest]: And just on the basis of being Muslim.

03:26:29.960 --> 03:26:31.960
[Guest]: Everything else is forgotten.

03:26:31.960 --> 03:26:33.960
[Guest]: So economically and politically,

03:26:33.960 --> 03:26:38.960
[Guest]: they are able to harm, ostracize,

03:26:38.960 --> 03:26:41.960
[Guest]: socially exclude.

03:26:41.960 --> 03:26:47.960
[Guest]: But in religion or culture or linguistic,

03:26:47.960 --> 03:26:50.960
[Guest]: they are finding it difficult to permit.

03:26:50.960 --> 03:26:52.960
[Guest]: That is what I think largely what I am trying to say.

03:26:52.960 --> 03:26:55.960
[Amit Varma]: As a statement of fact, I completely agree with you.

03:26:55.960 --> 03:26:59.960
[Amit Varma]: I don't think this would be an effective argument against them

03:26:59.960 --> 03:27:01.960
[Amit Varma]: because they have those economic and political sticks

03:27:01.960 --> 03:27:03.960
[Guest]: where they will just get to pull those...

03:27:03.960 --> 03:27:05.960
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, yeah. Economic and... Agreed, agreed.

03:27:05.960 --> 03:27:07.960
[Guest]: What you are saying is absolutely right.

03:27:07.960 --> 03:27:09.960
[Guest]: What is economic and political stick?

03:27:09.960 --> 03:27:11.960
[Guest]: That...

03:27:11.960 --> 03:27:12.960
[Guest]: What I was telling you,

03:27:12.960 --> 03:27:14.960
[Unknown]: I started it that it gives me peace.

03:27:14.960 --> 03:27:15.960
[Unknown]: Yeah, yeah.

03:27:15.960 --> 03:27:17.960
[Guest]: I did not say it as a conflict.

03:27:17.960 --> 03:27:19.960
[Guest]: I said this is what gives me peace about the community

03:27:19.960 --> 03:27:21.960
[Guest]: that these three are safe with us.

03:27:21.960 --> 03:27:22.960
[Unknown]: Right?

03:27:22.960 --> 03:27:24.960
[Guest]: But what you are saying is absolutely right

03:27:24.960 --> 03:27:26.960
[Guest]: because this is what is happening right now.

03:27:26.960 --> 03:27:28.960
[Guest]: Whether it is hijab,

03:27:28.960 --> 03:27:30.960
[Guest]: whether it is meat,

03:27:30.960 --> 03:27:34.960
[Guest]: whether it is a bulldozer or a house,

03:27:34.960 --> 03:27:38.960
[Guest]: whether it is boycotting fruit vendors,

03:27:38.960 --> 03:27:44.960
[Guest]: whether it is campaigning against biryani,

03:27:44.960 --> 03:27:46.960
[Guest]: this is what it is.

03:27:46.960 --> 03:27:52.960
[Guest]: Using the economic and political power stick,

03:27:52.960 --> 03:27:53.960
[Guest]: what you are saying,

03:27:53.960 --> 03:27:55.960
[Guest]: breaking the mosque, religion,

03:27:55.960 --> 03:27:58.960
[Guest]: defaming Islam, whatever they are doing,

03:27:58.960 --> 03:28:00.960
[Guest]: or cultural,

03:28:00.960 --> 03:28:02.960
[Guest]: attacking architecture or clothes,

03:28:02.960 --> 03:28:05.960
[Guest]: or linguistic, Urdu,

03:28:05.960 --> 03:28:07.960
[Guest]: which is spoken,

03:28:07.960 --> 03:28:09.960
[Guest]: which is known by the name of Urdu,

03:28:09.960 --> 03:28:10.960
[Unknown]: the film industry,

03:28:10.960 --> 03:28:12.960
[Guest]: and everyone demonizes it.

03:28:12.960 --> 03:28:14.960
[Guest]: So I completely agree with you

03:28:14.960 --> 03:28:17.960
[Guest]: that this economic and political stick

03:28:17.960 --> 03:28:19.960
[Guest]: keeps falling on all three.

03:28:19.960 --> 03:28:21.960
[Guest]: But I take peace on this.

03:28:21.960 --> 03:28:23.960
[Guest]: I mean,

03:28:23.960 --> 03:28:25.960
[Guest]: maybe they will stay alive.

03:28:25.960 --> 03:28:27.960
[Guest]: I mean, on an individual level,

03:28:27.960 --> 03:28:28.960
[Guest]: they stay alive inside.

03:28:28.960 --> 03:28:29.960
[Guest]: I mean, even now,

03:28:29.960 --> 03:28:32.960
[Guest]: I mean, I am not a very religious person.

03:28:32.960 --> 03:28:33.960
[Unknown]: Okay?

03:28:33.960 --> 03:28:34.960
[Guest]: But, I mean,

03:28:34.960 --> 03:28:36.960
[Guest]: they become some habits.

03:28:36.960 --> 03:28:38.960
[Guest]: That if they sit somewhere, they pray.

03:28:38.960 --> 03:28:40.960
[Guest]: Or somewhere,

03:28:40.960 --> 03:28:42.960
[Guest]: I mean, if they leave the house, they pray.

03:28:42.960 --> 03:28:44.960
[Guest]: I mean,

03:28:44.960 --> 03:28:47.960
[Guest]: if I tell them to pray, they pray.

03:28:47.960 --> 03:28:48.960
[Guest]: I mean, unfortunately,

03:28:48.960 --> 03:28:50.960
[Guest]: I have to tell them at home.

03:28:50.960 --> 03:28:52.960
[Guest]: I mean, I have to tell my family.

03:28:52.960 --> 03:28:53.960
[Guest]: But,

03:28:53.960 --> 03:28:55.960
[Guest]: I don't have any such religious

03:28:55.960 --> 03:28:57.960
[Guest]: or such behavior.

03:28:57.960 --> 03:28:58.960
[Guest]: I mean,

03:28:58.960 --> 03:29:00.960
[Guest]: and my family is upset with it.

03:29:00.960 --> 03:29:01.960
[Guest]: But what can I do?

03:29:01.960 --> 03:29:02.960
[Amit Varma]: And what happens is,

03:29:02.960 --> 03:29:04.960
[Guest]: it's your right to be as religious

03:29:04.960 --> 03:29:06.960
[Guest]: or non-religious as you want.

03:29:06.960 --> 03:29:07.960
[Guest]: I mean,

03:29:07.960 --> 03:29:09.960
[Guest]: now that I am old,

03:29:09.960 --> 03:29:12.960
[Guest]: the proportion of them being upset has become very low.

03:29:12.960 --> 03:29:14.960
[Guest]: But before, it was enough.

03:29:14.960 --> 03:29:15.960
[Unknown]: Okay.

03:29:15.960 --> 03:29:16.960
[Unknown]: Like, read,

