[Amit Varma]: everything as instrumental

03:30:29.960 --> 03:30:31.960
[Unknown]: to getting something

03:30:31.960 --> 03:30:33.960
[Amit Varma]: and all of that.

03:30:33.960 --> 03:30:35.960
[Amit Varma]: And then as we,

03:30:35.960 --> 03:30:36.960
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:30:36.960 --> 03:30:37.960
[Amit Varma]: as you spoke of,

03:30:37.960 --> 03:30:38.960
[Amit Varma]: you know,

03:30:38.960 --> 03:30:39.960
[Amit Varma]: shedding your skin,

03:30:39.960 --> 03:30:40.960
[Amit Varma]: as it were,

03:30:40.960 --> 03:30:41.960
[Amit Varma]: and meeting people like you

03:30:41.960 --> 03:30:42.960
[Amit Varma]: and the friends that you made

03:30:42.960 --> 03:30:43.960
[Amit Varma]: at the first open mic,

03:30:43.960 --> 03:30:44.960
[Amit Varma]: and, you know,

03:30:44.960 --> 03:30:45.960
[Amit Varma]: the fact that those friendships

03:30:45.960 --> 03:30:46.960
[Amit Varma]: meant so much to you.

03:30:46.960 --> 03:30:47.960
[Amit Varma]: And just now you spoke about

03:30:47.960 --> 03:30:48.960
[Amit Varma]: how you met Alishan

03:30:48.960 --> 03:30:49.960
[Amit Varma]: at this thing

03:30:49.960 --> 03:30:50.960
[Amit Varma]: and you connected with him

03:30:50.960 --> 03:30:51.960
[Amit Varma]: and you spoke for hours.

03:30:51.960 --> 03:30:52.960
[Amit Varma]: And that really speaks to me.

03:30:52.960 --> 03:30:54.960
[Amit Varma]: Because what one finds

03:30:54.960 --> 03:30:56.960
[Amit Varma]: is that so many people,

03:30:56.960 --> 03:30:58.960
[Amit Varma]: if you're in an office or whatever,

03:30:58.960 --> 03:30:59.960
[Amit Varma]: don't have that kind of

03:30:59.960 --> 03:31:01.960
[Amit Varma]: interior life that you might.

03:31:01.960 --> 03:31:02.960
[Amit Varma]: And I'm not passing judgment

03:31:02.960 --> 03:31:03.960
[Amit Varma]: and saying one is good,

03:31:03.960 --> 03:31:04.960
[Amit Varma]: one is bad,

03:31:04.960 --> 03:31:05.960
[Amit Varma]: maybe they're happier.

03:31:05.960 --> 03:31:06.960
[Amit Varma]: But they don't have

03:31:06.960 --> 03:31:07.960
[Amit Varma]: that kind of interior life

03:31:07.960 --> 03:31:08.960
[Amit Varma]: where they're engaging

03:31:08.960 --> 03:31:09.960
[Amit Varma]: with the world,

03:31:09.960 --> 03:31:10.960
[Amit Varma]: engaging with books,

03:31:10.960 --> 03:31:11.960
[Amit Varma]: music, whatever.

03:31:11.960 --> 03:31:12.960
[Amit Varma]: And therefore,

03:31:12.960 --> 03:31:13.960
[Amit Varma]: one kind of gets trapped by that.

03:31:13.960 --> 03:31:14.960
[Amit Varma]: And the thing is,

03:31:14.960 --> 03:31:15.960
[Amit Varma]: if this was 1970

03:31:15.960 --> 03:31:16.960
[Amit Varma]: or if this was 1960,

03:31:16.960 --> 03:31:17.960
[Amit Varma]: we'd be fucked, right?

03:31:17.960 --> 03:31:18.960
[Amit Varma]: We would, you know,

03:31:18.960 --> 03:31:19.960
[Amit Varma]: we wouldn't,

03:31:19.960 --> 03:31:20.960
[Amit Varma]: we would be restricted

03:31:20.960 --> 03:31:22.960
[Amit Varma]: by geography and circumstances

03:31:22.960 --> 03:31:24.960
[Amit Varma]: to a particular small sample size

03:31:24.960 --> 03:31:25.960
[Unknown]: of people.

03:31:25.960 --> 03:31:27.960
[Amit Varma]: And that's all we have to deal with.

03:31:27.960 --> 03:31:28.960
[Amit Varma]: So you're born in Indore,

03:31:28.960 --> 03:31:29.960
[Amit Varma]: you're not coming to Bombay

03:31:29.960 --> 03:31:30.960
[Amit Varma]: to go to an open mic

03:31:30.960 --> 03:31:31.960
[Amit Varma]: to meet a particular kind

03:31:31.960 --> 03:31:33.960
[Amit Varma]: of person who comes there.

03:31:33.960 --> 03:31:35.960
[Amit Varma]: You're not going on the internet

03:31:35.960 --> 03:31:37.960
[Amit Varma]: to randomly encounter somebody

03:31:37.960 --> 03:31:38.960
[Unknown]: who happens to share so much with you

03:31:38.960 --> 03:31:40.960
[Amit Varma]: and who can be your friend.

03:31:40.960 --> 03:31:42.960
[Amit Varma]: So I think one of the great joys

03:31:42.960 --> 03:31:43.960
[Amit Varma]: of modern times

03:31:43.960 --> 03:31:45.960
[Amit Varma]: is that we are not restricted anymore

03:31:45.960 --> 03:31:47.960
[Amit Varma]: by circumstances of birth

03:31:47.960 --> 03:31:49.960
[Amit Varma]: or geography and all of that.

03:31:49.960 --> 03:31:51.960
[Amit Varma]: We can form our communities of choice,

03:31:51.960 --> 03:31:52.960
[Amit Varma]: which is one of sort of the things

03:31:52.960 --> 03:31:53.960
[Amit Varma]: that I take comfort in,

03:31:53.960 --> 03:31:54.960
[Amit Varma]: that you and I

03:31:54.960 --> 03:31:55.960
[Unknown]: who might never have met otherwise

03:31:55.960 --> 03:31:57.960
[Unknown]: or been in Bombay otherwise,

03:31:57.960 --> 03:31:59.960
[Unknown]: can sit and have a conversation like this.

03:31:59.960 --> 03:32:00.960
[Amit Varma]: Would we know of each other

03:32:00.960 --> 03:32:01.960
[Unknown]: in a different time?

03:32:01.960 --> 03:32:03.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, maybe not.

03:32:03.960 --> 03:32:05.960
[Amit Varma]: So tell me your sense of this

03:32:05.960 --> 03:32:08.960
[Amit Varma]: because as much as you spoke about

03:32:08.960 --> 03:32:10.960
[Amit Varma]: that process of shedding the baggage

03:32:10.960 --> 03:32:11.960
[Amit Varma]: and figuring out what you want to do

03:32:11.960 --> 03:32:13.960
[Amit Varma]: and what you want to, you know,

03:32:13.960 --> 03:32:15.960
[Amit Varma]: how has this process been like?

03:32:15.960 --> 03:32:18.960
[Amit Varma]: Like, where, like, is there a way,

03:32:18.960 --> 03:32:20.960
[Amit Varma]: like, what are you rooted to?

03:32:20.960 --> 03:32:21.960
[Amit Varma]: What is your sense of home?

03:32:21.960 --> 03:32:23.960
[Amit Varma]: Which is a slightly different question.

03:32:23.960 --> 03:32:24.960
[Amit Varma]: But it also, like,

03:32:24.960 --> 03:32:26.960
[Amit Varma]: the reason it occurs to me is

03:32:26.960 --> 03:32:27.960
[Amit Varma]: that for me,

03:32:27.960 --> 03:32:29.960
[Amit Varma]: I feel a little deracinated

03:32:29.960 --> 03:32:31.960
[Amit Varma]: that I can't point to a city

03:32:31.960 --> 03:32:32.960
[Amit Varma]: and say this is my home

03:32:32.960 --> 03:32:33.960
[Amit Varma]: or that is my home

03:32:33.960 --> 03:32:34.960
[Amit Varma]: or that is my home.

03:32:34.960 --> 03:32:35.960
[Amit Varma]: But my comfort zone

03:32:35.960 --> 03:32:37.960
[Amit Varma]: is in this community of choice,

03:32:37.960 --> 03:32:38.960
[Amit Varma]: which is located nowhere,

03:32:38.960 --> 03:32:40.960
[Amit Varma]: which is everywhere.

03:32:40.960 --> 03:32:43.960
[Guest]: Yeah, it's very,

03:32:43.960 --> 03:32:45.960
[Guest]: like, I'll be very embarrassed to answer,

03:32:45.960 --> 03:32:46.960
[Guest]: I think.

03:32:46.960 --> 03:32:48.960
[Guest]: It's also something very,

03:32:48.960 --> 03:32:51.960
[Guest]: it's a little weird space in my mind.

03:32:51.960 --> 03:32:53.960
[Amit Varma]: Sense of home.

03:32:53.960 --> 03:32:55.960
[Amit Varma]: Can I clarify that question?

03:32:55.960 --> 03:32:57.960
[Amit Varma]: I want to read out something

03:32:57.960 --> 03:32:59.960
[Amit Varma]: which is, I had done an episode

03:32:59.960 --> 03:33:01.960
[Unknown]: with Amitabh Kumar.

03:33:01.960 --> 03:33:03.960
[Unknown]: He had quoted from Rahim Azum Raza

03:33:03.960 --> 03:33:04.960
[Amit Varma]: and he had written,

03:33:04.960 --> 03:33:06.960
[Amit Varma]: and this is based around

03:33:06.960 --> 03:33:07.960
[Amit Varma]: the time of partition.

03:33:07.960 --> 03:33:08.960
[Amit Varma]: And he wrote,

03:33:08.960 --> 03:33:10.960
[Amit Varma]: In Raza's Adha Gau,

03:33:10.960 --> 03:33:11.960
[Amit Varma]: the protest against a nation

03:33:11.960 --> 03:33:12.960
[Amit Varma]: is being made in the name

03:33:12.960 --> 03:33:13.960
[Amit Varma]: of the village.

03:33:13.960 --> 03:33:14.960
[Amit Varma]: When the fiercely well-educated

03:33:14.960 --> 03:33:16.960
[Amit Varma]: Muslim students come to Gangauli

03:33:16.960 --> 03:33:18.960
[Amit Varma]: to preach about partition

03:33:18.960 --> 03:33:19.960
[Amit Varma]: and the necessity for the creation

03:33:19.960 --> 03:33:21.960
[Amit Varma]: of a new nation of Pakistan,

03:33:21.960 --> 03:33:22.960
[Amit Varma]: the Muslim villagers

03:33:22.960 --> 03:33:24.960
[Amit Varma]: are genuinely bewildered.

03:33:24.960 --> 03:33:25.960
[Amit Varma]: One of the villagers

03:33:25.960 --> 03:33:26.960
[Amit Varma]: is a young man called Tannu

03:33:26.960 --> 03:33:28.960
[Amit Varma]: who has returned from battle

03:33:28.960 --> 03:33:29.960
[Amit Varma]: fighting for the British

03:33:29.960 --> 03:33:30.960
[Amit Varma]: in the Second World War.

03:33:30.960 --> 03:33:32.960
[Amit Varma]: He argues against the urban visitors

03:33:32.960 --> 03:33:33.960
[Amit Varma]: in the name of his village.

03:33:33.960 --> 03:33:34.960
[Amit Varma]: And he says,

03:33:34.960 --> 03:33:35.960
[Amit Varma]: now it's quoting Tannu,

03:33:35.960 --> 03:33:36.960
[Amit Varma]: I am a Muslim,

03:33:36.960 --> 03:33:37.960
[Amit Varma]: but I love this village

03:33:37.960 --> 03:33:39.960
[Amit Varma]: because I myself am this village.

03:33:39.960 --> 03:33:40.960
[Amit Varma]: I love the indigo warehouse,

03:33:40.960 --> 03:33:42.960
[Amit Varma]: this tank and those mud lanes

03:33:42.960 --> 03:33:44.960
[Amit Varma]: because they are different forms of myself.

03:33:44.960 --> 03:33:45.960
[Amit Varma]: On the battlefield,

03:33:45.960 --> 03:33:46.960
[Amit Varma]: when death came very near,

03:33:46.960 --> 03:33:48.960
[Amit Varma]: I certainly remembered Allah,

03:33:48.960 --> 03:33:49.960
[Amit Varma]: but instead of Mecca or Karbala,

03:33:49.960 --> 03:33:51.960
[Amit Varma]: I remembered Gangauli.

03:33:51.960 --> 03:33:52.960
[Amit Varma]: Stop quote.

03:33:52.960 --> 03:33:55.960
[Amit Varma]: And the question I asked Amitabh,

03:33:55.960 --> 03:33:56.960
[Amit Varma]: and I think I have asked

03:33:56.960 --> 03:33:57.960
[Amit Varma]: one or two people since then,

03:33:57.960 --> 03:33:59.960
[Amit Varma]: is what is your Gangauli?

03:33:59.960 --> 03:34:02.960
[Guest]: I think what he is saying

03:34:02.960 --> 03:34:03.960
[Guest]: in the passage,

03:34:03.960 --> 03:34:04.960
[Guest]: and what I think as well,

03:34:04.960 --> 03:34:10.960
[Guest]: is that you are made of your own soil.

03:34:10.960 --> 03:34:11.960
[Guest]: And that soil is not necessary,

03:34:11.960 --> 03:34:13.960
[Guest]: it should be the soil of India.

03:34:13.960 --> 03:34:17.960
[Guest]: It can be a very small city of India,

03:34:17.960 --> 03:34:19.960
[Guest]: it can be a neighborhood of that city,

03:34:19.960 --> 03:34:22.960
[Guest]: or it can be a street of that neighborhood.

03:34:22.960 --> 03:34:25.960
[Guest]: So, maybe that is why,

03:34:25.960 --> 03:34:27.960
[Guest]: not as a Muslim per se,

03:34:27.960 --> 03:34:28.960
[Guest]: but maybe that is why

03:34:28.960 --> 03:34:29.960
[Guest]: I have never evoked

03:34:29.960 --> 03:34:31.960
[Guest]: the feeling of nationalism.

03:34:31.960 --> 03:34:32.960
[Guest]: Because for me,

03:34:32.960 --> 03:34:34.960
[Guest]: what do I have to do with a nation?

03:34:34.960 --> 03:34:38.960
[Guest]: It has, as a teenager, as a child,

03:34:38.960 --> 03:34:40.960
[Guest]: you have a very small world

03:34:40.960 --> 03:34:42.960
[Guest]: in that era of no internet and everything.

03:34:42.960 --> 03:34:44.960
[Guest]: My attachment was always to the soil

03:34:44.960 --> 03:34:47.960
[Guest]: in the sense that I am from Indore,

03:34:47.960 --> 03:34:49.960
[Guest]: so what is there in Indore,

03:34:49.960 --> 03:34:50.960
[Guest]: which I could understand a little.

03:34:50.960 --> 03:34:52.960
[Guest]: I could understand Indore as much as

03:34:52.960 --> 03:34:53.960
[Guest]: I could understand the 3-4 areas

03:34:53.960 --> 03:34:54.960
[Guest]: where I used to roam.

03:34:54.960 --> 03:34:56.960
[Guest]: It is not that I have mastery over Indore

03:34:56.960 --> 03:34:57.960
[Guest]: and I understood everything.

03:34:57.960 --> 03:34:59.960
[Guest]: I understood all this politics,

03:34:59.960 --> 03:35:00.960
[Guest]: what is going on there,

03:35:00.960 --> 03:35:01.960
[Guest]: what is this,

03:35:01.960 --> 03:35:02.960
[Guest]: what is the zone,

03:35:02.960 --> 03:35:03.960
[Guest]: not all this.

03:35:03.960 --> 03:35:04.960
[Guest]: The 3-4 neighborhoods that I have seen,

03:35:04.960 --> 03:35:05.960
[Guest]: that is my childhood,

03:35:05.960 --> 03:35:06.960
[Guest]: that is my youth,

03:35:06.960 --> 03:35:11.960
[Guest]: and that is maybe your soil,

03:35:11.960 --> 03:35:13.960
[Guest]: that forms your base as well.

03:35:13.960 --> 03:35:14.960
[Guest]: So, I think,

03:35:14.960 --> 03:35:19.960
[Guest]: largely if I point at the city level,

03:35:19.960 --> 03:35:21.960
[Guest]: my sense of home is probably Indore,

03:35:21.960 --> 03:35:23.960
[Guest]: but then there are different things in that as well,

03:35:23.960 --> 03:35:25.960
[Guest]: like we used to have a joint family,

03:35:25.960 --> 03:35:26.960
[Guest]: so in my mind,

03:35:26.960 --> 03:35:27.960
[Guest]: in my imagination,

03:35:27.960 --> 03:35:31.960
[Guest]: that joint family is always a family

03:35:31.960 --> 03:35:34.960
[Guest]: where all those people are present,

03:35:34.960 --> 03:35:37.960
[Guest]: who came out of poverty together

03:35:37.960 --> 03:35:40.960
[Guest]: and came here.

03:35:40.960 --> 03:35:43.960
[Guest]: All those people are present in it,

03:35:43.960 --> 03:35:45.960
[Guest]: and this is also my pain point

03:35:45.960 --> 03:35:47.960
[Guest]: that now everyone has converted to nuclear.

03:35:47.960 --> 03:35:52.960
[Guest]: It is very difficult for me to imagine

03:35:52.960 --> 03:35:53.960
[Guest]: that my house,

03:35:53.960 --> 03:35:55.960
[Guest]: because now there are 3 parts of the house,

03:35:55.960 --> 03:35:57.960
[Guest]: so it is difficult for me

03:35:57.960 --> 03:35:59.960
[Guest]: to consider the house as one.

03:35:59.960 --> 03:36:02.960
[Guest]: But still, I accept that,

03:36:02.960 --> 03:36:04.960
[Guest]: so it is very strange,

03:36:04.960 --> 03:36:05.960
[Guest]: like even when I dream,

03:36:05.960 --> 03:36:09.960
[Guest]: I dream of my parents always as they are young,

03:36:09.960 --> 03:36:12.960
[Guest]: they are in their 40s or mid-40s,

03:36:12.960 --> 03:36:14.960
[Guest]: so in my head,

03:36:14.960 --> 03:36:15.960
[Guest]: they probably haven't aged,

03:36:15.960 --> 03:36:17.960
[Guest]: and that's also the age,

03:36:17.960 --> 03:36:19.960
[Guest]: 40s or 50s basically I guess.

03:36:19.960 --> 03:36:21.960
[Guest]: So in my head,

03:36:21.960 --> 03:36:24.960
[Guest]: somewhere they haven't aged since I left home.

03:36:24.960 --> 03:36:26.960
[Amit Varma]: Oh, that's a very interesting thought.

03:36:26.960 --> 03:36:28.960
[Amit Varma]: And I managed to,

