[Guest]: the introductions,

03:44:14.960 --> 03:44:15.960
[Guest]: and by reading,

03:44:15.960 --> 03:44:16.960
[Guest]: about the writers,

03:44:16.960 --> 03:44:17.960
[Guest]: the frame of mind,

03:44:17.960 --> 03:44:18.960
[Guest]: was that,

03:44:18.960 --> 03:44:19.960
[Guest]: you should be,

03:44:19.960 --> 03:44:20.960
[Guest]: honest,

03:44:20.960 --> 03:44:21.960
[Guest]: whatever you are writing,

03:44:21.960 --> 03:44:22.960
[Guest]: in that,

03:44:22.960 --> 03:44:23.960
[Guest]: the frame of mind,

03:44:23.960 --> 03:44:24.960
[Guest]: was that,

03:44:24.960 --> 03:44:25.960
[Guest]: you should not,

03:44:25.960 --> 03:44:26.960
[Guest]: unnecessarily,

03:44:26.960 --> 03:44:27.960
[Guest]: try to,

03:44:27.960 --> 03:44:28.960
[Guest]: show yourself,

03:44:28.960 --> 03:44:29.960
[Guest]: to be too smart,

03:44:29.960 --> 03:44:30.960
[Guest]: you should,

03:44:30.960 --> 03:44:31.960
[Guest]: try to say,

03:44:31.960 --> 03:44:32.960
[Guest]: simple things,

03:44:32.960 --> 03:44:33.960
[Guest]: in a simple way,

03:44:33.960 --> 03:44:34.960
[Guest]: it's,

03:44:34.960 --> 03:44:35.960
[Guest]: by writing,

03:44:35.960 --> 03:44:36.960
[Guest]: a very good language,

03:44:36.960 --> 03:44:37.960
[Guest]: you will,

03:44:37.960 --> 03:44:38.960
[Guest]: create a great literature,

03:44:38.960 --> 03:44:39.960
[Guest]: it won't be like that,

03:44:39.960 --> 03:44:40.960
[Guest]: you can say,

03:44:40.960 --> 03:44:41.960
[Guest]: very big things,

03:44:41.960 --> 03:44:42.960
[Guest]: in very simple words,

03:44:42.960 --> 03:44:43.960
[Guest]: so,

03:44:43.960 --> 03:44:44.960
[Guest]: this frame of mind,

03:44:44.960 --> 03:44:45.960
[Guest]: I developed,

03:44:45.960 --> 03:44:46.960
[Guest]: 3-4,

03:44:46.960 --> 03:44:47.960
[Guest]: like,

03:44:47.960 --> 03:44:48.960
[Guest]: first,

03:44:48.960 --> 03:44:49.960
[Guest]: honesty,

03:44:49.960 --> 03:44:50.960
[Guest]: you should,

03:44:50.960 --> 03:44:51.960
[Guest]: say,

03:44:51.960 --> 03:44:52.960
[Guest]: what you feel,

03:44:52.960 --> 03:44:53.960
[Guest]: you should not,

03:44:53.960 --> 03:44:54.960
[Guest]: pretend,

03:44:54.960 --> 03:44:55.960
[Guest]: that you are,

03:44:55.960 --> 03:44:56.960
[Guest]: very intelligent,

03:44:56.960 --> 03:44:57.960
[Guest]: you should,

03:44:57.960 --> 03:44:58.960
[Guest]: say,

03:44:58.960 --> 03:44:59.960
[Guest]: in a simple way,

03:44:59.960 --> 03:45:00.960
[Guest]: second,

03:45:00.960 --> 03:45:01.960
[Guest]: third,

03:45:01.960 --> 03:45:02.960
[Guest]: can,

03:45:02.960 --> 03:45:03.960
[Guest]: I,

03:45:03.960 --> 03:45:04.960
[Guest]: say,

03:45:04.960 --> 03:45:05.960
[Guest]: my,

03:45:05.960 --> 03:45:06.960
[Guest]: personal,

03:45:06.960 --> 03:45:07.960
[Guest]: experiences,

03:45:07.960 --> 03:45:08.960
[Guest]: in a way,

03:45:08.960 --> 03:45:09.960
[Guest]: that,

03:45:09.960 --> 03:45:10.960
[Guest]: people feel,

03:45:10.960 --> 03:45:11.960
[Guest]: that,

03:45:11.960 --> 03:45:12.960
[Guest]: it is,

03:45:12.960 --> 03:45:13.960
[Guest]: universal,

03:45:13.960 --> 03:45:14.960
[Guest]: can,

03:45:14.960 --> 03:45:15.960
[Guest]: I,

03:45:15.960 --> 03:45:16.960
[Guest]: make,

03:45:16.960 --> 03:45:17.960
[Guest]: my,

03:45:17.960 --> 03:45:18.960
[Guest]: self-experience,

03:45:18.960 --> 03:45:19.960
[Guest]: very well,

03:45:19.960 --> 03:45:20.960
[Guest]: I,

03:45:20.960 --> 03:45:21.960
[Guest]: I can make,

03:45:21.960 --> 03:45:22.960
[Guest]: this was one,

03:45:22.960 --> 03:45:23.960
[Guest]: frame of mind,

03:45:23.960 --> 03:45:24.960
[Guest]: I had,

03:45:24.960 --> 03:45:25.960
[Guest]: previously.

03:45:25.960 --> 03:45:26.960
[Guest]: But,

03:45:26.960 --> 03:45:27.960
[Guest]: this third,

03:45:27.960 --> 03:45:28.960
[Guest]: was less,

03:45:28.960 --> 03:45:29.960
[Guest]: in that too,

03:45:29.960 --> 03:45:30.960
[Guest]: this third,

03:45:30.960 --> 03:45:31.960
[Guest]: actually as,

03:45:31.960 --> 03:45:32.960
[Guest]: I try more,

03:45:32.960 --> 03:45:33.960
[Guest]: in songs,

03:45:33.960 --> 03:45:34.960
[Guest]: but,

03:45:34.960 --> 03:45:35.960
[Guest]: honesty,

03:45:35.960 --> 03:45:36.960
[Guest]: and simplicity,

03:45:36.960 --> 03:45:37.960
[Guest]: is what I was,

03:45:37.960 --> 03:45:38.960
[Guest]: focused on,

03:45:38.960 --> 03:45:39.960
[Guest]: and still,

03:45:39.960 --> 03:45:40.960
[Guest]: I,

03:45:40.960 --> 03:45:41.960
[Guest]: believe,

03:45:41.960 --> 03:45:42.960
[Guest]: that,

03:45:42.960 --> 03:45:43.960
[Guest]: on very complex,

03:45:43.960 --> 03:45:44.960
[Guest]: thoughts,

03:45:44.960 --> 03:45:45.960
[Guest]: very simple,

03:45:45.960 --> 03:45:46.960
[Guest]: poems,

03:45:46.960 --> 03:45:47.960
[Guest]: can be written,

03:45:47.960 --> 03:45:55.460
[Guest]: I have written a lot of poems in which you won't find a lot of color in the language.

03:45:55.460 --> 03:46:00.460
[Guest]: You won't feel like, wow, what a language, what a craft this person has done, what a wonder he has done.

03:46:00.460 --> 03:46:03.460
[Guest]: But even that is not zero in it.

03:46:03.460 --> 03:46:11.460
[Guest]: I mean, if you read the free poems of Urdu, I have worked on all those things.

03:46:11.460 --> 03:46:23.960
[Guest]: But honesty, I mean, like I listen to others, so I feel like what do I know about this person by listening to his poems.

03:46:23.960 --> 03:46:35.960
[Guest]: I also write songs, so I often don't like the writing style of the lyrics, which is very clever,

03:46:35.960 --> 03:46:42.960
[Guest]: even if it has become a hit, but if I feel like I have recognized this person after listening to the song,

03:46:42.960 --> 03:46:53.460
[Guest]: or I feel like he is saying this by listening to the poem, then I feel that this is a good poem.

03:46:53.460 --> 03:46:58.960
[Guest]: First, I pity honesty, of course, craft is very important for me, I am not snobbish about craft,

03:46:58.960 --> 03:47:06.960
[Guest]: but I believe that craft should at least be basic and your constant effort should be to improve it.

03:47:06.960 --> 03:47:13.960
[Guest]: So this was my growth, I mean, I improved slowly in craft, but some frame of mind remained intact,

03:47:13.960 --> 03:47:21.960
[Guest]: some frame of mind was added, like I have written some poems in which my political thought has come first,

03:47:21.960 --> 03:47:28.960
[Guest]: but even in that, there was a lot of emotion, I rationalized it later.

03:47:28.960 --> 03:47:36.960
[Guest]: Like in Chhipkali, like I told you, I didn't have a lot of political thought in it,

03:47:36.960 --> 03:47:42.960
[Guest]: I just knew that yes, this is Khaki and this is Gandhiji, it's more like feeling.

03:47:42.960 --> 03:47:48.960
[Guest]: So I have a friend who reads a lot of books, who has also read a lot of literature and has also read a lot about writing,

03:47:48.960 --> 03:47:55.960
[Guest]: he says that it's okay if you don't understand, it's fine, you write what you feel,

03:47:55.960 --> 03:48:01.960
[Guest]: and maybe you'll figure it out what you have written or maybe somebody else will figure it out for you.

03:48:01.960 --> 03:48:06.960
[Guest]: So I think it's okay, I mean, everything is news, it's not necessary,

03:48:06.960 --> 03:48:11.960
[Guest]: so I try to be a little conscious about the writing process and a little unconscious,

03:48:11.960 --> 03:48:14.960
[Guest]: it's okay if I don't understand a few things.

03:48:14.960 --> 03:48:20.960
[Amit Varma]: No, and your key point about honesty is great, like I think, you know, not just for poets or writers,

03:48:20.960 --> 03:48:26.960
[Amit Varma]: but in generally in the creator economy, I think ek cheez jo bilkul non-negotiable hai is authenticity to yourself,

03:48:26.960 --> 03:48:30.960
[Amit Varma]: you can't try to be somebody else, you can't wear a mask, you know,

03:48:30.960 --> 03:48:36.960
[Amit Varma]: if you are yourself, that is what people will really relate to, because everybody is unique at one level,

03:48:36.960 --> 03:48:39.960
[Amit Varma]: you know, the only thing that sets you apart from the 7 billion people in the world is you,

03:48:39.960 --> 03:48:45.960
[Amit Varma]: you're unique in a certain way, and at the same time, everybody is the same in the sense we go through the same emotions

03:48:45.960 --> 03:48:51.960
[Amit Varma]: and the same crisis and all that, so that turning the personal into something that has universal appeal is,

03:48:51.960 --> 03:48:56.960
[Amit Varma]: I think, you know, what all great art does, so, you know, and as far as craft is concerned,

03:48:56.960 --> 03:49:00.960
[Amit Varma]: you know, there's this quote by George Orwell, which I love, where he says,

03:49:00.960 --> 03:49:03.960
[Amit Varma]: good prose is like a window pane, and the idea is, you know,

03:49:03.960 --> 03:49:07.960
[Amit Varma]: the window pane is supposed to show you what's on the other side, not draw attention to itself,

03:49:07.960 --> 03:49:13.960
[Amit Varma]: it's a means to an end, so, you know, if I read something by you and I don't notice a craft,

03:49:13.960 --> 03:49:15.960
[Guest]: that means there is craft, that's a craft.

03:49:15.960 --> 03:49:23.960
[Guest]: Yes, yes, and I agree with this, that the art, whatever is hidden in it,

03:49:23.960 --> 03:49:30.960
[Guest]: it should look so innocuous that I can do it too, but if you start doing it,

03:49:30.960 --> 03:49:37.960
[Guest]: you start sweating, like, oh, man, I can't do this, so, I like that,

03:49:37.960 --> 03:49:42.960
[Guest]: there's that deception in simplicity, I mean, which I know a little bit,

03:49:42.960 --> 03:49:49.960
[Guest]: sometimes I do it, but I hope I know it better, and I wish I could do it more frequently.

03:49:49.960 --> 03:49:54.960
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, I first heard of you when, obviously, I saw your viral video,

03:49:54.960 --> 03:49:58.960
[Amit Varma]: Hindustani Musalma, which moved me a lot and still moves me, I mean, just for my listeners,

03:49:58.960 --> 03:50:03.960
[Amit Varma]: Hussain was just, you know, taking it very casually, and I think you're just very used to it,

03:50:03.960 --> 03:50:07.960
[Amit Varma]: and maybe you're tired of it and bored of it or whatever, but it's a wonderful poem,

03:50:07.960 --> 03:50:10.960
[Amit Varma]: especially the way, you know, things have progressed in the last few years,

03:50:10.960 --> 03:50:14.960
[Amit Varma]: and I won't ask you to read it out, because I don't think you'll want to do that,

03:50:14.960 --> 03:50:18.960
[Amit Varma]: I'll link it from the show notes, but tell me a little bit about that,

03:50:18.960 --> 03:50:21.960
[Amit Varma]: because what I love about that poem is, you know, I keep saying on the show that,

03:50:21.960 --> 03:50:25.960
[Amit Varma]: you know, people contain multitudes, and with that beautiful poem,

03:50:25.960 --> 03:50:29.960
[Amit Varma]: you're really speaking about the multitudes of the Indian Muslim,

03:50:29.960 --> 03:50:35.960
[Amit Varma]: about how impossible it is to tie someone down or even want to tie them down and all of that.

03:50:35.960 --> 03:50:41.960
[Amit Varma]: So, just tell me about, you know, that period and what the reception to the poem

03:50:41.960 --> 03:50:45.960
[Amit Varma]: and how people responded to it, what that meant to you,

03:50:45.960 --> 03:50:50.960
[Amit Varma]: because it's one thing like writing poetry very often is a solitary activity,

03:50:50.960 --> 03:50:56.960
[Amit Varma]: you're alone with your own, you know, solitariness and all of that.

03:50:56.960 --> 03:51:03.960
[Amit Varma]: And what you do when you perform it for a crowd of people is that you turn it into something else entirely.

03:51:03.960 --> 03:51:08.960
[Amit Varma]: So, one, what is that process like of having to perform something,

03:51:08.960 --> 03:51:11.960
[Amit Varma]: take something private and, you know, perform it for the world?

03:51:11.960 --> 03:51:14.960
[Amit Varma]: And two, what were the sort of responses to that?

03:51:14.960 --> 03:51:17.960
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, how did that shape the things you do?

03:51:17.960 --> 03:51:19.960
[Amit Varma]: Did it help your career in any way?

03:51:19.960 --> 03:51:22.960
[Guest]: So, let me tell you about the performance.

03:51:22.960 --> 03:51:28.960
[Guest]: When I was performing in 2009, I was performing only because I knew that nobody knows me.

03:51:28.960 --> 03:51:34.960
[Guest]: So, I was not afraid of the judgments that people would pass on my emotional, sappy, stupid poetry,

03:51:34.960 --> 03:51:37.960
[Guest]: which I thought was supposed to shame me.

03:51:37.960 --> 03:51:40.960
[Guest]: But then in 2016, when I returned to Bombay and when I was performing,

03:51:40.960 --> 03:51:45.960
[Guest]: I was performing more from the point of view that perhaps somebody would notice me

03:51:45.960 --> 03:51:49.960
[Guest]: and would help me get to write lyrics.

03:51:49.960 --> 03:51:50.960
[Guest]: That is all that I had in my mind.

03:51:50.960 --> 03:51:53.960
[Guest]: I had no idea what work is going on in the industry.

03:51:53.960 --> 03:51:54.960
[Guest]: I had no idea what the industry is.

03:51:54.960 --> 03:51:56.960
[Guest]: I had no idea.

03:51:56.960 --> 03:51:59.960
[Guest]: Despite all the Googling and all the technology available to me,

03:51:59.960 --> 03:52:03.960
[Guest]: I just came to Bombay without any prior information.

03:52:03.960 --> 03:52:11.960
[Guest]: But I knew I'll keep performing and I'll get some kind of a project if I keep performing.

03:52:11.960 --> 03:52:12.960
[Guest]: So, that is there.

03:52:12.960 --> 03:52:16.960
[Guest]: Reaction and response, especially to Hindustani Muslims.

03:52:16.960 --> 03:52:19.960
[Guest]: So, first of all, I did not...

03:52:19.960 --> 03:52:24.960
[Guest]: It was just meant to be a 30-40 people listening at event.

03:52:24.960 --> 03:52:27.960
[Guest]: It was supposed to be a poem that I'll read in front of 40-50 people,

03:52:27.960 --> 03:52:31.960
[Guest]: 7-8 times and then I'll get bored of it and then I'll retire the piece,

03:52:31.960 --> 03:52:33.960
[Guest]: which is what generally what I do.

03:52:33.960 --> 03:52:35.960
[Guest]: I get bored of it myself.

03:52:35.960 --> 03:52:38.960
[Guest]: Even though people want to take the time to read something new.

03:52:38.960 --> 03:52:40.960
[Guest]: I am tired of reading.

03:52:40.960 --> 03:52:44.960
[Guest]: So, which is a good thing also because it makes me write more.

03:52:44.960 --> 03:52:46.960
[Guest]: But it was supposed to be that.

03:52:46.960 --> 03:52:48.960
[Guest]: But then the video was to be recorded.

03:52:48.960 --> 03:52:52.960
[Guest]: And before that, one of my videos had gone viral, which is on smoking.

03:52:52.960 --> 03:52:53.960
[Guest]: Yeah.

03:52:53.960 --> 03:52:57.960
[Guest]: And so, what I expected was that,

03:52:57.960 --> 03:53:03.960
[Guest]: okay, it will get 10,000, 15,000, 20,000 views and the public will be happy.

03:53:03.960 --> 03:53:05.960
[Guest]: So, okay, I'll read a little in front of people.

03:53:05.960 --> 03:53:07.960
[Guest]: I'll call 2-3 more people to the event.

03:53:07.960 --> 03:53:10.960
[Guest]: There was no vision more than this.

03:53:10.960 --> 03:53:13.960
[Guest]: I mean, at that time, there was no scene of spoken word poetry.

03:53:13.960 --> 03:53:16.960
[Guest]: There was no scene of any virality.

03:53:16.960 --> 03:53:18.960
[Guest]: I mean, the slat that also went viral,

03:53:18.960 --> 03:53:20.960
[Guest]: the article was published in one or two places.

03:53:20.960 --> 03:53:23.960
[Guest]: It had around 70,000, 80,000, 90,000, 100,000 views.

03:53:23.960 --> 03:53:25.960
[Guest]: It didn't have a lot of views.

03:53:25.960 --> 03:53:28.960
[Guest]: Virality, I mean, it wasn't crazy virality.

03:53:28.960 --> 03:53:33.960
[Guest]: And poetry in video itself was not, you know, a thing at that time.

03:53:33.960 --> 03:53:36.960
[Guest]: This was, I'm talking about February 2017.

03:53:36.960 --> 03:53:40.960
[Guest]: So, when it was released, it went viral.

03:53:40.960 --> 03:53:44.960
[Guest]: I mean, I'm seeing that it has 5,000 views, 10,000 views.

03:53:44.960 --> 03:53:45.960
[Guest]: I said, okay, finish it.

03:53:45.960 --> 03:53:46.960
[Guest]: Now it has 10,000 views.

03:53:46.960 --> 03:53:47.960
[Guest]: What to do now?

03:53:47.960 --> 03:53:49.960
[Guest]: That's all I needed.

03:53:49.960 --> 03:53:52.960
[Guest]: So, then I'm seeing after 1-2 hours, 3 hours.

03:53:52.960 --> 03:53:54.960
[Guest]: I said, man, it has 30,000 views.

03:53:54.960 --> 03:53:55.960
[Guest]: What happened?

03:53:55.960 --> 03:53:57.960
[Guest]: What did people understand in this?

03:53:57.960 --> 03:53:59.960
[Guest]: What did I say?

03:53:59.960 --> 03:54:03.960
[Guest]: I mean, it's common sense that a person is not of the same type.

03:54:03.960 --> 03:54:08.960
[Guest]: I mean, what did people understand?

03:54:08.960 --> 03:54:11.960
[Guest]: Then I'm seeing that it's getting more viral.

03:54:11.960 --> 03:54:13.960
[Guest]: Someone is writing a news article.

03:54:13.960 --> 03:54:15.960
[Guest]: Then all the journalists are calling.

03:54:15.960 --> 03:54:17.960
[Guest]: That I'm talking from here, I'm talking from here.

03:54:17.960 --> 03:54:19.960
[Guest]: You will talk.

03:54:19.960 --> 03:54:21.960
[Guest]: I talked to some people.

03:54:21.960 --> 03:54:23.960
[Guest]: I didn't talk to some people.

03:54:23.960 --> 03:54:27.960
[Guest]: And I didn't talk to those who I didn't talk to because I knew

03:54:27.960 --> 03:54:32.960
[Guest]: what they show on TV against Muslims.

03:54:32.960 --> 03:54:34.960
[Guest]: I wasn't even interested in talking to them.

03:54:34.960 --> 03:54:40.960
[Guest]: So, I mean, I was surprised by the reaction.

03:54:40.960 --> 03:54:42.960
[Guest]: What did people understand?

03:54:42.960 --> 03:54:43.960
[Guest]: What am I saying?

03:54:43.960 --> 03:54:45.960
[Guest]: I mean, this is not even an old wine in a new bottle.

03:54:45.960 --> 03:54:47.960
[Guest]: This bottle is also old.

03:54:47.960 --> 03:54:52.960
[Guest]: I mean, so, but yes, but what happened was that it brought

03:54:52.960 --> 03:54:54.960
[Guest]: spoken word poetry on the map.

03:54:54.960 --> 03:54:58.960
[Guest]: And I mean, I might be blowing my own trumpet here.

03:54:58.960 --> 03:55:01.960
[Guest]: And it is because I'm mildly disappointed by people who don't do it.

03:55:01.960 --> 03:55:03.960
[Unknown]: For me, otherwise.

03:55:03.960 --> 03:55:05.960
[Unknown]: I'm happy to do it to you.

03:55:05.960 --> 03:55:09.960
[Guest]: But it is, there was no spoken word poetry scene.

03:55:09.960 --> 03:55:12.960
[Guest]: You can check YouTube and you can check Google and you can check

03:55:12.960 --> 03:55:14.960
[Guest]: all articles before that.

03:55:14.960 --> 03:55:20.960
[Guest]: In February 2017, before that, you will only get one video.

03:55:20.960 --> 03:55:23.960
[Guest]: The one that went viral was a poem on the English introvert.

03:55:23.960 --> 03:55:28.960
[Guest]: But all the viral poems that have come have come after this.

03:55:28.960 --> 03:55:30.960
[Amit Varma]: So, you were the gateway drug.

03:55:30.960 --> 03:55:33.960
[Guest]: In a way, I also did two things.

03:55:33.960 --> 03:55:36.960
[Guest]: I mean, the first is that spoken word poetry was slapped.

03:55:36.960 --> 03:55:41.960
[Guest]: Second, political poetry is also allowed.

03:55:41.960 --> 03:55:44.960
[Guest]: That also happened.

03:55:44.960 --> 03:55:46.960
[Guest]: And I did not know it at that time.

03:55:46.960 --> 03:55:48.960
[Guest]: I was just doing what I was doing.

03:55:48.960 --> 03:55:50.960
[Guest]: I mean, I was just happy that it went viral.

03:55:50.960 --> 03:55:54.960
[Guest]: And I was like, okay, maybe I can just send a link to more people

03:55:54.960 --> 03:55:56.960
[Guest]: and say, brother, I know how to write, give me work.

03:55:56.960 --> 03:55:58.960
[Guest]: Okay, see what rhyming is, get the song written.

03:55:58.960 --> 03:56:01.960
[Guest]: There was no one more than this.

03:56:01.960 --> 03:56:03.960
[Guest]: People were taking interviews.

03:56:03.960 --> 03:56:04.960
[Guest]: I gave 5-7 interviews.

03:56:04.960 --> 03:56:06.960
[Guest]: Then I got bored by giving interviews.

03:56:06.960 --> 03:56:08.960
[Guest]: Because I didn't come to Bombay to give an interview.

03:56:08.960 --> 03:56:09.960
[Guest]: I came to write.

03:56:09.960 --> 03:56:10.960
[Guest]: I came to work.

03:56:10.960 --> 03:56:11.960
[Guest]: What will I do with so many interviews?

03:56:11.960 --> 03:56:13.960
[Guest]: I mean, okay, someone will Google it.

03:56:13.960 --> 03:56:14.960
[Guest]: People will think he is a big man.

03:56:14.960 --> 03:56:16.960
[Guest]: But nothing happens with that.

03:56:16.960 --> 03:56:20.960
[Guest]: I mean, only this work is done by work.

03:56:20.960 --> 03:56:23.960
[Guest]: So, I was not very excited.

03:56:23.960 --> 03:56:28.960
[Guest]: So, although the interview with Ravish Kumar,

03:56:28.960 --> 03:56:30.960
[Guest]: a lot of people heard it, saw it, read it.

03:56:30.960 --> 03:56:32.960
[Guest]: A lot of people were inspired by it.

03:56:32.960 --> 03:56:35.960
[Guest]: And although he was also refusing the interview for NDTV,

03:56:35.960 --> 03:56:37.960
[Guest]: but then he talked to me.

03:56:37.960 --> 03:56:39.960
[Guest]: So, I said, no, no, sir, I will come.

03:56:39.960 --> 03:56:41.960
[Guest]: Because I used to listen to him before.

03:56:41.960 --> 03:56:47.960
[Guest]: So, the response reaction was that people liked it a lot.

03:56:47.960 --> 03:56:50.960
[Guest]: And I was a little surprised that why it was looking good.

03:56:50.960 --> 03:56:52.960
[Guest]: But I generally fainted that oh, thank you, thank you.

03:56:52.960 --> 03:56:54.960
[Guest]: What do I tell them now?

03:56:54.960 --> 03:56:59.960
[Guest]: But then as I started reading from him,

03:56:59.960 --> 03:57:04.960
[Guest]: I think it was mostly a response to the propaganda of that time.

03:57:04.960 --> 03:57:06.960
[Guest]: When I wrote it.

03:57:06.960 --> 03:57:09.960
[Guest]: It was mostly a response to the propaganda

03:57:09.960 --> 03:57:14.960
[Guest]: that was taking a very sharp turn towards collectivizing of the other

03:57:14.960 --> 03:57:18.960
[Guest]: in the word Muslim in late 2016 and 17.

03:57:18.960 --> 03:57:20.960
[Guest]: Because I realized that all propaganda

03:57:20.960 --> 03:57:23.960
[Guest]: was suddenly getting diverted towards Muslim, Muslim, Muslim, Muslim.

03:57:23.960 --> 03:57:27.960
[Guest]: And I was of the opinion that this Muslim is not of the same kind.

03:57:27.960 --> 03:57:29.960
[Guest]: We don't know how many types exist.

03:57:29.960 --> 03:57:32.960
[Guest]: How did you find out that everyone is the same?

03:57:32.960 --> 03:57:36.960
[Guest]: So, it was more of a response to that.

03:57:36.960 --> 03:57:41.960
[Guest]: So, but what happened,

03:57:41.960 --> 03:57:45.960
[Guest]: I mean, one thing that I found very interesting

03:57:45.960 --> 03:57:48.960
[Guest]: and especially after CA also is that

03:57:48.960 --> 03:57:50.960
[Guest]: during the CNRC movement, what happened was

03:57:50.960 --> 03:57:56.960
[Guest]: that it became instead of me trying to tell the majority community

03:57:56.960 --> 03:57:59.960
[Guest]: that hey, we are of many types,

03:57:59.960 --> 03:58:02.960
[Guest]: like, but we are one in the sense that we are Indian Muslims.

03:58:02.960 --> 03:58:05.960
[Guest]: I think during the CNRC it got interpreted as

03:58:05.960 --> 03:58:09.960
[Guest]: that hey, we are all together and we are Indian Muslim

03:58:09.960 --> 03:58:12.960
[Guest]: and we need to resist this as Indian Muslims.

03:58:12.960 --> 03:58:14.960
[Guest]: I think the whole thing inverted

03:58:14.960 --> 03:58:17.960
[Guest]: and I didn't realize it until I read it two or three times.

03:58:17.960 --> 03:58:21.960
[Guest]: And one of the reasons I kept reading that poem during CNRC

03:58:21.960 --> 03:58:24.960
[Guest]: was also because I wanted to very clearly register the fact

03:58:24.960 --> 03:58:27.960
[Guest]: that this is also a Muslim resistance.

03:58:27.960 --> 03:58:30.960
[Guest]: I didn't want to counter anybody on the stage

03:58:30.960 --> 03:58:33.960
[Guest]: as they tried to talk about other aspects

03:58:33.960 --> 03:58:37.960
[Guest]: because that would have been confrontational and counterproductive.

03:58:37.960 --> 03:58:40.960
[Guest]: But I also wanted to assert that

03:58:40.960 --> 03:58:46.960
[Guest]: this law is as unconstitutional as it is communal.

03:58:46.960 --> 03:58:51.960
[Guest]: And because it is communal, it is a law.

03:58:51.960 --> 03:58:54.960
[Guest]: It is not like they are being attacked because it is unconstitutional.

03:58:54.960 --> 03:58:56.960
[Guest]: It is communal and that is why it is being done.

03:58:56.960 --> 03:59:00.960
[Guest]: So I wanted to keep this in mind, so I was doing this as well.

03:59:00.960 --> 03:59:05.960
[Guest]: And often, I mean, in response to this,

03:59:05.960 --> 03:59:08.960
[Guest]: I mean, I changed a few things in this poem,

03:59:08.960 --> 03:59:09.960
[Guest]: I changed two or three lines.

03:59:09.960 --> 03:59:12.960
[Guest]: I find some weird things in the response.

03:59:12.960 --> 03:59:15.960
[Guest]: So since I have read this poem so many times,

03:59:15.960 --> 03:59:17.960
[Guest]: so for example, whenever I say this line,

03:59:17.960 --> 03:59:20.960
[Guest]: I have one month of Ramadan and I have done Ganga bath as well.

03:59:20.960 --> 03:59:22.960
[Guest]: There is always a clap.

03:59:22.960 --> 03:59:25.960
[Guest]: Now I wish to ask people why there is a clap.

03:59:25.960 --> 03:59:28.960
[Guest]: What if the person does not want to do Ganga bath,

03:59:28.960 --> 03:59:30.960
[Guest]: an Indian Muslim does not want to do Ganga bath?

03:59:30.960 --> 03:59:34.960
[Guest]: Is he any less Indian Muslim if he does not want to do Ganga bath?

03:59:34.960 --> 03:59:35.960
[Guest]: He is not.

03:59:35.960 --> 03:59:39.960
[Guest]: He could very happily be just not interested,

03:59:39.960 --> 03:59:40.960
[Guest]: like simply not interested.

03:59:40.960 --> 03:59:44.960
[Guest]: Like I am not interested in eating lobster.

03:59:44.960 --> 03:59:46.960
[Guest]: Am I against seafood?

03:59:46.960 --> 03:59:47.960
[Guest]: No.

03:59:47.960 --> 03:59:48.960
[Guest]: It could be anything, right?

03:59:48.960 --> 03:59:49.960
[Guest]: It is not that.

03:59:49.960 --> 03:59:51.960
[Guest]: Then there is another response,

03:59:51.960 --> 03:59:53.960
[Guest]: that no politician is in my control,

03:59:53.960 --> 03:59:54.960
[Guest]: I am not in any party's control.

03:59:54.960 --> 03:59:56.960
[Guest]: Why is there an applause to that?

03:59:56.960 --> 04:00:00.960
[Guest]: Why could I not want a politician of my own?

04:00:00.960 --> 04:00:03.960
[Guest]: Why could I not want a party of my own?

04:00:03.960 --> 04:00:05.960
[Guest]: Why could I not be political?

04:00:05.960 --> 04:00:09.960
[Guest]: Why could I not remain apolitical?

04:00:09.960 --> 04:00:12.960
[Guest]: Why could I not remove the apoliticalness

04:00:12.960 --> 04:00:16.960
[Guest]: that perhaps you desire or you expect from me

04:00:16.960 --> 04:00:18.960
[Guest]: so as to look less aggressive?

04:00:18.960 --> 04:00:23.960
[Guest]: Why would my political stance make me seem more aggressive?

04:00:23.960 --> 04:00:24.960
[Guest]: Is what I am trying to understand.

04:00:24.960 --> 04:00:26.960
[Guest]: Why would there be an applause to this?

04:00:26.960 --> 04:00:27.960
[Guest]: Right?

04:00:27.960 --> 04:00:29.960
[Guest]: When I am writing,

04:00:29.960 --> 04:00:30.960
[Guest]: I am an Indian Muslim,

04:00:30.960 --> 04:00:32.960
[Guest]: so I am talking about myself.

04:00:32.960 --> 04:00:33.960
[Guest]: Although I am, of course,

04:00:33.960 --> 04:00:34.960
[Guest]: metaphorizing,

04:00:34.960 --> 04:00:35.960
[Guest]: taking freedom somewhere,

04:00:35.960 --> 04:00:38.960
[Guest]: sometimes telling all types,

04:00:38.960 --> 04:00:43.960
[Guest]: but I am talking to my POV somewhere.

04:00:43.960 --> 04:00:45.960
[Guest]: So I should get a concession for that.

04:00:45.960 --> 04:00:47.960
[Guest]: Now, like I am saying,

04:00:47.960 --> 04:00:49.960
[Guest]: whenever I would come to the portions

04:00:49.960 --> 04:00:51.960
[Guest]: that I am a dome of Babri,

04:00:51.960 --> 04:00:53.960
[Guest]: I am a border between cities,

04:00:53.960 --> 04:00:56.960
[Guest]: I was born in Juggis,

04:00:56.960 --> 04:00:57.960
[Guest]: I was born in Juggis,

04:00:57.960 --> 04:00:59.960
[Guest]: I was born in a broken roof of a Madrasa.

04:00:59.960 --> 04:01:02.960
[Guest]: Why is there silence over there?

04:01:02.960 --> 04:01:06.960
[Guest]: Why do people start buggling?

04:01:06.960 --> 04:01:08.960
[Guest]: I have seen this physical response

04:01:08.960 --> 04:01:10.960
[Guest]: while reading this poem many times.

04:01:10.960 --> 04:01:12.960
[Guest]: Why do you feel embarrassed when this happens?

04:01:12.960 --> 04:01:14.960
[Guest]: Why do you feel uncomfortable

04:01:14.960 --> 04:01:17.960
[Guest]: sitting on your chair when I talk about this?

04:01:17.960 --> 04:01:20.960
[Guest]: So you should understand why this happens.

04:01:20.960 --> 04:01:21.960
[Guest]: Because in such a sweet,

04:01:21.960 --> 04:01:23.960
[Guest]: so-called sweet poem,

04:01:23.960 --> 04:01:26.960
[Guest]: I am suddenly giving you a hint,

04:01:26.960 --> 04:01:27.960
[Guest]: giving you a hint,

04:01:27.960 --> 04:01:30.960
[Guest]: so you are becoming uncomfortable.

04:01:30.960 --> 04:01:32.960
[Guest]: But then I suddenly say that

04:01:32.960 --> 04:01:33.960
[Guest]: I am 14 out of 100,

04:01:33.960 --> 04:01:35.960
[Guest]: but 14 is not less.

04:01:35.960 --> 04:01:36.960
[Guest]: I am in the top 100,

04:01:36.960 --> 04:01:37.960
[Guest]: I am in the top 100.

04:01:37.960 --> 04:01:40.960
[Guest]: So you clap again.

04:01:40.960 --> 04:01:45.960
[Guest]: As soon as I say that I am assimilating,

04:01:45.960 --> 04:01:46.960
[Guest]: you clap again.

04:01:46.960 --> 04:01:50.960
[Guest]: Is it necessary that I dissolve like sugar in milk

04:01:50.960 --> 04:01:52.960
[Guest]: that we learned in school?

04:01:52.960 --> 04:01:53.960
[Guest]: I don't want to dissolve.

04:01:53.960 --> 04:01:56.960
[Guest]: I can live like pebbles in a river.

04:01:56.960 --> 04:01:59.960
[Guest]: Are pebbles bad for a river?

04:01:59.960 --> 04:02:02.960
[Guest]: Is a stone bad for a river?

04:02:02.960 --> 04:02:05.960
[Guest]: Is it not necessary that I dissolve?

04:02:05.960 --> 04:02:06.960
[Guest]: So what is the problem?

04:02:06.960 --> 04:02:08.960
[Guest]: So when I ask this to people,

04:02:08.960 --> 04:02:11.960
[Guest]: they often don't have an answer.

04:02:11.960 --> 04:02:19.960
[Guest]: I think people consider this image to be steadfast,

04:02:19.960 --> 04:02:22.960
[Guest]: that one has to bathe in the Ganga.

04:02:22.960 --> 04:02:28.960
[Guest]: So I break all these notions by saying all these things.

04:02:28.960 --> 04:02:33.960
[Guest]: Apart from this, I guess the reaction responses to poetry.

04:02:33.960 --> 04:02:38.960
[Guest]: You would also see that I have not made my YouTube channel.

04:02:38.960 --> 04:02:40.960
[Guest]: I had a lot of success.

04:02:40.960 --> 04:02:42.960
[Guest]: I could have easily made my YouTube channel.

04:02:42.960 --> 04:02:43.960
[Unknown]: I could have become that.

04:02:43.960 --> 04:02:46.960
[Guest]: I could have also written 3-4 more poems on Muslim identity

04:02:46.960 --> 04:02:47.960
[Guest]: right after Hindustani Musliman.

04:02:47.960 --> 04:02:48.960
[Guest]: I never did that.

04:02:48.960 --> 04:02:53.960
[Guest]: I was offered many TEDx talks.

04:02:53.960 --> 04:02:54.960
[Guest]: I never did that.

04:02:54.960 --> 04:03:01.960
[Guest]: I was also offered an event where I had to advocate a TV serial

04:03:01.960 --> 04:03:03.960
[Guest]: which is on Indian Muslim families.

04:03:03.960 --> 04:03:07.960
[Guest]: And I had to read this poem and go for a promotion

04:03:07.960 --> 04:03:10.960
[Guest]: as if I am advocating this serial.

04:03:10.960 --> 04:03:13.960
[Guest]: But I didn't do that because I also understand that this is a poem.

04:03:13.960 --> 04:03:18.960
[Guest]: It does not make me some kind of a voice.

04:03:18.960 --> 04:03:25.960
[Guest]: Because I think my bio is also very strange that my share is 1 by 130 crores and so is yours.

04:03:25.960 --> 04:03:26.960
[Guest]: Yeah, I saw that.

04:03:26.960 --> 04:03:28.960
[Guest]: And that is what I think.

04:03:28.960 --> 04:03:33.960
[Guest]: So my share in Indian Muslims is only 1 by 120 crores, I guess.

04:03:33.960 --> 04:03:34.960
[Guest]: 1 by 18 crores.

04:03:34.960 --> 04:03:36.960
[Guest]: And so is everybody else's.

04:03:36.960 --> 04:03:39.960
[Guest]: You know why I like Hindustani Musliman so much

04:03:39.960 --> 04:03:41.960
[Guest]: and including those parts you mentioned

04:03:41.960 --> 04:03:44.960
[Unknown]: and including the parts which others are disturbed by

04:03:44.960 --> 04:03:47.960
[Amit Varma]: is for me, it's fighting essentialism.

04:03:47.960 --> 04:03:52.960
[Amit Varma]: And it's fighting essentialism because I just hate essentialism of all types.

04:03:52.960 --> 04:03:55.960
[Amit Varma]: Muslims are like this or Hindus are like this or blah blah blah.

04:03:55.960 --> 04:03:58.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, because I just feel we all contain multitudes.

04:03:58.960 --> 04:04:02.960
[Amit Varma]: We should celebrate that and not tie people down to identities or birth

04:04:02.960 --> 04:04:03.960
[Amit Varma]: or something they could not control.

04:04:03.960 --> 04:04:09.960
[Amit Varma]: And as a collective, it seems an expression that Muslims are everywhere doing everything.

04:04:09.960 --> 04:04:12.960
[Amit Varma]: And there is that possibility there.

04:04:12.960 --> 04:04:15.960
[Amit Varma]: And there is also agency there in the sense of we are interpreted

04:04:15.960 --> 04:04:18.960
[Amit Varma]: that I can do any of these things, not that I have to do all of them.

04:04:18.960 --> 04:04:21.960
[Amit Varma]: Like I have never done a Ganga asana and never went obviously.

04:04:21.960 --> 04:04:24.960
[Amit Varma]: Why is that even something desirable?

04:04:24.960 --> 04:04:30.960
[Amit Varma]: So it's not those individual things but that overall thing just makes me feel so good

04:04:30.960 --> 04:04:35.960
[Amit Varma]: and it also sort of brings into focus what I love about this country

04:04:35.960 --> 04:04:38.960
[Amit Varma]: and what is worth fighting for all of us.

04:04:38.960 --> 04:04:41.960
[Amit Varma]: So I think you're being a little hard on yourself,

04:04:41.960 --> 04:04:44.960
[Amit Varma]: perhaps on many of the people who like it

04:04:44.960 --> 04:04:45.960
[Guest]: because I suspect many people.

04:04:45.960 --> 04:04:46.960
[Guest]: No, no, I am not.

04:04:46.960 --> 04:04:49.960
[Guest]: So like I said earlier, I am not dissociating with it.

04:04:49.960 --> 04:04:51.960
[Guest]: I am not criticizing it.

04:04:51.960 --> 04:04:54.960
[Guest]: I am not saying that I don't like the poem anymore.

04:04:54.960 --> 04:04:55.960
[Guest]: I own it completely.

04:04:55.960 --> 04:05:00.960
[Guest]: I own it with all the humility that all the appreciation that I get

04:05:00.960 --> 04:05:03.960
[Guest]: and all the criticism that I may get for it.

04:05:03.960 --> 04:05:07.960
[Guest]: But I don't dissociate with it and I also understand its importance.

04:05:07.960 --> 04:05:09.960
[Guest]: You are reading that poem even today.

04:05:09.960 --> 04:05:14.960
[Guest]: So I am appealing to you because what I am writing is that

04:05:14.960 --> 04:05:16.960
[Guest]: a society cannot have only one kind of people.

04:05:16.960 --> 04:05:22.960
[Guest]: A society has a lot of parameters based on which people live on different scales

04:05:22.960 --> 04:05:26.960
[Guest]: and they live on different points in different axis.

04:05:26.960 --> 04:05:29.960
[Guest]: And sometimes it becomes a 3D axis in 3-4 dimensions.

04:05:29.960 --> 04:05:34.960
[Guest]: One is religion, one is education, one is geography, one is language,

04:05:34.960 --> 04:05:41.960
[Guest]: one is food habits, one is economic location, one is caste location, one is sect location.

04:05:41.960 --> 04:05:48.960
[Guest]: There are so many parameters in Muslims that you cannot be one.

04:05:48.960 --> 04:05:51.960
[Guest]: And this fact will stand true for the next 25 years.

04:05:51.960 --> 04:05:54.960
[Guest]: It is very difficult to disagree with that thing

04:05:54.960 --> 04:06:05.960
[Guest]: because its description, what I am saying, the things and the ironies that are available

04:06:05.960 --> 04:06:14.960
[Guest]: when you are going from conservative and modern to less religious,

04:06:14.960 --> 04:06:20.960
[Guest]: you feel those ironies both inside and outside.

04:06:20.960 --> 04:06:23.960
[Guest]: So this is my opinion.

04:06:23.960 --> 04:06:25.960
[Guest]: It's not just being hard.

04:06:25.960 --> 04:06:30.960
[Guest]: I also feel a bit betrayed actually

04:06:30.960 --> 04:06:35.960
[Guest]: because I tried very hard with this poem to talk to people.

04:06:35.960 --> 04:06:39.960
[Guest]: But we still came here where we are.

04:06:39.960 --> 04:06:43.960
[Guest]: I mean at that point in 2016 and 2017,

04:06:43.960 --> 04:06:50.960
[Guest]: I was more of a cautionary, polite guy trying to tell people that

04:06:50.960 --> 04:06:56.960
[Guest]: hey, this is not how you should be otherizing or demonizing a community.

04:06:56.960 --> 04:06:58.960
[Guest]: I was still that guy.

04:06:58.960 --> 04:07:00.960
[Guest]: Now I think that access is lost.

04:07:00.960 --> 04:07:03.960
[Guest]: I am still that guy who wants to say the same things again.

04:07:03.960 --> 04:07:10.960
[Guest]: But I think now that access is lost, people may not listen.

04:07:10.960 --> 04:07:13.960
[Guest]: And I am also a bit angered now.

04:07:13.960 --> 04:07:16.960
[Guest]: Now I am like, how humiliated you guys are.

04:07:16.960 --> 04:07:18.960
[Guest]: I used to say no earlier as well.

04:07:18.960 --> 04:07:22.960
[Amit Varma]: To mark both a positive and a negative note to that,

04:07:22.960 --> 04:07:27.960
[Amit Varma]: I think that the game was already lost by then

04:07:27.960 --> 04:07:29.960
[Amit Varma]: in the sense that society is what it is.

04:07:29.960 --> 04:07:33.960
[Amit Varma]: And one viral poem was not going to change that.

04:07:33.960 --> 04:07:34.960
[Amit Varma]: That's the negative view.

04:07:34.960 --> 04:07:40.960
[Amit Varma]: But the positive view is that the fact that so many people,

04:07:40.960 --> 04:07:44.960
[Amit Varma]: and again relative to society out there, it may not be many people,

04:07:44.960 --> 04:07:46.960
[Amit Varma]: but in absolute numbers still,

04:07:46.960 --> 04:07:49.960
[Amit Varma]: if hundreds of thousands of people or I don't know how many million views it has,

04:07:49.960 --> 04:07:54.960
[Amit Varma]: but if all those people are appreciating it and agreeing with it and all of that,

04:07:54.960 --> 04:07:57.960
[Amit Varma]: it still means something. It is there.

04:07:57.960 --> 04:08:00.960
[Amit Varma]: One is not completely alone in the world.

04:08:00.960 --> 04:08:05.960
[Amit Varma]: I think what artists really do in a sense is play the long game.

04:08:05.960 --> 04:08:07.960
[Amit Varma]: You are playing the long game.

04:08:07.960 --> 04:08:09.960
[Amit Varma]: Maybe now you can't change anything.

04:08:09.960 --> 04:08:12.960
[Amit Varma]: Maybe now it doesn't make any difference.

04:08:12.960 --> 04:08:17.960
[Guest]: 30 years later, kids listening to that, their whole worldview will be shaped.

04:08:17.960 --> 04:08:20.960
[Guest]: See, the thing is I am making a very basic argument

04:08:20.960 --> 04:08:23.960
[Guest]: that Indian Muslims are divided into many things.

04:08:23.960 --> 04:08:24.960
[Guest]: Yeah.

04:08:24.960 --> 04:08:29.960
[Guest]: And all of them are equally valid and all of them are equally good

04:08:29.960 --> 04:08:31.960
[Guest]: and all of them are equally legit.

04:08:31.960 --> 04:08:35.960
[Guest]: And I am saying it in a very reasonable way.

04:08:35.960 --> 04:08:39.960
[Guest]: I am not saying it like you guys improve.

04:08:39.960 --> 04:08:42.960
[Amit Varma]: I am saying, we are like this. I am like this.

04:08:42.960 --> 04:08:44.960
[Amit Varma]: No, and it's said so beautifully.

04:08:44.960 --> 04:08:47.960
[Amit Varma]: Like you said, it isn't that you were saying something new or whatever.

04:08:47.960 --> 04:08:49.960
[Amit Varma]: If you just say it in normal words, it's almost banal.

04:08:49.960 --> 04:08:51.960
[Amit Varma]: But the beautiful way in which you say it,

04:08:51.960 --> 04:08:57.960
[Amit Varma]: the fact that people feel that emotional connection and that's what art does, right?

04:08:57.960 --> 04:08:58.960
[Guest]: I mean, ultimately.

04:08:58.960 --> 04:09:00.960
[Guest]: Yeah, I mean, it's very strange.

04:09:00.960 --> 04:09:02.960
[Guest]: I also think about it many times.

04:09:02.960 --> 04:09:03.960
[Guest]: Where does it start from?

04:09:03.960 --> 04:09:05.960
[Guest]: It starts with shame.

04:09:05.960 --> 04:09:06.960
[Guest]: It starts with guilt.

04:09:06.960 --> 04:09:09.960
[Guest]: I wrote it while smoking a cigarette on the road.

04:09:09.960 --> 04:09:11.960
[Guest]: I mean, it's a very strange construction.

04:09:11.960 --> 04:09:12.960
[Guest]: I don't even know how I did it.

04:09:12.960 --> 04:09:14.960
[Guest]: I have no idea how I wrote it.

04:09:14.960 --> 04:09:16.960
[Guest]: But I mean, yes.

04:09:16.960 --> 04:09:18.960
[Guest]: But those lines always remained in my mind.

04:09:18.960 --> 04:09:21.960
[Guest]: I wrote it in Bhutan sometime in 2015.

04:09:21.960 --> 04:09:23.960
[Guest]: I wrote it while going to Bhutan.

04:09:23.960 --> 04:09:25.960
[Guest]: When I was going to Bhutan from Kolkata.

04:09:25.960 --> 04:09:27.960
[Guest]: And that poem was lost from me.

04:09:27.960 --> 04:09:29.960
[Guest]: But I remembered this line.

04:09:29.960 --> 04:09:30.960
[Guest]: While smoking a cigarette on the road,

04:09:30.960 --> 04:09:31.960
[Guest]: when I heard the Azad,

04:09:31.960 --> 04:09:32.960
[Guest]: I remembered what time it is.

04:09:32.960 --> 04:09:33.960
[Guest]: And then this came to my mind.

04:09:33.960 --> 04:09:35.960
[Guest]: What kind of a Muslim am I?

04:09:35.960 --> 04:09:38.960
[Guest]: So this thought and this came to my mind

04:09:38.960 --> 04:09:39.960
[Guest]: because I used to smoke a cigarette

04:09:39.960 --> 04:09:41.960
[Guest]: and the Azad used to come.

04:09:41.960 --> 04:09:42.960
[Guest]: And I used to think,

04:09:42.960 --> 04:09:45.960
[Guest]: why do I smoke at the wrong time?

04:09:45.960 --> 04:09:47.960
[Guest]: So either I used to put it off or I used to stop.

04:09:47.960 --> 04:09:50.960
[Guest]: Now, I don't even know why I used to stop.

04:09:50.960 --> 04:09:51.960
[Guest]: But this is just a condition

04:09:51.960 --> 04:09:52.960
[Guest]: that I can't do this.

04:09:52.960 --> 04:09:54.960
[Guest]: This is wrong.

04:09:54.960 --> 04:09:56.960
[Guest]: So this, anyway.

04:09:56.960 --> 04:09:58.960
[Guest]: So it started from there

04:09:58.960 --> 04:10:00.960
[Guest]: and then it happened to me again.

04:10:00.960 --> 04:10:01.960
[Guest]: And at that time,

04:10:01.960 --> 04:10:03.960
[Guest]: at the end of 2017-2016,

04:10:03.960 --> 04:10:04.960
[Guest]: I mean, all this was going on.

04:10:04.960 --> 04:10:07.960
[Guest]: So I think it just colluded with that.

04:10:07.960 --> 04:10:09.960
[Guest]: On one hand,

04:10:09.960 --> 04:10:11.960
[Guest]: there was an internal dialogue.

04:10:13.960 --> 04:10:15.960
[Guest]: I mean, how much of a Muslim I am?

04:10:15.960 --> 04:10:16.960
[Guest]: What kind of a Muslim I am?

04:10:16.960 --> 04:10:18.960
[Guest]: And I think then I realized that

04:10:18.960 --> 04:10:20.960
[Guest]: maybe the multitudes that I contain

04:10:20.960 --> 04:10:22.960
[Guest]: are also reflective of the multitudes

04:10:22.960 --> 04:10:24.960
[Guest]: that the land in which I am born contains.

04:10:24.960 --> 04:10:27.960
[Unknown]: Is the answer that I figured.

04:10:27.960 --> 04:10:29.960
[Guest]: Now, it may not.

04:10:29.960 --> 04:10:34.960
[Guest]: But yes, even Imtiaz Dharkar,

04:10:34.960 --> 04:10:37.960
[Guest]: who is a very known poet in the UK

04:10:37.960 --> 04:10:39.960
[Guest]: and Pakistan-based poet,

04:10:39.960 --> 04:10:41.960
[Guest]: she also took my interview

04:10:41.960 --> 04:10:43.960
[Guest]: and she was so...

04:10:43.960 --> 04:10:46.960
[Guest]: I was surprised that she was able to relate to it

04:10:46.960 --> 04:10:48.960
[Guest]: so much as well.

04:10:48.960 --> 04:10:50.960
[Guest]: That I was not able to believe.

04:10:50.960 --> 04:10:52.960
[Guest]: First of all, she is a very...

04:10:52.960 --> 04:10:55.960
[Guest]: I mean, in terms of stature,

04:10:55.960 --> 04:10:57.960
[Guest]: she is a top-notch poet.

04:10:57.960 --> 04:10:59.960
[Guest]: So I am nothing in front of her.

04:10:59.960 --> 04:11:02.960
[Guest]: And the way she had complimented

04:11:02.960 --> 04:11:04.960
[Guest]: and the kind of things she was saying,

04:11:04.960 --> 04:11:05.960
[Guest]: that I was relating so much,

04:11:05.960 --> 04:11:06.960
[Guest]: in every line.

04:11:06.960 --> 04:11:07.960
[Guest]: And I was like,

04:11:07.960 --> 04:11:09.960
[Guest]: Madam, you are so...

04:11:09.960 --> 04:11:10.960
[Guest]: So I understood that,

04:11:10.960 --> 04:11:12.960
[Guest]: okay, it has worked somewhere.

04:11:12.960 --> 04:11:15.960
[Guest]: I still don't fully understand anything.

04:11:15.960 --> 04:11:17.960
[Guest]: Basically, what I do is,

04:11:19.960 --> 04:11:22.960
[Guest]: whatever I feel is good or bad,

04:11:22.960 --> 04:11:23.960
[Guest]: or whatever people tell me,

04:11:23.960 --> 04:11:25.960
[Guest]: I regurgitate it.

04:11:25.960 --> 04:11:27.960
[Guest]: But the truth is, I don't know.

04:11:27.960 --> 04:11:29.960
[Guest]: And I am not sure if I will ever be able

04:11:29.960 --> 04:11:31.960
[Amit Varma]: to understand fully also.

04:11:31.960 --> 04:11:33.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, and the other thing,

04:11:33.960 --> 04:11:36.960
[Amit Varma]: and I will segue with this to my next question.

04:11:36.960 --> 04:11:38.960
[Amit Varma]: You know, the other thing I liked about

04:11:38.960 --> 04:11:39.960
[Amit Varma]: Hindustani Musalma also is,

04:11:39.960 --> 04:11:41.960
[Amit Varma]: just the rhythm of it,

04:11:41.960 --> 04:11:42.960
[Amit Varma]: the sound of it,

04:11:42.960 --> 04:11:43.960
[Amit Varma]: it sounds so beautiful.

04:11:43.960 --> 04:11:46.960
[Amit Varma]: And it is also a reminder of how

04:11:46.960 --> 04:11:48.960
[Amit Varma]: languages are so fundamentally different,

04:11:48.960 --> 04:11:50.960
[Amit Varma]: that in English you wouldn't get

04:11:50.960 --> 04:11:51.960
[Amit Varma]: this kind of rhythm,

04:11:51.960 --> 04:11:52.960
[Amit Varma]: this kind of easy movement.

04:11:52.960 --> 04:11:53.960
[Amit Varma]: You will have your own rhythms

04:11:53.960 --> 04:11:55.960
[Amit Varma]: and your own ways of doing things.

04:11:55.960 --> 04:11:57.960
[Amit Varma]: But this sort of musicality

04:11:57.960 --> 04:12:00.960
[Amit Varma]: is something that really appealed to me.

04:12:00.960 --> 04:12:01.960
[Amit Varma]: So my question is this,

04:12:01.960 --> 04:12:02.960
[Amit Varma]: that after this,

04:12:02.960 --> 04:12:05.960
[Amit Varma]: you went on to writing lyrics.

04:12:05.960 --> 04:12:07.960
[Amit Varma]: It strikes me that there is a challenge there,

04:12:07.960 --> 04:12:09.960
[Amit Varma]: which is that there is,

04:12:09.960 --> 04:12:10.960
[Amit Varma]: when you are writing poetry,

04:12:10.960 --> 04:12:12.960
[Amit Varma]: there is an inherent music in it already.

04:12:12.960 --> 04:12:14.960
[Amit Varma]: And then when you are writing lyrics,

04:12:14.960 --> 04:12:16.960
[Amit Varma]: you are given music from outside,

04:12:16.960 --> 04:12:18.960
[Amit Varma]: either before or after you are writing.

04:12:18.960 --> 04:12:20.960
[Amit Varma]: And you have to bring the two together

04:12:20.960 --> 04:12:22.960
[Amit Varma]: to make them work together and all of that.

04:12:22.960 --> 04:12:24.960
[Amit Varma]: So what was that process like?

04:12:24.960 --> 04:12:28.960
[Amit Varma]: How did you get into lyric writing?

04:12:28.960 --> 04:12:29.960
[Amit Varma]: How did you feel that this is

04:12:29.960 --> 04:12:31.960
[Amit Varma]: the kind of thing I would like to do?

04:12:31.960 --> 04:12:33.960
[Amit Varma]: And what were the early challenges you faced

04:12:33.960 --> 04:12:34.960
[Amit Varma]: when you were doing it before?

04:12:34.960 --> 04:12:36.960
[Guest]: Oh yeah, so actually,

04:12:36.960 --> 04:12:39.960
[Guest]: I had written songs before Hindustani Musalman.

04:12:39.960 --> 04:12:41.960
[Guest]: The songs of Kareeb Kareeb Singhal and Mukkabad

04:12:41.960 --> 04:12:44.960
[Guest]: were written before Hindustani Musalman.

04:12:44.960 --> 04:12:46.960
[Guest]: A lot of people think

04:12:46.960 --> 04:12:48.960
[Guest]: that I got those songs because of that,

04:12:48.960 --> 04:12:49.960
[Guest]: but it's not like that.

04:12:49.960 --> 04:12:50.960
[Guest]: They were released later.

04:12:50.960 --> 04:12:54.960
[Guest]: But the challenges that I...

04:12:54.960 --> 04:12:55.960
[Guest]: Yeah, but of course,

04:12:55.960 --> 04:12:56.960
[Guest]: I was doing poetry before that,

04:12:56.960 --> 04:12:58.960
[Guest]: I was doing performance before that.

04:12:58.960 --> 04:13:01.960
[Guest]: I think the biggest challenge was that

04:13:01.960 --> 04:13:03.960
[Guest]: what happens in poetry is that

04:13:03.960 --> 04:13:05.960
[Guest]: I have complete control.

04:13:05.960 --> 04:13:07.960
[Guest]: What topic will I speak on?

04:13:07.960 --> 04:13:09.960
[Guest]: What language will I speak in?

04:13:09.960 --> 04:13:11.960
[Guest]: What meter will I take?

04:13:11.960 --> 04:13:14.960
[Guest]: What kind of words will I choose?

04:13:14.960 --> 04:13:17.960
[Guest]: And who will I take feedback from?

04:13:17.960 --> 04:13:18.960
[Guest]: And whose feedback will I accept?

04:13:18.960 --> 04:13:20.960
[Guest]: And who will I not accept?

04:13:20.960 --> 04:13:21.960
[Guest]: It's all in my hands.

04:13:21.960 --> 04:13:24.960
[Guest]: Everything is mine in that.

04:13:24.960 --> 04:13:27.960
[Guest]: Secondly, in songs,

04:13:27.960 --> 04:13:29.960
[Guest]: except for the words,

04:13:29.960 --> 04:13:31.960
[Guest]: nothing is mine.

04:13:31.960 --> 04:13:33.960
[Guest]: And those words also have a lot of interference

04:13:33.960 --> 04:13:35.960
[Guest]: of other people.

04:13:35.960 --> 04:13:36.960
[Guest]: A brief is given,

04:13:36.960 --> 04:13:38.960
[Guest]: the character's language is there,

04:13:38.960 --> 04:13:40.960
[Guest]: then there is music,

04:13:40.960 --> 04:13:42.960
[Guest]: then there is a situation

04:13:42.960 --> 04:13:43.960
[Guest]: that what is the character doing

04:13:43.960 --> 04:13:45.960
[Guest]: at that time in that era?

04:13:45.960 --> 04:13:49.960
[Guest]: Then sometimes there can be a dialect in it.

04:13:49.960 --> 04:13:51.960
[Guest]: So,

04:13:51.960 --> 04:13:54.960
[Guest]: all these things happen.

04:13:54.960 --> 04:13:57.960
[Guest]: Even in that, I have to try to be...

04:13:57.960 --> 04:13:59.960
[Guest]: At least I try to be a little poetic.

04:13:59.960 --> 04:14:01.960
[Guest]: I try to bring in an angle

04:14:01.960 --> 04:14:04.960
[Guest]: which I want to talk about as well.

04:14:04.960 --> 04:14:07.960
[Guest]: Sometimes it works,

04:14:07.960 --> 04:14:09.960
[Guest]: sometimes it does not work.

04:14:09.960 --> 04:14:12.960
[Guest]: Sometimes directors are fine with me doing that,

04:14:12.960 --> 04:14:14.960
[Guest]: sometimes directors don't like it.

04:14:14.960 --> 04:14:17.960
[Guest]: But thankfully, I have worked with more who like it.

04:14:17.960 --> 04:14:19.960
[Guest]: So that has been advantageous for me.

04:14:19.960 --> 04:14:22.960
[Guest]: Then there is also

04:14:22.960 --> 04:14:23.960
[Guest]: the musicality,

04:14:23.960 --> 04:14:25.960
[Guest]: the metrical musicality

04:14:25.960 --> 04:14:28.960
[Guest]: or the rhythmic quality of the poem is set by me.

04:14:28.960 --> 04:14:29.960
[Guest]: I decide it.

04:14:29.960 --> 04:14:31.960
[Guest]: But in music, generally,

04:14:31.960 --> 04:14:34.960
[Guest]: either I have to make it short,

04:14:34.960 --> 04:14:36.960
[Guest]: like the metrical has to be slightly short

04:14:36.960 --> 04:14:40.960
[Guest]: or in that 4x4 pattern which often works.

04:14:40.960 --> 04:14:44.960
[Guest]: So, there is a sense of limitation over there.

04:14:44.960 --> 04:14:46.960
[Guest]: And

04:14:46.960 --> 04:14:49.960
[Guest]: then there is a certain phonetic quality that

04:14:49.960 --> 04:14:52.960
[Guest]: I can keep in my poem

04:14:52.960 --> 04:14:53.960
[Guest]: as per my own wishes.

04:14:53.960 --> 04:14:55.960
[Guest]: But then the tune

04:14:55.960 --> 04:14:58.960
[Guest]: in a lot of ways dictates the phonetic quality.

04:14:58.960 --> 04:14:59.960
[Guest]: Can you illustrate that?

04:14:59.960 --> 04:15:01.960
[Guest]: Like,

04:15:01.960 --> 04:15:04.960
[Guest]: if a tune is going something like

04:15:04.960 --> 04:15:10.960
[Unknown]: da-ra-ri-ra-ra-ri-ra

04:15:10.960 --> 04:15:14.960
[Guest]: Now, I cannot write

04:15:14.960 --> 04:15:18.960
[Guest]: something like

04:15:18.960 --> 04:15:24.960
[Guest]: khata khat se chal raha hai prachand

04:15:24.960 --> 04:15:26.960
[Guest]: bhala

04:15:26.960 --> 04:15:28.960
[Guest]: You know,

04:15:28.960 --> 04:15:30.960
[Unknown]: khata khat prachand

04:15:30.960 --> 04:15:32.960
[Unknown]: it's not going to sound

04:15:32.960 --> 04:15:35.960
[Unknown]: whatever rubbish I sang.

04:15:35.960 --> 04:15:37.960
[Guest]: I will have to use short phonetic

04:15:37.960 --> 04:15:38.960
[Guest]: phonetics ki

04:15:38.960 --> 04:15:42.960
[Unknown]: hole se silhane me

04:15:42.960 --> 04:15:44.960
[Guest]: rakhe kar ye yaade

04:15:44.960 --> 04:15:46.960
[Guest]: It's soft.

04:15:46.960 --> 04:15:48.960
[Guest]: So,

04:15:48.960 --> 04:15:49.960
[Guest]: it's

04:15:49.960 --> 04:15:51.960
[Guest]: like I don't know how to explain it.

04:15:51.960 --> 04:15:54.960
[Guest]: But each phonetic has a feel.

04:15:54.960 --> 04:15:56.960
[Unknown]: It flows like the music.

04:15:56.960 --> 04:15:58.960
[Amit Varma]: In my writing class, I

04:15:58.960 --> 04:15:59.960
[Amit Varma]: speak about how Shakespeare used language

04:15:59.960 --> 04:16:01.960
[Unknown]: and I speak about soft and hard sounds

04:16:01.960 --> 04:16:03.960
[Unknown]: and how poets and

04:16:03.960 --> 04:16:05.960
[Amit Varma]: songwriters kind of use them.

04:16:05.960 --> 04:16:07.960
[Amit Varma]: I'm going to snip this and make everyone

04:16:07.960 --> 04:16:09.960
[Amit Varma]: listen to this because it's such a beautiful

04:16:09.960 --> 04:16:11.960
[Guest]: illustration of exactly that.

04:16:11.960 --> 04:16:13.960
[Guest]: Soft sounds are necessary.

04:16:13.960 --> 04:16:15.960
[Guest]: That's why

04:16:15.960 --> 04:16:17.960
[Guest]: the phonetic identity

04:16:17.960 --> 04:16:19.960
[Guest]: is there.

04:16:19.960 --> 04:16:21.960
[Guest]: Like, ta sounds weird.

04:16:21.960 --> 04:16:23.960
[Guest]: But then there are some ironies also.

04:16:23.960 --> 04:16:25.960
[Guest]: Like, Shelly ji has written a song

04:16:25.960 --> 04:16:27.960
[Guest]: and

04:16:27.960 --> 04:16:29.960
[Guest]: I forgot the composer's name.

04:16:29.960 --> 04:16:31.960
[Guest]: He's a very good composer.

04:16:31.960 --> 04:16:33.960
[Guest]: It's Clinton sir who composed

04:16:33.960 --> 04:16:35.960
[Guest]: Dug Dugi Dug.

04:16:35.960 --> 04:16:37.960
[Guest]: It's very weird. He has a song called Dug Dugi Dug.

04:16:37.960 --> 04:16:39.960
[Guest]: You'll feel like Dug Dugi Dug

04:16:39.960 --> 04:16:41.960
[Guest]: is a hard phonetic.

04:16:41.960 --> 04:16:43.960
[Guest]: But the composition is very soft.

04:16:43.960 --> 04:16:45.960
[Guest]: So, it's based on craft.

04:16:45.960 --> 04:16:47.960
[Guest]: Then you're playing with the rules.

04:16:47.960 --> 04:16:49.960
[Guest]: But generally, you can't do this.

04:16:49.960 --> 04:16:51.960
[Amit Varma]: You can play with the rules once you know the rules.

04:16:51.960 --> 04:16:53.960
[Guest]: But you can't do random.

04:16:53.960 --> 04:16:55.960
[Guest]: So, that's one thing.

04:16:55.960 --> 04:16:57.960
[Guest]: The second thing is,

04:16:57.960 --> 04:16:59.960
[Guest]: I had some difficulties.

04:16:59.960 --> 04:17:01.960
[Guest]: I had written 4-5 drafts

04:17:01.960 --> 04:17:03.960
[Guest]: for my first single.

04:17:03.960 --> 04:17:05.960
[Guest]: I was going very poetic.

04:17:05.960 --> 04:17:07.960
[Guest]: So, Tanuja was...

04:17:07.960 --> 04:17:09.960
[Guest]: Actually, Tanuja Chandra

04:17:09.960 --> 04:17:11.960
[Guest]: is a person who can be credited

04:17:11.960 --> 04:17:13.960
[Guest]: for teaching me how to write lyrics.

04:17:13.960 --> 04:17:15.960
[Guest]: Because, even though she's a director

04:17:15.960 --> 04:17:17.960
[Guest]: and not a lyricist herself,

04:17:17.960 --> 04:17:19.960
[Guest]: but she has worked with Anand Bakshi and Nida Fazli

04:17:19.960 --> 04:17:21.960
[Guest]: and such great lyricists.

04:17:21.960 --> 04:17:23.960
[Guest]: So, she was able to

04:17:23.960 --> 04:17:25.960
[Guest]: teach me that, first of all,

04:17:25.960 --> 04:17:27.960
[Guest]: you have to write simple.

04:17:27.960 --> 04:17:29.960
[Guest]: Don't show off.

04:17:29.960 --> 04:17:31.960
[Guest]: Don't show off that you know a lot of poetry.

04:17:31.960 --> 04:17:33.960
[Guest]: Be simple.

04:17:33.960 --> 04:17:35.960
[Guest]: Say things in a simple way.

04:17:35.960 --> 04:17:37.960
[Guest]: Then,

04:17:37.960 --> 04:17:39.960
[Guest]: say things in a direct way.

04:17:39.960 --> 04:17:41.960
[Guest]: Don't...

04:17:41.960 --> 04:17:43.960
[Guest]: People are listening to music.

04:17:43.960 --> 04:17:45.960
[Guest]: They will get confused in your sentences.

04:17:45.960 --> 04:17:47.960
[Guest]: If you're going to write convoluted sentences.

04:17:47.960 --> 04:17:49.960
[Guest]: Those convoluted sentences

04:17:49.960 --> 04:17:51.960
[Guest]: work in poetry.

04:17:51.960 --> 04:17:53.960
[Guest]: But they do not work in songs.

04:17:53.960 --> 04:17:55.960
[Guest]: Then,

04:17:55.960 --> 04:17:57.960
[Guest]: after 3-4 drafts, I finished a song called Tanha Begum.

04:17:57.960 --> 04:17:59.960
[Guest]: And then came a song

04:17:59.960 --> 04:18:01.960
[Guest]: which had 4

04:18:01.960 --> 04:18:03.960
[Guest]: different briefs, eventually,

04:18:03.960 --> 04:18:05.960
[Guest]: on a single composition.

04:18:05.960 --> 04:18:07.960
[Guest]: And I ended up writing some 40 drafts for it.

04:18:07.960 --> 04:18:09.960
[Guest]: Wow!

04:18:09.960 --> 04:18:11.960
[Guest]: Because,

04:18:11.960 --> 04:18:13.960
[Guest]: the brief changed 3 times

04:18:13.960 --> 04:18:15.960
[Guest]: and the 4th brief was eventually taken.

04:18:15.960 --> 04:18:17.960
[Guest]: And for every draft,

04:18:17.960 --> 04:18:19.960
[Guest]: I had written 6 or 7 drafts.

04:18:19.960 --> 04:18:21.960
[Guest]: Every brief, I had written 6 or 7 drafts.

04:18:21.960 --> 04:18:23.960
[Guest]: So, I ended up writing around

04:18:23.960 --> 04:18:25.960
[Guest]: 35-40 drafts of it.

04:18:25.960 --> 04:18:27.960
[Guest]: And, that I think,

04:18:27.960 --> 04:18:29.960
[Guest]: that completely

04:18:29.960 --> 04:18:31.960
[Guest]: taught me one thing that

04:18:31.960 --> 04:18:33.960
[Guest]: I do not need to fear rewriting.

04:18:33.960 --> 04:18:35.960
[Guest]: I used to be scared

04:18:35.960 --> 04:18:37.960
[Guest]: to death of rewriting.

04:18:37.960 --> 04:18:39.960
[Guest]: I used to be

04:18:39.960 --> 04:18:41.960
[Guest]: petrified of rewriting.

04:18:41.960 --> 04:18:43.960
[Guest]: Rewriting...

04:18:43.960 --> 04:18:45.960
[Guest]: If someone asked me to change a line,

04:18:45.960 --> 04:18:47.960
[Guest]: my BP used to rise.

04:18:47.960 --> 04:18:49.960
[Guest]: Not actual BP,

04:18:49.960 --> 04:18:51.960
[Guest]: I used to die of anxiety.

04:18:51.960 --> 04:18:53.960
[Guest]: And I used to think,

04:18:53.960 --> 04:18:55.960
[Guest]: how will I change a line now?

04:18:55.960 --> 04:18:57.960
[Guest]: But that song taught me

04:18:57.960 --> 04:18:59.960
[Guest]: how to not get rattled

04:18:59.960 --> 04:19:01.960
[Guest]: when somebody asks you to change a line.

04:19:01.960 --> 04:19:03.960
[Guest]: And to be more

04:19:03.960 --> 04:19:05.960
[Guest]: free with the director

04:19:05.960 --> 04:19:07.960
[Guest]: and the music director that

04:19:07.960 --> 04:19:09.960
[Guest]: it's okay, let's try this.

04:19:09.960 --> 04:19:11.960
[Guest]: Okay, let's do this.

04:19:11.960 --> 04:19:13.960
[Guest]: It's not working? Okay, let me try this.

04:19:13.960 --> 04:19:15.960
[Guest]: If there's something working and I know it's good,

04:19:15.960 --> 04:19:17.960
[Guest]: then I will probably push.

04:19:17.960 --> 04:19:19.960
[Guest]: And, generally, they respect

04:19:19.960 --> 04:19:21.960
[Guest]: my opinion and they generally take it.

04:19:21.960 --> 04:19:23.960
[Guest]: But, if something,

04:19:23.960 --> 04:19:25.960
[Guest]: even if I like something, then I have to

04:19:25.960 --> 04:19:27.960
[Guest]: be ready to kill it.

04:19:27.960 --> 04:19:29.960
[Guest]: Kill your darling type.

04:19:29.960 --> 04:19:31.960
[Guest]: So,

04:19:31.960 --> 04:19:33.960
[Guest]: if there's a beloved line,

04:19:33.960 --> 04:19:35.960
[Guest]: if a director or a music director

04:19:35.960 --> 04:19:37.960
[Guest]: strangles it, then I learned

04:19:37.960 --> 04:19:39.960
[Guest]: not to mourn his death.

04:19:39.960 --> 04:19:41.960
[Guest]: But then, the result that

04:19:41.960 --> 04:19:43.960
[Guest]: came out is that

04:19:43.960 --> 04:19:45.960
[Guest]: Tanuja was absolutely correct.

04:19:45.960 --> 04:19:47.960
[Guest]: She managed to teach me.

04:19:47.960 --> 04:19:49.960
[Guest]: She managed to convince me

04:19:49.960 --> 04:19:51.960
[Guest]: that my approach towards writing

04:19:51.960 --> 04:19:53.960
[Guest]: needed to be improved, which was

04:19:53.960 --> 04:19:55.960
[Guest]: not be so rigid.

04:19:55.960 --> 04:19:57.960
[Guest]: Be flexible.

04:19:57.960 --> 04:19:59.960
[Guest]: And I became

04:19:59.960 --> 04:20:01.960
[Guest]: very flexible.

04:20:01.960 --> 04:20:03.960
[Guest]: Now, I feel comfortable.

04:20:03.960 --> 04:20:05.960
[Guest]: I don't get rattled by that.

04:20:05.960 --> 04:20:07.960
[Guest]: Then,

04:20:07.960 --> 04:20:09.960
[Guest]: all that learning,

04:20:09.960 --> 04:20:11.960
[Guest]: I took

04:20:11.960 --> 04:20:13.960
[Guest]: and put it into Mukkabwaaz.

04:20:13.960 --> 04:20:15.960
[Guest]: And, Mukkabwaaz

04:20:15.960 --> 04:20:17.960
[Guest]: was up my

04:20:17.960 --> 04:20:19.960
[Guest]: attitude alley.

04:20:19.960 --> 04:20:21.960
[Guest]: But, it was not at all

04:20:21.960 --> 04:20:23.960
[Guest]: up my alley in terms of the language

04:20:23.960 --> 04:20:25.960
[Guest]: because it was UP Hindi.

04:20:25.960 --> 04:20:27.960
[Guest]: And, I am from MP.

04:20:27.960 --> 04:20:29.960
[Guest]: So, I had to learn.

04:20:29.960 --> 04:20:31.960
[Guest]: I had to understand the dialect.

04:20:31.960 --> 04:20:33.960
[Guest]: And, that I did by basically

04:20:33.960 --> 04:20:35.960
[Guest]: talking to a lot of people from UP.

04:20:35.960 --> 04:20:37.960
[Guest]: I was living at Muhammad Ali.

04:20:37.960 --> 04:20:39.960
[Guest]: I used to live in Chal at that time.

04:20:39.960 --> 04:20:41.960
[Guest]: So, I used to go down and talk to everyone.

04:20:41.960 --> 04:20:43.960
[Guest]: Press people,

04:20:43.960 --> 04:20:45.960
[Guest]: tea people,

04:20:45.960 --> 04:20:47.960
[Guest]: and

04:20:47.960 --> 04:20:49.960
[Guest]: people from ITAR.

04:20:49.960 --> 04:20:51.960
[Guest]: So, I used to ask everyone,

04:20:51.960 --> 04:20:53.960
[Guest]: where are you from? Eastern UP or Western UP?

04:20:53.960 --> 04:20:55.960
[Guest]: And, that time I was supposed to learn

04:20:55.960 --> 04:20:57.960
[Guest]: Eastern UP.

04:20:57.960 --> 04:20:59.960
[Guest]: In the script, as per the script.

04:20:59.960 --> 04:21:01.960
[Guest]: So, if someone says

04:21:01.960 --> 04:21:03.960
[Guest]: Western UP, I will just listen

04:21:03.960 --> 04:21:05.960
[Guest]: but then I will not talk to them again.

04:21:05.960 --> 04:21:07.960
[Guest]: But, if it is Eastern UP, I will listen to them again and again

04:21:07.960 --> 04:21:09.960
[Guest]: so that I can get what they are saying.

04:21:09.960 --> 04:21:11.960
[Guest]: So, there were a lot of people from UP as well.

04:21:11.960 --> 04:21:13.960
[Guest]: When I was working in Calcutta,

04:21:13.960 --> 04:21:15.960
[Guest]: in the healthcare sector.

04:21:15.960 --> 04:21:17.960
[Guest]: So, I picked up all that

04:21:17.960 --> 04:21:19.960
[Guest]: and then I wrote songs.

04:21:19.960 --> 04:21:21.960
[Guest]: And, yeah, I mean,

04:21:21.960 --> 04:21:23.960
[Guest]: I think those songs did come out well.

04:21:23.960 --> 04:21:25.960
[Guest]: I think, there was a couple of songs

04:21:25.960 --> 04:21:27.960
[Guest]: that I had narrated to Anurag sir, Anurag Kashyap

04:21:27.960 --> 04:21:29.960
[Guest]: while

04:21:29.960 --> 04:21:31.960
[Guest]: he was interviewing me, so to say,

04:21:31.960 --> 04:21:33.960
[Guest]: to be in the film.

04:21:33.960 --> 04:21:35.960
[Guest]: One of them was Hatapai.

04:21:35.960 --> 04:21:37.960
[Guest]: And, the other I wrote was Blonde Balma.

04:21:37.960 --> 04:21:39.960
[Guest]: So,

04:21:39.960 --> 04:21:41.960
[Guest]: he read those and he was like,

04:21:41.960 --> 04:21:43.960
[Guest]: yeah, yeah, yeah, you write it.

04:21:43.960 --> 04:21:45.960
[Guest]: So, that's how he makes decisions.

04:21:45.960 --> 04:21:47.960
[Guest]: So, yeah,

04:21:47.960 --> 04:21:49.960
[Guest]: that was there.

04:21:49.960 --> 04:21:51.960
[Guest]: And then, of course, I mean,

04:21:51.960 --> 04:21:53.960
[Guest]: in the first album with Rochak Kohli

04:21:53.960 --> 04:21:55.960
[Guest]: and Kareeb Kareeb Single, I wrote on composition.

04:21:55.960 --> 04:21:57.960
[Guest]: In Mukkabaz, all songs

04:21:57.960 --> 04:21:59.960
[Guest]: are written on

04:21:59.960 --> 04:22:01.960
[Guest]: songs first.

04:22:01.960 --> 04:22:03.960
[Guest]: They were composed later.

04:22:03.960 --> 04:22:05.960
[Guest]: Then, Dhaga was written on composition

04:22:05.960 --> 04:22:07.960
[Guest]: first. I mean, I had to write

04:22:07.960 --> 04:22:09.960
[Guest]: it on a composition. Then, the

04:22:09.960 --> 04:22:11.960
[Guest]: entire album of Tripling was again

04:22:11.960 --> 04:22:13.960
[Guest]: composition first.

04:22:13.960 --> 04:22:15.960
[Guest]: Then, Chacha Vidhay Ke Hamare,

04:22:15.960 --> 04:22:17.960
[Guest]: the title song that I have written is

04:22:17.960 --> 04:22:19.960
[Guest]: lyrics first. But then, Vishal

04:22:19.960 --> 04:22:21.960
[Guest]: Dadlani has composed it so well that

04:22:21.960 --> 04:22:23.960
[Guest]: it does not, like, nobody can make

04:22:23.960 --> 04:22:25.960
[Guest]: out who, what has come

04:22:25.960 --> 04:22:27.960
[Guest]: first. And then,

04:22:27.960 --> 04:22:29.960
[Guest]: Taish mein, I had written

04:22:29.960 --> 04:22:31.960
[Guest]: two songs. Both had

04:22:31.960 --> 04:22:33.960
[Guest]: tune first. In Sherni,

04:22:33.960 --> 04:22:35.960
[Guest]: I had written a song, Bandar Baat,

04:22:35.960 --> 04:22:37.960
[Guest]: which I quite like.

04:22:37.960 --> 04:22:39.960
[Guest]: And it does have a lot of political

04:22:39.960 --> 04:22:41.960
[Guest]: but...

04:22:41.960 --> 04:22:43.960
[Guest]: Usme bhi aisa

04:22:43.960 --> 04:22:45.960
[Guest]: hua tha ki initially beat

04:22:45.960 --> 04:22:47.960
[Guest]: and mukhda mujhe diya gaya tha.

04:22:47.960 --> 04:22:49.960
[Guest]: And it was so difficult

04:22:49.960 --> 04:22:51.960
[Guest]: to fit lyrics on it because

04:22:51.960 --> 04:22:53.960
[Guest]: the singer is not breathing at

04:22:53.960 --> 04:22:55.960
[Guest]: all. There is no pause

04:22:55.960 --> 04:22:57.960
[Guest]: until it comes to that folkish...

04:22:57.960 --> 04:22:59.960
[Guest]: Wo bhi maine assume kar liya tha ki folkish hai.

04:22:59.960 --> 04:23:01.960
[Guest]: Toh...

04:23:01.960 --> 04:23:03.960
[Guest]: Usme toh enter kaise karo

04:23:03.960 --> 04:23:05.960
[Guest]: samanjh mein nahi aara tha is gaane mein.

04:23:05.960 --> 04:23:07.960
[Guest]: Toh ajeeb-ajeeb tarah ek complication aati hai.

04:23:07.960 --> 04:23:09.960
[Guest]: Phir...

04:23:09.960 --> 04:23:11.960
[Guest]: Usme phir aadha...

04:23:11.960 --> 04:23:13.960
[Guest]: phir uske baad aage ka beats

04:23:13.960 --> 04:23:15.960
[Guest]: pakad ke phir maine hi

04:23:15.960 --> 04:23:17.960
[Guest]: compose karke antara bhi bana diya tha uska.

04:23:17.960 --> 04:23:19.960
[Guest]: Toh yeh is tarah se hua tha.

04:23:19.960 --> 04:23:21.960
[Guest]: Toh yeh sab cheezein is tarah se rehti hain.

04:23:21.960 --> 04:23:23.960
[Guest]: Matlab, music mein. Aapko

04:23:23.960 --> 04:23:25.960
[Guest]: comparatively chote sentences likhne hota hain.

04:23:25.960 --> 04:23:27.960
[Guest]: Comparatively simple aur direct baate likhne hoti hain.

04:23:27.960 --> 04:23:29.960
[Guest]: Main

04:23:29.960 --> 04:23:31.960
[Guest]: is tarah ki lyrics mein

04:23:31.960 --> 04:23:33.960
[Guest]: comparatively mujhe

04:23:33.960 --> 04:23:35.960
[Guest]: English mein likhna koi bahut zyada clever aur

04:23:35.960 --> 04:23:37.960
[Guest]: bahut zyada edgy nahi lagta hai.

04:23:37.960 --> 04:23:39.960
[Guest]: Yeh mera bahut unpopular aur bahut hi

04:23:39.960 --> 04:23:41.960
[Guest]: cancellable opinion hai shayad.

04:23:41.960 --> 04:23:43.960
[Guest]: Wo isliye kyunki

04:23:43.960 --> 04:23:45.960
[Guest]: lyrics mein jab aap English mein likhte hain,

04:23:45.960 --> 04:23:47.960
[Guest]: toh aap wahi thought ko jaise aap

04:23:47.960 --> 04:23:49.960
[Guest]: apni mixed bhaasha mein soch raha hain.

04:23:49.960 --> 04:23:51.960
[Guest]: Usi mein likhte dete hain.

04:23:51.960 --> 04:23:53.960
[Guest]: It's actually an easier process

04:23:53.960 --> 04:23:55.960
[Guest]: to write in English.

04:23:55.960 --> 04:23:57.960
[Guest]: Toh proper ek zawaan mein,

04:23:57.960 --> 04:23:59.960
[Guest]: ek dialect mein likhke batayiye

04:23:59.960 --> 04:24:01.960
[Guest]: ek haath ki safai ke saath.

04:24:01.960 --> 04:24:03.960
[Guest]: Aapko daat ho talay pasina aayega.

04:24:03.960 --> 04:24:05.960
[Guest]: Toh jo log yeh mix

04:24:05.960 --> 04:24:07.960
[Guest]: language mein kayi baar achche gaane likh lete hain,

04:24:07.960 --> 04:24:09.960
[Guest]: unse aap jab proper

04:24:09.960 --> 04:24:11.960
[Guest]: likhne ko kehte hain

04:24:11.960 --> 04:24:13.960
[Guest]: ek zawaan mein,

04:24:13.960 --> 04:24:15.960
[Guest]: aapko unke haath ki safai pata lag jati hain.

04:24:15.960 --> 04:24:17.960
[Guest]: Ki unka haath itna saaf nahi hain.

04:24:17.960 --> 04:24:19.960
[Guest]: Toh wo pata aapko

04:24:19.960 --> 04:24:21.960
[Guest]: tabhi lagta hai jab aap se kaha jaye

04:24:21.960 --> 04:24:23.960
[Guest]: ki ek hi universe

04:24:23.960 --> 04:24:25.960
[Guest]: vocabulary create karo.

04:24:25.960 --> 04:24:27.960
[Guest]: Kyuki har gaane ki apni universe

04:24:27.960 --> 04:24:29.960
[Guest]: vocabulary bhi create hoti hain.

04:24:29.960 --> 04:24:31.960
[Guest]: Aapne agar pehli hi line mein

04:24:31.960 --> 04:24:33.960
[Guest]: agar English likh diya kuch,

04:24:33.960 --> 04:24:35.960
[Guest]: pehli teen line mein aapne English likha

04:24:35.960 --> 04:24:37.960
[Guest]: aur phir baad mein

04:24:37.960 --> 04:24:39.960
[Guest]: poora hard core tatsam tatbhav shabd ke

04:24:39.960 --> 04:24:41.960
[Guest]: Hindi chal raha hain, toh yeh iska matlab

04:24:41.960 --> 04:24:43.960
[Guest]: aapne dheek se likha nahi hai wo.

04:24:43.960 --> 04:24:45.960
[Guest]: Pehle aapne tyre puncture hogaya

04:24:45.960 --> 04:24:47.960
[Guest]: types kuch likh diya

04:24:47.960 --> 04:24:49.960
[Guest]: aur aakhri mein matlab

04:24:49.960 --> 04:24:51.960
[Guest]: tatkaal aur yeh

04:24:51.960 --> 04:24:53.960
[Guest]: matlab da rahe hain, yeh it will just not make sense

04:24:53.960 --> 04:24:55.960
[Guest]: it will not sound good.

04:24:55.960 --> 04:24:57.960
[Guest]: Toh ek universe setting hoti hain

04:24:57.960 --> 04:24:59.960
[Guest]: vocabulary lyrics mein, jo main

04:24:59.960 --> 04:25:01.960
[Guest]: atleast try karta hu, main ensure karta hu ki wo

04:25:01.960 --> 04:25:03.960
[Guest]: karun. Bahut se log isko

04:25:03.960 --> 04:25:05.960
[Guest]: counter bhi kar sakte hain yeh keh ke ki aap

04:25:05.960 --> 04:25:07.960
[Guest]: freedom rok raha hain.

04:25:07.960 --> 04:25:09.960
[Guest]: That is also way of thinking.

04:25:09.960 --> 04:25:11.960
[Guest]: I don't agree to it, but I know most

04:25:11.960 --> 04:25:13.960
[Guest]: will agree to it.

04:25:13.960 --> 04:25:15.960
[Guest]: Then, mujhe

04:25:15.960 --> 04:25:17.960
[Guest]: ek certain poetic

04:25:17.960 --> 04:25:19.960
[Guest]: matlab flavour toh chahiye gaano mein.

04:25:19.960 --> 04:25:21.960
[Guest]: Thik hai, main yeh nahi kehata ki har gaane

04:25:21.960 --> 04:25:23.960
[Guest]: mein shairi thoos di jaye.

04:25:23.960 --> 04:25:25.960
[Guest]: Lekin, kuch ek

04:25:25.960 --> 04:25:27.960
[Guest]: poetic

04:25:27.960 --> 04:25:29.960
[Guest]: flavour ho, koi ek turn of

04:25:29.960 --> 04:25:31.960
[Guest]: phrase ho jo mujhe acha lage, ki haan yeh

04:25:31.960 --> 04:25:33.960
[Guest]: acha hai. Koi ek

04:25:33.960 --> 04:25:35.960
[Guest]: baat aisi ho jo

04:25:35.960 --> 04:25:37.960
[Guest]: lage, yaar yeh toh nahi baat bol gaya,

04:25:37.960 --> 04:25:39.960
[Guest]: yeh acha phrase bol gaya.

04:25:39.960 --> 04:25:41.960
[Guest]: Yaar, koi ek poetic

04:25:41.960 --> 04:25:43.960
[Guest]: reference, koi cliche aapne

04:25:43.960 --> 04:25:45.960
[Guest]: uthaya hai aur cliche ko istara se

04:25:45.960 --> 04:25:47.960
[Guest]: rephrase kiya hai, ki acha lag raha hai.

04:25:47.960 --> 04:25:49.960
[Guest]: Sunne mein.

04:25:49.960 --> 04:25:51.960
[Guest]: Toh main yeh bhi nahi kehata ki cliche,

04:25:51.960 --> 04:25:53.960
[Guest]: main iss se fully wo nahi karta hai

04:25:53.960 --> 04:25:55.960
[Guest]: ki cliche nahi hona chahiye gaane.

04:25:55.960 --> 04:25:57.960
[Guest]: Main kehata hoon, agar aap achche se likh sakte

04:25:57.960 --> 04:25:59.960
[Guest]: toh kyon nahi hona chahiye.

04:25:59.960 --> 04:26:01.960
[Guest]: Aap,

04:26:01.960 --> 04:26:03.960
[Guest]: cliche ka fayada yeh hota hai ki audience

04:26:03.960 --> 04:26:05.960
[Guest]: badhi jaldi samajh jati hai.

04:26:05.960 --> 04:26:07.960
[Guest]: Lekin, ab main us cliche ke saath kar kya raha hoon?

04:26:07.960 --> 04:26:09.960
[Guest]: Yeh bhi

04:26:09.960 --> 04:26:11.960
[Guest]: audience kahi baar sunna chahati hai.

04:26:11.960 --> 04:26:13.960
[Guest]: Toh yeh mujhe kahi baar

04:26:13.960 --> 04:26:15.960
[Guest]: interesting lagta hai. Mera yeh bhi maanna hai ki

04:26:15.960 --> 04:26:17.960
[Guest]: instead of using aise shabd

04:26:17.960 --> 04:26:19.960
[Guest]: matlab clever sound karne ke liye

04:26:19.960 --> 04:26:21.960
[Guest]: jo aapne abhi abhi seekhe hain

04:26:21.960 --> 04:26:23.960
[Guest]: unhe hook line me daal dena

04:26:23.960 --> 04:26:25.960
[Guest]: unhe usme daal dena, usse behtar yeh hai

04:26:25.960 --> 04:26:27.960
[Guest]: ki jo shabd aapko aate hain, unhi pe khelo.

04:26:27.960 --> 04:26:29.960
[Guest]: Jinn lafzo ke saath

04:26:29.960 --> 04:26:31.960
[Guest]: aap bahut waqt bitaaye ho.

04:26:31.960 --> 04:26:33.960
[Guest]: You know, bahut saare

04:26:33.960 --> 04:26:35.960
[Guest]: lafz aise hote hain, jinn ke saath aapne bahut waqt

04:26:35.960 --> 04:26:37.960
[Guest]: bitaaya hota hai.

04:26:37.960 --> 04:26:39.960
[Guest]: Toh aap unko istamaal karein

04:26:39.960 --> 04:26:41.960
[Guest]: aur unhe achche se

04:26:41.960 --> 04:26:43.960
[Guest]: istamaal karein, unhe qaeda se istamaal karein,

04:26:43.960 --> 04:26:45.960
[Guest]: aap barte hain, achche se barte hain.

04:26:45.960 --> 04:26:47.960
[Guest]: You treat those words

04:26:47.960 --> 04:26:49.960
[Guest]: well.

04:26:49.960 --> 04:26:51.960
[Guest]: That is

04:26:51.960 --> 04:26:53.960
[Guest]: something I prefer

04:26:53.960 --> 04:26:55.960
[Guest]: more than using a word

04:26:55.960 --> 04:26:57.960
[Guest]: that I have learnt probably 3 months back,

04:26:57.960 --> 04:26:59.960
[Guest]: 6 months back and I thought, hey this is an edgy, nice

04:26:59.960 --> 04:27:01.960
[Guest]: word, it has a nice ring to it, maybe it can be a

04:27:01.960 --> 04:27:03.960
[Guest]: hook line, maybe, you know things like that.

04:27:03.960 --> 04:27:05.960
[Guest]: I don't go by that.

04:27:05.960 --> 04:27:07.960
[Guest]: So that's lyrics.

04:27:07.960 --> 04:27:09.960
[Amit Varma]: Before I

04:27:09.960 --> 04:27:11.960
[Amit Varma]: come to my next question,

04:27:11.960 --> 04:27:13.960
[Amit Varma]: observation that I often make in class

04:27:13.960 --> 04:27:15.960
[Amit Varma]: that, you know, a lot of the greatest

04:27:15.960 --> 04:27:17.960
[Amit Varma]: art, from Shakespeare to Dylan to

04:27:17.960 --> 04:27:19.960
[Amit Varma]: Springsteen to whatever, comes from

04:27:19.960 --> 04:27:21.960
[Amit Varma]: simple everyday language, that point you made

04:27:21.960 --> 04:27:23.960
[Amit Varma]: about keep it simple and all that and the example

04:27:23.960 --> 04:27:25.960
[Amit Varma]: I gave is, and I'll link it from

04:27:25.960 --> 04:27:27.960
[Amit Varma]: the show notes, is a great song by Bruce Springsteen

04:27:27.960 --> 04:27:29.960
[Amit Varma]: called You're Missing, which was written after

04:27:29.960 --> 04:27:31.960
[Amit Varma]: 9-11 and he's writing about

04:27:31.960 --> 04:27:33.960
[Amit Varma]: you know, the family of someone

04:27:33.960 --> 04:27:35.960
[Amit Varma]: which is mourning someone who is not

04:27:35.960 --> 04:27:37.960
[Amit Varma]: there, who died in the attack. So I'll just read

04:27:37.960 --> 04:27:39.960
[Unknown]: out a passage and you can just see the simplicity

04:27:39.960 --> 04:27:41.960
[Amit Varma]: of the words. Coffee cups on

04:27:41.960 --> 04:27:43.960
[Amit Varma]: the counter, jackets on the chair,

04:27:43.960 --> 04:27:45.960
[Unknown]: papers on the doorstep, you're not there.

04:27:45.960 --> 04:27:47.960
[Amit Varma]: Everything is everything. Everything is everything.

04:27:47.960 --> 04:27:49.960
[Unknown]: But you're missing.

04:27:49.960 --> 04:27:51.960
[Unknown]: Right? And who would have thought

04:27:51.960 --> 04:27:53.960
[Amit Varma]: that words like everything is everything

04:27:53.960 --> 04:27:55.960
[Amit Varma]: can be the stuff of art.

04:27:55.960 --> 04:27:57.960
[Amit Varma]: You're taking the most common words

04:27:57.960 --> 04:27:59.960
[Unknown]: and using them. And there is so much craft also

04:27:59.960 --> 04:28:01.960
[Amit Varma]: because the mute sounds, the hard sounds,

04:28:01.960 --> 04:28:03.960
[Guest]: everything missing.

04:28:03.960 --> 04:28:05.960
[Guest]: Actually, it is

04:28:05.960 --> 04:28:07.960
[Guest]: very difficult

04:28:07.960 --> 04:28:09.960
[Guest]: to write simple.

04:28:09.960 --> 04:28:11.960
[Guest]: It is very easy to write

04:28:11.960 --> 04:28:13.960
[Guest]: simplistic.

04:28:13.960 --> 04:28:15.960
[Guest]: And it is also easy to write difficult.

04:28:15.960 --> 04:28:17.960
[Guest]: But I think it is difficult

04:28:17.960 --> 04:28:19.960
[Amit Varma]: to write easy.

04:28:19.960 --> 04:28:21.960
[Guest]: Difficult to write simple.

04:28:21.960 --> 04:28:23.960
[Amit Varma]: So here's my next question, that

04:28:23.960 --> 04:28:25.960
[Amit Varma]: when you're writing lyrics,

04:28:25.960 --> 04:28:27.960
[Amit Varma]: everything is changed, right? In the sense that

04:28:27.960 --> 04:28:29.960
[Amit Varma]: now there are all these constraints on you

04:28:29.960 --> 04:28:31.960
[Amit Varma]: about the kind of lengths you can use,

04:28:31.960 --> 04:28:33.960
[Amit Varma]: the kind of words you can use, this hard sound,

04:28:33.960 --> 04:28:35.960
[Amit Varma]: soft sound thing, the music that you're given,

04:28:35.960 --> 04:28:37.960
[Amit Varma]: you have those parameters.

04:28:37.960 --> 04:28:39.960
[Amit Varma]: And these constraints make you

04:28:39.960 --> 04:28:41.960
[Amit Varma]: look at the language really closely,

04:28:41.960 --> 04:28:43.960
[Unknown]: make you examine every element of what

04:28:43.960 --> 04:28:45.960
[Amit Varma]: you're writing. Does this then

04:28:45.960 --> 04:28:47.960
[Amit Varma]: play into your poetry as well,

04:28:47.960 --> 04:28:49.960
[Amit Varma]: play into your other writing and make you better at that

04:28:49.960 --> 04:28:51.960
[Amit Varma]: because you've been forced to pay

04:28:51.960 --> 04:28:53.960
[Amit Varma]: attention with such granularity

04:28:53.960 --> 04:28:55.960
[Guest]: to all these little details?

04:28:55.960 --> 04:28:57.960
[Guest]: Yes, yes, yes, it is. And the thing is I like it.

04:28:57.960 --> 04:28:59.960
[Guest]: I mean, I like thinking about

04:28:59.960 --> 04:29:01.960
[Guest]: words. I like

04:29:01.960 --> 04:29:03.960
[Guest]: knowing new usages of the

04:29:03.960 --> 04:29:05.960
[Guest]: words. I like

04:29:05.960 --> 04:29:07.960
[Guest]: there are a lot of

04:29:07.960 --> 04:29:09.960
[Guest]: words that for some reason

04:29:09.960 --> 04:29:11.960
[Guest]: phonetically make a lot of sense to me.

04:29:11.960 --> 04:29:13.960
[Guest]: And there are a lot of words that I phonetically do

04:29:13.960 --> 04:29:15.960
[Guest]: not prefer.

04:29:15.960 --> 04:29:17.960
[Guest]: Like

04:29:17.960 --> 04:29:19.960
[Guest]: muskana. I don't like

04:29:19.960 --> 04:29:21.960
[Guest]: that word.

04:29:21.960 --> 04:29:23.960
[Guest]: There's nothing wrong with that

04:29:23.960 --> 04:29:25.960
[Guest]: word, okay? I just don't like it.

04:29:25.960 --> 04:29:27.960
[Guest]: Masaka. I don't like it.

04:29:27.960 --> 04:29:29.960
[Guest]: I don't like the sound of muskana.

04:29:29.960 --> 04:29:31.960
[Guest]: But muskurana, I'm

04:29:31.960 --> 04:29:33.960
[Guest]: okay with it for some reason.

04:29:33.960 --> 04:29:35.960
[Guest]: But if I can avoid

04:29:35.960 --> 04:29:37.960
[Guest]: muskurana or muskurahat

04:29:37.960 --> 04:29:39.960
[Guest]: or muskana, I will do it.

04:29:39.960 --> 04:29:41.960
[Guest]: I will not use

04:29:41.960 --> 04:29:43.960
[Guest]: either of the three words. Do I have

04:29:43.960 --> 04:29:45.960
[Guest]: a reason for it? I don't have a reason for it.

04:29:45.960 --> 04:29:47.960
[Guest]: It's a clear preference.

04:29:47.960 --> 04:29:49.960
[Guest]: But, you were saying

04:29:49.960 --> 04:29:51.960
[Guest]: sorry, I completely digressed

04:29:51.960 --> 04:29:53.960
[Amit Varma]: that... No, you were absolutely right

04:29:53.960 --> 04:29:55.960
[Amit Varma]: that I was, I mean you were answering the question

04:29:55.960 --> 04:29:57.960
[Amit Varma]: in the sense I was asking is that did the close

04:29:57.960 --> 04:29:59.960
[Guest]: attention you had to pay... Oh yes, yes, yes.

04:29:59.960 --> 04:30:01.960
[Guest]: So, yes, in close attention,

04:30:01.960 --> 04:30:03.960
[Guest]: what happens in poetry

04:30:03.960 --> 04:30:05.960
[Guest]: is that in poetry,

04:30:05.960 --> 04:30:07.960
[Guest]: the subtlety of the songs

04:30:07.960 --> 04:30:09.960
[Guest]: and the attention

04:30:09.960 --> 04:30:11.960
[Guest]: goes into your subconscious training.

04:30:11.960 --> 04:30:13.960
[Guest]: So,

04:30:13.960 --> 04:30:15.960
[Guest]: in songs, I often have

04:30:15.960 --> 04:30:17.960
[Guest]: that line should not be wasted.

04:30:19.960 --> 04:30:21.960
[Guest]: And, in poetry,

04:30:21.960 --> 04:30:23.960
[Guest]: I used to have

04:30:23.960 --> 04:30:25.960
[Guest]: that whatever seems extra, cut it.

04:30:25.960 --> 04:30:27.960
[Guest]: Cut it, cut it, cut it

04:30:27.960 --> 04:30:29.960
[Guest]: as much as you can.

04:30:29.960 --> 04:30:31.960
[Guest]: I am not like, keep this, keep that.

04:30:31.960 --> 04:30:33.960
[Guest]: I am like, cut it. Cut it as much as you can

04:30:33.960 --> 04:30:35.960
[Guest]: and make it a point. Talk about

04:30:35.960 --> 04:30:37.960
[Guest]: as much as the point is. Don't talk more than that.

04:30:37.960 --> 04:30:39.960
[Guest]: I mean, if

04:30:39.960 --> 04:30:41.960
[Guest]: this lizard, I can

04:30:41.960 --> 04:30:43.960
[Guest]: I could have written the poem that

04:30:43.960 --> 04:30:45.960
[Guest]: I went to the office, was smoking a cigarette.

04:30:45.960 --> 04:30:47.960
[Guest]: All that is

04:30:47.960 --> 04:30:49.960
[Guest]: irrelevant. It is just that

04:30:49.960 --> 04:30:51.960
[Guest]: moment which is irrelevant. Everything

04:30:51.960 --> 04:30:53.960
[Guest]: can be cut. So,

04:30:53.960 --> 04:30:55.960
[Guest]: that brevity

04:30:55.960 --> 04:30:57.960
[Guest]: and that kind of bounce

04:30:57.960 --> 04:30:59.960
[Guest]: in phrases that I learn

04:30:59.960 --> 04:31:01.960
[Guest]: subconsciously from songs

04:31:01.960 --> 04:31:03.960
[Guest]: does flow into my poetry.

04:31:03.960 --> 04:31:05.960
[Guest]: However,

04:31:05.960 --> 04:31:07.960
[Guest]: the poetry is still more

04:31:07.960 --> 04:31:09.960
[Guest]: it gives me more freedom

04:31:09.960 --> 04:31:11.960
[Guest]: in what I want to write.

04:31:11.960 --> 04:31:13.960
[Guest]: It also gives me more

04:31:13.960 --> 04:31:15.960
[Guest]: vulnerability and

04:31:15.960 --> 04:31:17.960
[Guest]: avenue to be

04:31:17.960 --> 04:31:19.960
[Guest]: emotionally exposed

04:31:19.960 --> 04:31:21.960
[Guest]: which songs do not.

04:31:21.960 --> 04:31:23.960
[Guest]: In songs, of course, there is a brief

04:31:23.960 --> 04:31:25.960
[Guest]: and everything. But,

04:31:25.960 --> 04:31:27.960
[Guest]: I get into songs as well. There are many things.

04:31:27.960 --> 04:31:29.960
[Guest]: It is not like

04:31:29.960 --> 04:31:31.960
[Guest]: I am not myself in songs.

04:31:31.960 --> 04:31:33.960
[Guest]: The rage of a lot of respect

04:31:33.960 --> 04:31:35.960
[Guest]: is my rage.

04:31:35.960 --> 04:31:37.960
[Guest]: And, I mean,

04:31:39.960 --> 04:31:41.960
[Guest]: whatever I am saying in it, I am saying it.

04:31:41.960 --> 04:31:43.960
[Guest]: It is just that I have put UP's dialect in it.

04:31:43.960 --> 04:31:45.960
[Amit Varma]: And does Tanha Begum also

04:31:45.960 --> 04:31:47.960
[Guest]: have your feeling of love? Yeah, yeah, yeah. It has.

04:31:47.960 --> 04:31:49.960
[Guest]: It does. Even simple things

04:31:49.960 --> 04:31:51.960
[Guest]: like, if you leave, I will leave too.

04:31:51.960 --> 04:31:53.960
[Guest]: Even those basic things, Ishq-e-Hafiz,

04:31:53.960 --> 04:31:55.960
[Guest]: that guilt in love, or

04:31:55.960 --> 04:31:57.960
[Guest]: if I see the politics of

04:31:57.960 --> 04:31:59.960
[Guest]: Bandar Baant, then who are the monkeys?

04:31:59.960 --> 04:32:01.960
[Guest]: The cats are

04:32:01.960 --> 04:32:03.960
[Guest]: marginalized, they are fighting.

04:32:03.960 --> 04:32:05.960
[Guest]: And the monkey sitting on top

04:32:05.960 --> 04:32:07.960
[Guest]: is eating the bread.

04:32:07.960 --> 04:32:09.960
[Guest]: So, I mean,

04:32:09.960 --> 04:32:11.960
[Guest]: that is also coming from there.

04:32:11.960 --> 04:32:13.960
[Guest]: Like,

04:32:13.960 --> 04:32:15.960
[Guest]: even the short film named

04:32:15.960 --> 04:32:17.960
[Guest]: Madhyantar that I have written on Netflix,

04:32:17.960 --> 04:32:19.960
[Guest]: I have put a very small thing in it

04:32:19.960 --> 04:32:21.960
[Guest]: which I find

04:32:21.960 --> 04:32:23.960
[Guest]: very interesting. In that, the girl

04:32:23.960 --> 04:32:25.960
[Guest]: keeps eating food, if you watch that film.

04:32:25.960 --> 04:32:27.960
[Guest]: So, I find it very strange

04:32:27.960 --> 04:32:29.960
[Guest]: that whenever I watch films,

04:32:29.960 --> 04:32:31.960
[Guest]: I used to think,

04:32:31.960 --> 04:32:33.960
[Guest]: why don't girls eat food

04:32:33.960 --> 04:32:35.960
[Guest]: in any film?

04:32:35.960 --> 04:32:37.960
[Guest]: Okay? Wow.

04:32:37.960 --> 04:32:39.960
[Guest]: I mean, don't girls eat food?

04:32:39.960 --> 04:32:41.960
[Guest]: And it is not that there are zero scenes of women

04:32:41.960 --> 04:32:43.960
[Guest]: eating, but generally

04:32:43.960 --> 04:32:45.960
[Guest]: a man eating is shown

04:32:45.960 --> 04:32:47.960
[Guest]: much more times than a woman eating.

04:32:47.960 --> 04:32:49.960
[Guest]: I don't know.

04:32:49.960 --> 04:32:51.960
[Guest]: Now, I don't know if this is a revolutionary feminist

04:32:51.960 --> 04:32:53.960
[Guest]: thought or not, but

04:32:53.960 --> 04:32:55.960
[Guest]: I mean, obviously not.

04:32:55.960 --> 04:32:57.960
[Guest]: But, I feel that

04:32:57.960 --> 04:32:59.960
[Guest]: my common

04:32:59.960 --> 04:33:01.960
[Guest]: observation is that I have

04:33:01.960 --> 04:33:03.960
[Guest]: heard a lot of girls talking

04:33:03.960 --> 04:33:05.960
[Guest]: only about food.

04:33:05.960 --> 04:33:07.960
[Guest]: And mostly about food.

04:33:07.960 --> 04:33:09.960
[Guest]: So, I felt that this is such a basic

04:33:09.960 --> 04:33:11.960
[Guest]: thing that I can show in that character.

04:33:11.960 --> 04:33:13.960
[Guest]: That she likes to eat

04:33:13.960 --> 04:33:15.960
[Guest]: and she also likes sweets.

04:33:15.960 --> 04:33:17.960
[Guest]: And she takes a lot of

04:33:17.960 --> 04:33:19.960
[Guest]: care about food.

04:33:19.960 --> 04:33:21.960
[Guest]: So, I mean,

04:33:21.960 --> 04:33:23.960
[Guest]: of course, there is a poetic

04:33:23.960 --> 04:33:25.960
[Guest]: type metaphorization in cinema

04:33:25.960 --> 04:33:27.960
[Guest]: that her hunger

04:33:27.960 --> 04:33:29.960
[Guest]: of ambition, etc.

04:33:29.960 --> 04:33:31.960
[Guest]: can be associated.

04:33:31.960 --> 04:33:33.960
[Guest]: But, I actually

04:33:33.960 --> 04:33:35.960
[Guest]: wanted to show that a girl

04:33:35.960 --> 04:33:37.960
[Guest]: likes to eat a lot.

04:33:37.960 --> 04:33:39.960
[Guest]: And why not?

04:33:39.960 --> 04:33:41.960
[Amit Varma]: There is a lovely film

04:33:41.960 --> 04:33:43.960
[Amit Varma]: by one of my favorite filmmakers,

04:33:43.960 --> 04:33:45.960
[Amit Varma]: Manuel, which is called The Discreet Charm

04:33:45.960 --> 04:33:47.960
[Unknown]: of the Bourgeoisie. I think it came in

04:33:47.960 --> 04:33:49.960
[Unknown]: 1973. Screenplay was by

04:33:49.960 --> 04:33:51.960
[Amit Varma]: Jean-Claude Carrire, who also

04:33:51.960 --> 04:33:53.960
[Amit Varma]: wrote the screenplay of Peter Brooks

04:33:53.960 --> 04:33:55.960
[Amit Varma]: Mahabharata and Unbearable Lightness

04:33:55.960 --> 04:33:57.960
[Amit Varma]: of Being. And that film is

04:33:57.960 --> 04:33:59.960
[Amit Varma]: only about a bunch of people who are always

04:33:59.960 --> 04:34:01.960
[Amit Varma]: sitting down to eat and never actually eating.

04:34:01.960 --> 04:34:03.960
[Amit Varma]: Something or the other happens.

04:34:03.960 --> 04:34:05.960
[Amit Varma]: So, the whole freaking film is that

04:34:05.960 --> 04:34:07.960
[Amit Varma]: sitting down at various places trying to eat

04:34:07.960 --> 04:34:09.960
[Amit Varma]: and something or the other happens.

04:34:09.960 --> 04:34:11.960
[Amit Varma]: And they can't eat.

04:34:11.960 --> 04:34:13.960
[Amit Varma]: So, if you watch the whole thing, by the end of it,

04:34:13.960 --> 04:34:15.960
[Guest]: you are hungry.

04:34:15.960 --> 04:34:17.960
[Guest]: No, no. I put a lot of personal stuff.

04:34:17.960 --> 04:34:19.960
[Guest]: Like, a series that I have co-written,

04:34:19.960 --> 04:34:21.960
[Guest]: one in lakhs, in which

04:34:21.960 --> 04:34:23.960
[Guest]: I have worked in healthcare for three years.

04:34:23.960 --> 04:34:25.960
[Guest]: I have put a lot of experience of that.

04:34:25.960 --> 04:34:27.960
[Guest]: The cataract operations,

04:34:27.960 --> 04:34:29.960
[Guest]: the camps,

04:34:29.960 --> 04:34:31.960
[Guest]: the doctors I had

04:34:31.960 --> 04:34:33.960
[Guest]: contact with, who I talked to,

04:34:33.960 --> 04:34:35.960
[Guest]: what kind of personality,

04:34:35.960 --> 04:34:37.960
[Guest]: what kind of things happen in hospitals,

04:34:37.960 --> 04:34:39.960
[Guest]: what kind of crises happen,

04:34:39.960 --> 04:34:41.960
[Guest]: what kind of incidents happen in hospitals.

04:34:41.960 --> 04:34:43.960
[Guest]: So, in a sugar-coated,

04:34:43.960 --> 04:34:45.960
[Guest]: or rather sugar-candied way,

04:34:45.960 --> 04:34:47.960
[Guest]: the healthcare

04:34:47.960 --> 04:34:49.960
[Guest]: and hospitals that have been shown

04:34:49.960 --> 04:34:51.960
[Guest]: in cinemas till now,

04:34:51.960 --> 04:34:53.960
[Guest]: and how

04:34:53.960 --> 04:34:55.960
[Guest]: prone to

04:34:55.960 --> 04:34:57.960
[Guest]: falling down

04:34:57.960 --> 04:34:59.960
[Guest]: and falling down,

04:34:59.960 --> 04:35:01.960
[Guest]: India's healthcare system.

04:35:01.960 --> 04:35:03.960
[Guest]: So, this series came out in 2019

04:35:03.960 --> 04:35:05.960
[Guest]: and in 2020,

04:35:05.960 --> 04:35:07.960
[Guest]: people saw its effect after the pandemic.

04:35:07.960 --> 04:35:09.960
[Guest]: But when people were reading the news

04:35:09.960 --> 04:35:11.960
[Guest]: during the pandemic, I felt like,

04:35:11.960 --> 04:35:13.960
[Guest]: we have said all of this in the series.

04:35:13.960 --> 04:35:15.960
[Guest]: We have just said that this will happen,

04:35:15.960 --> 04:35:17.960
[Guest]: that will happen. But...

04:35:17.960 --> 04:35:19.960
[Guest]: So, that thing,

04:35:19.960 --> 04:35:21.960
[Guest]: yes, there is a lot of

04:35:21.960 --> 04:35:23.960
[Guest]: significance of experience.

04:35:23.960 --> 04:35:25.960
[Guest]: Like,

04:35:25.960 --> 04:35:27.960
[Guest]: in songs,

04:35:27.960 --> 04:35:29.960
[Guest]: I talk about myself in a lot of places.

04:35:29.960 --> 04:35:31.960
[Guest]: Like, there is a song in Tripling

04:35:31.960 --> 04:35:33.960
[Guest]: in which it says,

04:35:33.960 --> 04:35:35.960
[Guest]: forgive everything.

04:35:35.960 --> 04:35:37.960
[Guest]: In homes, it is said,

04:35:37.960 --> 04:35:39.960
[Guest]: forgive everything.

04:35:39.960 --> 04:35:41.960
[Guest]: We say this in Gujarati.

04:35:41.960 --> 04:35:43.960
[Guest]: So, this...

04:35:43.960 --> 04:35:45.960
[Guest]: So, this is a phrase

04:35:45.960 --> 04:35:47.960
[Guest]: that my grandmother used to say,

04:35:47.960 --> 04:35:49.960
[Guest]: forgive everything.

04:35:49.960 --> 04:35:51.960
[Guest]: I don't even know

04:35:51.960 --> 04:35:53.960
[Guest]: where I am taking this from.

04:35:53.960 --> 04:35:55.960
[Guest]: That we are praying from here,

04:35:55.960 --> 04:35:57.960
[Guest]: whatever may happen,

04:35:57.960 --> 04:35:59.960
[Guest]: this is what my grandmother used to say.

04:35:59.960 --> 04:36:01.960
[Guest]: We should pray from here.

04:36:01.960 --> 04:36:03.960
[Guest]: So, like this,

04:36:03.960 --> 04:36:05.960
[Guest]: she used to say,

04:36:05.960 --> 04:36:07.960
[Guest]: I don't even know

04:36:07.960 --> 04:36:09.960
[Guest]: where I am taking this from.

04:36:09.960 --> 04:36:11.960
[Guest]: So, like,

04:36:11.960 --> 04:36:13.960
[Guest]: sometimes,

04:36:13.960 --> 04:36:15.960
[Guest]: there is another theme,

04:36:15.960 --> 04:36:17.960
[Guest]: there is a song called Patang in Tripling,

04:36:17.960 --> 04:36:19.960
[Guest]: in which I have talked about,

04:36:19.960 --> 04:36:21.960
[Guest]: very indirectly, about migration from your home.

04:36:21.960 --> 04:36:23.960
[Guest]: It's not talking about migration,

04:36:23.960 --> 04:36:25.960
[Guest]: but in the end,

04:36:25.960 --> 04:36:27.960
[Guest]: it somehow reveals.

04:36:27.960 --> 04:36:29.960
[Guest]: But, in that too,

04:36:29.960 --> 04:36:31.960
[Guest]: you do some small tricks.

04:36:31.960 --> 04:36:33.960
[Guest]: Again, that writing craft,

04:36:33.960 --> 04:36:35.960
[Guest]: like we are talking about,

04:36:35.960 --> 04:36:37.960
[Guest]: so, first I have written,

04:36:37.960 --> 04:36:39.960
[Guest]: those who got lost in the winds,

04:36:39.960 --> 04:36:41.960
[Guest]: became like a kite.

04:36:41.960 --> 04:36:43.960
[Guest]: So, those who got lost in the winds,

04:36:43.960 --> 04:36:45.960
[Guest]: became like a kite,

04:36:45.960 --> 04:36:47.960
[Guest]: is what I have written initially.

04:36:47.960 --> 04:36:49.960
[Guest]: Then, it literally translated to,

04:36:49.960 --> 04:36:51.960
[Guest]: that when I got lost in the winds,

04:36:51.960 --> 04:36:53.960
[Guest]: I became like a kite.

04:36:53.960 --> 04:36:55.960
[Guest]: Then, I have rephrased it to,

04:36:55.960 --> 04:36:57.960
[Guest]: those who got lost in the winds,

04:36:57.960 --> 04:36:59.960
[Guest]: became like a kite.

04:36:59.960 --> 04:37:01.960
[Guest]: Then, I became of the winds.

04:37:03.960 --> 04:37:05.960
[Guest]: Certain change.

04:37:05.960 --> 04:37:07.960
[Guest]: I got lost like a kite.

04:37:07.960 --> 04:37:09.960
[Guest]: And, I thought, okay,

04:37:09.960 --> 04:37:11.960
[Guest]: this is more interesting.

04:37:11.960 --> 04:37:13.960
[Guest]: But, yeah, these are very small changes.

04:37:13.960 --> 04:37:15.960
[Guest]: So, in the lyrics,

04:37:15.960 --> 04:37:17.960
[Guest]: in the writing,

04:37:17.960 --> 04:37:19.960
[Guest]: in the screenwriting,

04:37:19.960 --> 04:37:21.960
[Guest]: I put a lot of effort.

04:37:21.960 --> 04:37:23.960
[Guest]: And, of course,

04:37:23.960 --> 04:37:25.960
[Guest]: like,

04:37:25.960 --> 04:37:27.960
[Guest]: that,

04:37:27.960 --> 04:37:29.960
[Guest]: it doesn't happen that you have to insert.

04:37:29.960 --> 04:37:31.960
[Guest]: It has to come naturally

04:37:31.960 --> 04:37:33.960
[Guest]: in the story.

04:37:33.960 --> 04:37:35.960
[Guest]: The art will always take precedence.

04:37:35.960 --> 04:37:37.960
[Guest]: It cannot,

04:37:37.960 --> 04:37:39.960
[Guest]: which,

04:37:39.960 --> 04:37:41.960
[Guest]: I mean, if you are writing a poem,

04:37:41.960 --> 04:37:43.960
[Guest]: then that poem should also be good.

04:37:43.960 --> 04:37:45.960
[Guest]: I mean, it is possible that you have a political thought

04:37:45.960 --> 04:37:47.960
[Guest]: in it. It is possible that

04:37:47.960 --> 04:37:49.960
[Guest]: you have to say something,

04:37:49.960 --> 04:37:51.960
[Guest]: which is personal and political.

04:37:51.960 --> 04:37:53.960
[Guest]: And, of course, there is a debate,

04:37:53.960 --> 04:37:55.960
[Guest]: personal is political, etc.

04:37:55.960 --> 04:37:57.960
[Guest]: So, for me,

04:37:57.960 --> 04:37:59.960
[Guest]: personally, I feel that

04:37:59.960 --> 04:38:01.960
[Guest]: the medium of art form,

04:38:01.960 --> 04:38:03.960
[Guest]: its rules, its craft, takes precedence.

04:38:07.960 --> 04:38:09.960
[Guest]: It should also hold

04:38:09.960 --> 04:38:11.960
[Guest]: stand-alone.

04:38:11.960 --> 04:38:13.960
[Guest]: I mean,

04:38:13.960 --> 04:38:15.960
[Guest]: if I don't tell anyone

04:38:15.960 --> 04:38:17.960
[Guest]: why I have written this,

04:38:17.960 --> 04:38:19.960
[Guest]: what I have written,

04:38:19.960 --> 04:38:21.960
[Guest]: if someone doesn't know what I am saying,

04:38:21.960 --> 04:38:23.960
[Guest]: if there is a lizard,

04:38:23.960 --> 04:38:25.960
[Guest]: if I am reading it,

04:38:25.960 --> 04:38:27.960
[Guest]: then will no tropical climate

04:38:27.960 --> 04:38:29.960
[Guest]: in Africa relate to it,

04:38:29.960 --> 04:38:31.960
[Guest]: where there are lizards?

04:38:31.960 --> 04:38:33.960
[Guest]: He will understand,

04:38:33.960 --> 04:38:35.960
[Guest]: because he has seen this image,

04:38:35.960 --> 04:38:37.960
[Guest]: that this is coming from a photo.

04:38:37.960 --> 04:38:39.960
[Guest]: Some poems, of course,

04:38:39.960 --> 04:38:41.960
[Guest]: won't be like that.

04:38:41.960 --> 04:38:43.960
[Guest]: But, now,

04:38:43.960 --> 04:38:45.960
[Guest]: I have a poem called Lohe Ke Swaat,

04:38:45.960 --> 04:38:47.960
[Guest]: in that I am talking about

04:38:47.960 --> 04:38:49.960
[Guest]: how people,

04:38:49.960 --> 04:38:51.960
[Guest]: oppressed, marginalized,

04:38:51.960 --> 04:38:53.960
[Guest]: can complain or can resist

04:38:53.960 --> 04:38:55.960
[Guest]: in different manners. Some of them can be rude,

04:38:55.960 --> 04:38:57.960
[Guest]: some of them can be polite.

04:38:57.960 --> 04:38:59.960
[Guest]: No

04:38:59.960 --> 04:39:01.960
[Guest]: person oppressed

04:39:01.960 --> 04:39:03.960
[Guest]: is going to give you the same narrative,

04:39:03.960 --> 04:39:05.960
[Guest]: in the same language, in the same fashion,

04:39:05.960 --> 04:39:07.960
[Guest]: at the same time,

04:39:07.960 --> 04:39:09.960
[Guest]: for your ready consumption,

04:39:09.960 --> 04:39:11.960
[Guest]: in the way that you want it,

04:39:11.960 --> 04:39:13.960
[Guest]: palatable to your ears,

04:39:13.960 --> 04:39:15.960
[Guest]: and soothing to your ears.

04:39:17.960 --> 04:39:19.960
[Guest]: So, that's what the poem is talking about.

04:39:19.960 --> 04:39:21.960
[Guest]: But then, if one translates it,

04:39:21.960 --> 04:39:23.960
[Guest]: one would translate it

04:39:23.960 --> 04:39:25.960
[Guest]: into English, then it has to make sense.

04:39:25.960 --> 04:39:27.960
[Guest]: It cannot be just

04:39:27.960 --> 04:39:29.960
[Guest]: this.

04:39:29.960 --> 04:39:31.960
[Guest]: It has to have...

04:39:31.960 --> 04:39:33.960
[Guest]: There is another poem I have written, it's called

04:39:33.960 --> 04:39:35.960
[Guest]: Mai Sepahi Nahi.

04:39:35.960 --> 04:39:37.960
[Guest]: It's about, I am not a soldier,

04:39:37.960 --> 04:39:39.960
[Guest]: that I have been thrown into this.

04:39:39.960 --> 04:39:41.960
[Guest]: And,

04:39:41.960 --> 04:39:43.960
[Guest]: those who have thrown me, know that I am going to lose.

04:39:43.960 --> 04:39:45.960
[Guest]: And,

04:39:45.960 --> 04:39:47.960
[Guest]: I don't even know how to fight, but I am just fighting.

04:39:47.960 --> 04:39:49.960
[Guest]: And,

04:39:49.960 --> 04:39:51.960
[Guest]: I just want to tell you that,

04:39:51.960 --> 04:39:53.960
[Guest]: I am fighting, but I am not a soldier.

04:39:53.960 --> 04:39:55.960
[Guest]: That's what the poem is.

04:39:55.960 --> 04:39:57.960
[Guest]: So,

04:39:57.960 --> 04:39:59.960
[Guest]: yeah, I mean, that's how,

04:39:59.960 --> 04:40:01.960
[Guest]: I guess it,

04:40:01.960 --> 04:40:03.960
[Guest]: slowly, it happens.

04:40:03.960 --> 04:40:05.960
[Guest]: I guess I forgot what I was going on about.

04:40:05.960 --> 04:40:07.960
[Amit Varma]: No, no, this is a

04:40:07.960 --> 04:40:09.960
[Amit Varma]: lovely insight into the way you think

04:40:09.960 --> 04:40:11.960
[Amit Varma]: about writing. So, tell me something,

04:40:11.960 --> 04:40:13.960
[Amit Varma]: you've done screenplays, you've dabbled with that,

04:40:13.960 --> 04:40:15.960
[Amit Varma]: you've done a lot of lyric writing,

04:40:15.960 --> 04:40:17.960
[Amit Varma]: you are a poet, and

04:40:17.960 --> 04:40:19.960
[Amit Varma]: what is it

04:40:19.960 --> 04:40:21.960
[Amit Varma]: that you see yourself fundamentally

04:40:21.960 --> 04:40:23.960
[Amit Varma]: as if there is, like

04:40:23.960 --> 04:40:25.960
[Amit Varma]: in the sense that many artists will

04:40:25.960 --> 04:40:27.960
[Amit Varma]: say, this is my art and this is what

04:40:27.960 --> 04:40:29.960
[Amit Varma]: I do to pay the rent, right?

04:40:29.960 --> 04:40:31.960
[Amit Varma]: And that this is the stuff that I do

04:40:31.960 --> 04:40:33.960
[Amit Varma]: for work, but left to myself, if I

04:40:33.960 --> 04:40:35.960
[Amit Varma]: was not getting paid, this is

04:40:35.960 --> 04:40:37.960
[Amit Varma]: what I would do. And what you do though,

04:40:37.960 --> 04:40:39.960
[Amit Varma]: which you're not getting paid for is of course

04:40:39.960 --> 04:40:41.960
[Unknown]: the poetry, that's your labor of

04:40:41.960 --> 04:40:43.960
[Amit Varma]: love, but apart from that,

04:40:43.960 --> 04:40:45.960
[Amit Varma]: like, how do you see yourself?

04:40:45.960 --> 04:40:47.960
[Amit Varma]: Like, what is your conception of yourself now?

04:40:47.960 --> 04:40:49.960
[Amit Varma]: Are you a poet? Are you a writer?

04:40:49.960 --> 04:40:51.960
[Amit Varma]: Are you, you know, how would

04:40:51.960 --> 04:40:53.960
[Amit Varma]: you kind of define the things you want to do and

04:40:53.960 --> 04:40:55.960
[Guest]: what you are?

04:40:55.960 --> 04:40:57.960
[Guest]: Yeah, I think I'm more a writer

04:40:57.960 --> 04:40:59.960
[Guest]: now, but

04:40:59.960 --> 04:41:01.960
[Guest]: I mean,

04:41:01.960 --> 04:41:03.960
[Guest]: the base is my poetry.

04:41:03.960 --> 04:41:05.960
[Guest]: The base and

04:41:05.960 --> 04:41:07.960
[Guest]: I also like poems.

04:41:07.960 --> 04:41:09.960
[Guest]: I like Urdu poetry and poems.

04:41:09.960 --> 04:41:11.960
[Guest]: If I

04:41:11.960 --> 04:41:13.960
[Guest]: if I have to choose one out of everything,

04:41:13.960 --> 04:41:15.960
[Guest]: then I'll choose poems and poetry.

04:41:15.960 --> 04:41:17.960
[Guest]: There's no doubt about it.

04:41:17.960 --> 04:41:19.960
[Guest]: But there are a few things, I mean

04:41:19.960 --> 04:41:21.960
[Guest]: I think the poetry that I've

04:41:21.960 --> 04:41:23.960
[Guest]: done, I have never done any kind of

04:41:23.960 --> 04:41:25.960
[Guest]: brand collaborations.

04:41:25.960 --> 04:41:27.960
[Guest]: I have never tried to write

04:41:27.960 --> 04:41:29.960
[Guest]: for a brand per se.

04:41:29.960 --> 04:41:31.960
[Guest]: Yes, what I write, I will perform

04:41:31.960 --> 04:41:33.960
[Guest]: on stage and ask for compensation.

04:41:33.960 --> 04:41:35.960
[Guest]: That is true. But

04:41:35.960 --> 04:41:37.960
[Guest]: I will not write

04:41:37.960 --> 04:41:39.960
[Guest]: commissioned pieces.

04:41:39.960 --> 04:41:41.960
[Guest]: Rather, I will not perform

04:41:41.960 --> 04:41:43.960
[Unknown]: write and perform commissioned pieces.

04:41:43.960 --> 04:41:45.960
[Guest]: If there's an advertisement, they want me to

04:41:45.960 --> 04:41:47.960
[Guest]: write some poetry. If it's a biscuit, I will

04:41:47.960 --> 04:41:49.960
[Guest]: write it. But I'm not going

04:41:49.960 --> 04:41:51.960
[Guest]: to go on a stage and say,

04:41:51.960 --> 04:41:53.960
[Guest]: and I'm not going to put

04:41:53.960 --> 04:41:55.960
[Amit Varma]: my face and my name and my performance poetry on that.

04:41:55.960 --> 04:41:57.960
[Amit Varma]: You have said in one of your poems,

04:41:57.960 --> 04:41:59.960
[Amit Varma]: biscuit khao, your chai coffee, you speak

04:41:59.960 --> 04:42:01.960
[Unknown]: about having chai with biscuit instead of

04:42:01.960 --> 04:42:03.960
[Unknown]: coffee with muffin.

04:42:03.960 --> 04:42:05.960
[Guest]: I know what you're saying.

04:42:05.960 --> 04:42:07.960
[Guest]: Yeah, but it's not

04:42:07.960 --> 04:42:09.960
[Amit Varma]: because Parle-G is not sponsoring it.

04:42:09.960 --> 04:42:11.960
[Guest]: I know, I know.

04:42:11.960 --> 04:42:13.960
[Guest]: I didn't write it because Parle-G paid me.

04:42:13.960 --> 04:42:15.960
[Amit Varma]: I know, I know.

04:42:15.960 --> 04:42:17.960
[Guest]: That's something I've not done.

04:42:17.960 --> 04:42:19.960
[Guest]: And I know that

04:42:19.960 --> 04:42:21.960
[Guest]: I feel bad about it,

04:42:21.960 --> 04:42:23.960
[Guest]: but it's my fault too.

04:42:23.960 --> 04:42:25.960
[Guest]: If you

04:42:25.960 --> 04:42:27.960
[Guest]: don't stand in the market

04:42:27.960 --> 04:42:29.960
[Guest]: and are not ready to sell yourself,

04:42:29.960 --> 04:42:31.960
[Guest]: what will you give to others?

04:42:31.960 --> 04:42:33.960
[Guest]: After that, this whole

04:42:33.960 --> 04:42:35.960
[Guest]: spoken word poetry business began,

04:42:35.960 --> 04:42:37.960
[Guest]: sponsorships and everything started becoming,

04:42:37.960 --> 04:42:39.960
[Guest]: money started flowing in.

04:42:39.960 --> 04:42:41.960
[Guest]: And I was like, no, this poetry

04:42:41.960 --> 04:42:43.960
[Guest]: is sacred for me.

04:42:43.960 --> 04:42:45.960
[Guest]: And we just kept looking at people.

04:42:45.960 --> 04:42:47.960
[Guest]: Anyway, so poetry is something

04:42:47.960 --> 04:42:49.960
[Guest]: that

04:42:49.960 --> 04:42:51.960
[Guest]: is private

04:42:51.960 --> 04:42:53.960
[Guest]: to me in a sense, and I would

04:42:53.960 --> 04:42:55.960
[Guest]: want to keep it that way. I would not

04:42:55.960 --> 04:42:57.960
[Guest]: want to commercialize it.

04:42:57.960 --> 04:42:59.960
[Guest]: That's why I never made a YouTube

04:42:59.960 --> 04:43:01.960
[Guest]: channel or anything.

04:43:01.960 --> 04:43:03.960
[Guest]: I might make it, but if I make it,

04:43:03.960 --> 04:43:05.960
[Guest]: it's not for the money.

04:43:05.960 --> 04:43:07.960
[Guest]: It would be just that I'm fed up

04:43:07.960 --> 04:43:09.960
[Guest]: and I want to put my work somewhere.

04:43:09.960 --> 04:43:11.960
[Guest]: That would be the only reason.

04:43:11.960 --> 04:43:13.960
[Guest]: Other than that,

04:43:13.960 --> 04:43:15.960
[Guest]: I like writing lyrics.

04:43:15.960 --> 04:43:17.960
[Guest]: I really like

04:43:17.960 --> 04:43:19.960
[Guest]: collaborating with music

04:43:19.960 --> 04:43:21.960
[Guest]: and writing,

04:43:21.960 --> 04:43:23.960
[Guest]: bringing in new words,

04:43:23.960 --> 04:43:25.960
[Guest]: and I don't have any stock songs.

04:43:25.960 --> 04:43:27.960
[Guest]: I write on what I'm told.

04:43:27.960 --> 04:43:29.960
[Guest]: And I try a lot,

04:43:29.960 --> 04:43:31.960
[Guest]: and every time, I'm like,

04:43:31.960 --> 04:43:33.960
[Guest]: this time, everyone will know

04:43:33.960 --> 04:43:35.960
[Guest]: that he doesn't know anything.

04:43:35.960 --> 04:43:37.960
[Guest]: So, I have to prove

04:43:37.960 --> 04:43:39.960
[Guest]: that I have to ensure

04:43:39.960 --> 04:43:41.960
[Guest]: that the other person doesn't know that it's a fraud.

04:43:41.960 --> 04:43:43.960
[Guest]: Okay?

04:43:43.960 --> 04:43:45.960
[Amit Varma]: So, this challenge

04:43:45.960 --> 04:43:47.960
[Guest]: whether or not

04:43:47.960 --> 04:43:49.960
[Guest]: anyone else does it on me, it definitely works.

04:43:49.960 --> 04:43:51.960
[Guest]: Like, bro, he'll fire you.

04:43:51.960 --> 04:43:53.960
[Guest]: Write it.

04:43:53.960 --> 04:43:55.960
[Guest]: So, this works.

04:43:55.960 --> 04:43:57.960
[Guest]: So, I like lyrics

04:43:57.960 --> 04:43:59.960
[Guest]: with music. When it's made,

04:43:59.960 --> 04:44:01.960
[Guest]: the process, I mean, you know,

04:44:01.960 --> 04:44:03.960
[Guest]: when you make a good song,

04:44:03.960 --> 04:44:05.960
[Guest]: and the other person also wants to make a good song,

04:44:05.960 --> 04:44:07.960
[Guest]: and the singer is also putting,

04:44:07.960 --> 04:44:09.960
[Guest]: and the orchestra coming in,

04:44:09.960 --> 04:44:11.960
[Guest]: and the music director is constantly trying to make it better,

04:44:11.960 --> 04:44:13.960
[Guest]: it's a very good feeling.

04:44:13.960 --> 04:44:15.960
[Guest]: Especially when there's a collaborative effort

04:44:15.960 --> 04:44:17.960
[Guest]: with the music director.

04:44:17.960 --> 04:44:19.960
[Guest]: Screenplay and dialogue,

04:44:19.960 --> 04:44:21.960
[Guest]: I realize that I find it

04:44:21.960 --> 04:44:23.960
[Guest]: much more, it's like a

04:44:23.960 --> 04:44:25.960
[Unknown]: bigger canvas.

04:44:25.960 --> 04:44:27.960
[Guest]: So, I'm not,

04:44:27.960 --> 04:44:29.960
[Guest]: even though I understand the craft

04:44:29.960 --> 04:44:31.960
[Guest]: and I know how to do it,

04:44:31.960 --> 04:44:33.960
[Guest]: and of course I'm not great at it,

04:44:33.960 --> 04:44:35.960
[Guest]: but I'm good at it

04:44:35.960 --> 04:44:37.960
[Guest]: and I can be much better.

04:44:37.960 --> 04:44:39.960
[Guest]: It's just that

04:44:39.960 --> 04:44:41.960
[Guest]: it still involves

04:44:41.960 --> 04:44:43.960
[Guest]: more part of my head

04:44:43.960 --> 04:44:45.960
[Guest]: than my instinct

04:44:45.960 --> 04:44:47.960
[Unknown]: as of today, is what I largely understand.

04:44:47.960 --> 04:44:49.960
[Guest]: I think the instinct

04:44:49.960 --> 04:44:51.960
[Guest]: is something I apply more towards

04:44:51.960 --> 04:44:53.960
[Guest]: the structuring of the story

04:44:53.960 --> 04:44:55.960
[Guest]: and the way I lay out the scenes

04:44:55.960 --> 04:44:57.960
[Guest]: and things like that,

04:44:57.960 --> 04:44:59.960
[Unknown]: but it's largely mathematical.

04:44:59.960 --> 04:45:01.960
[Guest]: My mind is more focused on that.

04:45:01.960 --> 04:45:03.960
[Guest]: I feel that when I learn

04:45:03.960 --> 04:45:05.960
[Guest]: the craft better,

04:45:05.960 --> 04:45:07.960
[Guest]: I will be able to play it

04:45:07.960 --> 04:45:09.960
[Guest]: more instinctively

04:45:09.960 --> 04:45:11.960
[Guest]: the way I have

04:45:11.960 --> 04:45:13.960
[Guest]: always done in poetry,

